FS7 OIL QUANTITY.name: fs7 oil quantity
FS7 OIL QUANTITY.description: This is an imperial unit derived from quarts and gallons and only used when dealing with engine oil amounts. The formula used to derive the unit is: VALUE * ((8 / 32767) * (0.25 * (3.785411784 * 0.001)))

KELVIN.name: kelvin
KELVIN.description: The kelvin is the base unit of temperature in the International System of Units (SI). The kelvin is the primary unit of temperature measurement for the physical sciences, but is often used in conjunction with the degree Celsius - which has the same magnitude - where 0 kelvin (called "Absolute Zero") corresponds to a temperature of -273.15°C. "Absolute Zero" is the equivalent -459.67°F.

RANKINE.name: rankine
RANKINE.description: The Rankine is a base unit of temperature, similar to the kelvin as 0 Rankine is the same as "Absolute Zero" kelvin. However the difference of 1 Rankine is defined as equal to 1 Fahrenheit degree, rather than the Celsius degree used on the kelvin scale. A temperature of 0K is equal to 0R which is the equivalent of -273.15°C or -459.67°F.

FARENHEIT.name: farenheit, fahrenheit
FARENHEIT.description: The Fahrenheit scale is a temperature scale based on two fixed points: the temperature at which pure water ice melts (32°F) and the temperature at which water boils (212°F) both at sea level and under standard atmospheric pressure. 0°F is equal to 255.372K, 459.67R or -17.7778°C.

FAHRENHEIT.name: farenheit, fahrenheit
FAHRENHEIT.description: The Fahrenheit scale is a temperature scale based on two fixed points: the temperature at which pure water ice melts (32°F) and the temperature at which water boils (212°F) both at sea level and under standard atmospheric pressure. 0°F is equal to 255.372K, 459.67R or -17.7778°C.

CELSIUS.name: celsius
CELSIUS.description: The Celsius scale is a temperature scale based on 0°C for the freezing point of water and 100 °C for the boiling point of water at 1 atmosphere of pressure. 0°C is equal to 273.15K, 491.67R or 32°F

CELSIUS FS7 EGT.name: celsius fs7 egt
CELSIUS FS7 EGT.description: This the same as the Celsius unit only scaled by the following formula: VALUE / (1.8 * (6144 / 2060)).

CELSIUS FS7 OIL TEMP.name: celsius fs7 oil temp
CELSIUS FS7 OIL TEMP.description: This the same as the Celsius unit only scaled by the following formula: (VALUE - 273.15) * (16384 / 140.0). It is only used when dealing with engine oil temperature.

CELSIUS SCALER 1/256.name: celsius scaler 1/256
CELSIUS SCALER 1/256.description: This unit is for degrees Celsius scaled by 1/256, eg: VALUE / 256.

CELSIUS SCALER 256.name: celsius scaler 256
CELSIUS SCALER 256.description: This unit is for degrees Celsius scaled by 256, eg: VALUE * 256.

CELSIUS SCALER 16K.name: celsius scaler 16k
CELSIUS SCALER 16K.description: This unit is for degrees Celsius scaled by 16K, eg: VALUE * 16384.0.

RADIAN.name: radian, radians
RADIAN.description: The radian is the base unit of temperature in the International System of Units (SI). One radian is defined as the angle subtended from the center of a circle which intercepts an arc equal in length to the radius of the circle. 1 radian is equivalent to 57.296°.

RADIANS.name: radian, radians

DEGREE LATITUDE.name: degree latitude, degrees latitude
DEGREE LATITUDE.description: A degree latitude is an angle used to measure the geographic position along the North-South axis of the Earth, over it's surface. Degrees latitude range from 0° at the Equator to +90° at the North pole or -90° at the South pole.

DEGREE LONGITUDE.name: degree longitude, degrees longitude
DEGREE LONGITUDE.description: A degree longitude is an angle used to measure the geographic position along the East-West axis of the Earth, over it's surface. Degrees longitude range from 0° at the Prime Meridian to +180° Eastward and -180° Westward.

DEGREES LONGITUDE.name: degree longitude, degrees longitude
DEGREES LONGITUDE.description: A degree longitude is an angle used to measure the geographic position along the East-West axis of the Earth, over it's surface. Degrees longitude range from 0° at the Prime Meridian to +180° Eastward and -180° Westward.

METERS LATITUDE.name: meter latitude, meters latitude

RADIAN/SECOND.name: radian per second, radians per second

RADIANS/SECOND.name: radian per second, radians per second

KNOT.name: knot, knots

MACH.name: mach, machs
MACH.description: A mach number is a unit of of both speed and velocity based on an aircraft's speed relative to the speed of sound. An aircraft travelling at mach 1 is equivalent to 1234.8kph or 767.27mph.

MACHS.name: mach, machs

METER/SECOND SQUARED.name: meter per second squared, meters per second squared

GFORCE.name: Gforce, G Force

A g-force of 1g is equal to the conventional value of gravitational acceleration on Earth - about 9.8 meters per second squared, or 32.174 feet per second squared.

SECOND.name: second, seconds
SECOND.description: The second is the base unit of time in the International System of Units (SI), defined as 1⁄86400 of a day, or more accurately as being equal to the time duration of 9,192,631,770 periods of the radiation corresponding to the transition between the two hyperfine levels of the fundamental unperturbed ground-state of the caesium-133 atom.

SECONDS.name: second, seconds

MINUTE.name: minute, minutes

MINUTES.name: minute, minutes

HOUR.name: hour, hours

HOURS.name: hour, hours

DAY.name: day, days

DAYS.name: day, days

YEAR.name: year, years

YEARS.name: year, years

          IMPORTANT! SimVars that use this unit actually require a value in liters per second (0.264172 gallons per second). This is a hold-over from the legacy FSX simulation.

PA.name: pascal, pascals, Pa
PA.description: The pascal is the SI derived unit of pressure used to quantify internal pressure. The unit, is defined as one newton per square meter.

KILOPASCAL.name: kilopascal, kpa
KILOPASCAL.description: This is a measure of pressure equivalent to 1,000 pascal (103 pascal).

KPA.name: kilopascal, kpa
KPA.description: This is a measure of pressure equivalent to 1,000 pascal (103 pascal).

MILLIMETER OF MERCURY.name: millimeter of mercury, millimeters of mercury, mmHg
MILLIMETER OF MERCURY.description: A millimeter of mercury is a unit of pressure. It is defined as the extra pressure generated by a column of mercury one millimeter high under the force of 1 gravity. It is equivalent to 133.322 pascals, or 0.019337psi.

MILLIMETERS OF MERCURY.name: millimeter of mercury, millimeters of mercury, mmHg
MILLIMETERS OF MERCURY.description: A millimeter of mercury is a unit of pressure. It is defined as the extra pressure generated by a column of mercury one millimeter high under the force of 1 gravity. It is equivalent to 133.322 pascals, or 0.019337psi.

MMHG.name: millimeter of mercury, millimeters of mercury, mmHg
MMHG.description: A millimeter of mercury is a unit of pressure. It is defined as the extra pressure generated by a column of mercury one millimeter high under the force of 1 gravity. It is equivalent to 133.322 pascals, or 0.019337psi.

CENTIMETER OF MERCURY.name: centimeter of mercury, centimeters of mercury, cmHg
CENTIMETER OF MERCURY.description: A centimeter of mercury is a unit of pressure. It is defined as the extra pressure generated by a column of mercury one centimeter high under the force of 1 gravity. It is equivalent to 1333.223 pascals, or 0.193367psi.

CENTIMETERS OF MERCURY.name: centimeter of mercury, centimeters of mercury, cmHg
CENTIMETERS OF MERCURY.description: A centimeter of mercury is a unit of pressure. It is defined as the extra pressure generated by a column of mercury one centimeter high under the force of 1 gravity. It is equivalent to 1333.223 pascals, or 0.193367psi.

CMHG.name: centimeter of mercury, centimeters of mercury, cmHg
CMHG.description: A centimeter of mercury is a unit of pressure. It is defined as the extra pressure generated by a column of mercury one centimeter high under the force of 1 gravity. It is equivalent to 1333.223 pascals, or 0.193367psi.

INCH OF MERCURY.name: inch of mercury, inches of mercury, inHg
INCH OF MERCURY.description: An inch of mercury is a unit of pressure. It is defined as the extra pressure generated by a column of mercury one centimeter high under the force of 1 gravity. It is equivalent to 3386.39 pascals, or 0.491154psi.

INCHES OF MERCURY.name: inch of mercury, inches of mercury, inHg
INCHES OF MERCURY.description: An inch of mercury is a unit of pressure. It is defined as the extra pressure generated by a column of mercury one centimeter high under the force of 1 gravity. It is equivalent to 3386.39 pascals, or 0.491154psi.

INHG.name: inch of mercury, inches of mercury, inHg
INHG.description: An inch of mercury is a unit of pressure. It is defined as the extra pressure generated by a column of mercury one centimeter high under the force of 1 gravity. It is equivalent to 3386.39 pascals, or 0.491154psi.

INHG 64 OVER 64K.name: inHg 64 over 64k
INHG 64 OVER 64K.description: This unit is for inches of mercury, only the value has been scaled using the following formula: (64.0 / 65536.0) * VALUE. Generally only required for describing units of manifold pressure.

MILLIMETER OF WATER.name: millimeter of water, millimeters of water
MILLIMETER OF WATER.description: A millimeter of water is a unit of pressure. It is defined as the extra pressure generated by a column of water 1 mm high with a density of 1 gram per cubic centimeter, under the force of 1 gravity. It is equivalent to 9.80638 pascals, or 0.0014223psi.

MILLIMETERS OF WATER.name: millimeter of water, millimeters of water
MILLIMETERS OF WATER.description: A millimeter of water is a unit of pressure. It is defined as the extra pressure generated by a column of water 1 mm high with a density of 1 gram per cubic centimeter, under the force of 1 gravity. It is equivalent to 9.80638 pascals, or 0.0014223psi.

NEWTON/SQUARE METER.name: Newton per square meter, newtons per square meter
NEWTON/SQUARE METER.description: Newtons per square meter is a unit that shows how the pascal unit is derived from other SI units. 1 newton per square meter equals 1 pascal.

NEWTONS/SQUARE METER.name: Newton per square meter, newtons per square meter
NEWTONS/SQUARE METER.description: Newtons per square meter is a unit that shows how the pascal unit is derived from other SI units. 1 newton per square meter equals 1 pascal.

KILOGRAM FORCE/SQUARE CENTIMETER.name: kilogram force per square centimeter, KgFSqCm
KILOGRAM FORCE/SQUARE CENTIMETER.description: Kilogram force per square centimeter is a unit of pressure which is not a part of the International System of Units (SI). It is equivalent to 98066.5 pascals, or 14.2233psi.

KGFSQCM.name: kilogram force per square centimeter, KgFSqCm
KGFSQCM.description: Kilogram force per square centimeter is a unit of pressure which is not a part of the International System of Units (SI). It is equivalent to 98066.5 pascals, or 14.2233psi.

KILOGRAM METER SQUARED.name: kilogram meter squared, kilograms meter squared
KILOGRAM METER SQUARED.description: Kilograms per square meter is a unit of measurement of surface density. It is equivalent to 9.80665 pascals, or 0.001423psi.

KILOGRAMS METER SQUARED.name: kilogram meter squared, kilograms meter squared
KILOGRAMS METER SQUARED.description: Kilograms per square meter is a unit of measurement of surface density. It is equivalent to 9.80665 pascals, or 0.001423psi.

ATMOSPHERE.name: atmosphere, atmospheres, atm
ATMOSPHERE.description: The atmosphere is a unit of pressure defined as approximately equal to Earth's atmospheric pressure at sea level. It is equivalent to 101325 pascals, or 14.6959psi.

ATMOSPHERES.name: atmosphere, atmospheres, atm
ATMOSPHERES.description: The atmosphere is a unit of pressure defined as approximately equal to Earth's atmospheric pressure at sea level. It is equivalent to 101325 pascals, or 14.6959psi.

ATM.name: atmosphere, atmospheres, atm
ATM.description: The atmosphere is a unit of pressure defined as approximately equal to Earth's atmospheric pressure at sea level. It is equivalent to 101325 pascals, or 14.6959psi.

BAR.name: bar, bars
BAR.description: The bar is a metric unit of pressure, but not part of the International System of Units (SI). It is defined as exactly equal to 100,000 pascals, equivalent to 14.50378psi.

BARS.name: bar, bars
BARS.description: The bar is a metric unit of pressure, but not part of the International System of Units (SI). It is defined as exactly equal to 100,000 pascals, equivalent to 14.50378psi.

MILLIBAR.name: millibar, millibars, mbar, mbars, hectopascal, hectopascals
MILLIBAR.description: The millibar is a metric unit of pressure, but not part of the International System of Units (SI). It is defined as exactly equal to 1000 pascals, equivalent to 0.0145psi.

MILLIBARS.name: millibar, millibars, mbar, mbars, hectopascal, hectopascals
MILLIBARS.description: The millibar is a metric unit of pressure, but not part of the International System of Units (SI). It is defined as exactly equal to 1000 pascals, equivalent to 0.0145psi.

MBAR.name: millibar, millibars, mbar, mbars, hectopascal, hectopascals
MBAR.description: The millibar is a metric unit of pressure, but not part of the International System of Units (SI). It is defined as exactly equal to 1000 pascals, equivalent to 0.0145psi.

MBARS.name: millibar, millibars, mbar, mbars, hectopascal, hectopascals
MBARS.description: The millibar is a metric unit of pressure, but not part of the International System of Units (SI). It is defined as exactly equal to 1000 pascals, equivalent to 0.0145psi.

HECTOPASCAL.name: millibar, millibars, mbar, mbars, hectopascal, hectopascals
HECTOPASCAL.description: The millibar is a metric unit of pressure, but not part of the International System of Units (SI). It is defined as exactly equal to 1000 pascals, equivalent to 0.0145psi.

HECTOPASCALS.name: millibar, millibars, mbar, mbars, hectopascal, hectopascals
HECTOPASCALS.description: The millibar is a metric unit of pressure, but not part of the International System of Units (SI). It is defined as exactly equal to 1000 pascals, equivalent to 0.0145psi.

MILLIBAR SCALER 16.name: millibar scaler 16, millibars scaler 16
MILLIBAR SCALER 16.description: This unit is the same as the millibar (above), only scaled by a factor of 1/16, ie: VALUE / 16;

MILLIBARS SCALER 16.name: millibar scaler 16, millibars scaler 16
MILLIBARS SCALER 16.description: This unit is the same as the millibar (above), only scaled by a factor of 1/16, ie: VALUE / 16;

POUND FORCE/SQUARE INCH.name: pound-force per square inch, psi
POUND FORCE/SQUARE INCH.description: The pound-force per square inch is an imperial unit of pressure. It is equivalent to 6894.76 pascals.

PSI.name: pound-force per square inch, psi
PSI.description: The pound-force per square inch is an imperial unit of pressure. It is equivalent to 6894.76 pascals.

PSI SCALER 16K.name: psi scaler 16k
PSI SCALER 16K.description: This is the psi value scaled by 16K, using the formula: VALUE / 16384.0

PSI 4 OVER 16K.name: psi 4 over 16k
PSI 4 OVER 16K.description: This is the psi value scaled using the formula: (4 / 16384.0) * VALUE

PSI FS7 OIL PRESSURE.name: psi fs7 oil pressure
PSI FS7 OIL PRESSURE.description: This is the psi value scaled using the formula: (55.0 / 16384) * VALUE. Only usually used when dealing with engine oil pressure.

PSF.name: pound-force per square foot, psf
PSF.description: The pound-force per square foot is an imperial unit of pressure. It is equivalent to 47.8803 pascals.

PSF SCALER 16K.name: psf scaler 16k
PSF SCALER 16K.description: This is the psf value scaled by 16K, using the formula: VALUE / 16384.0

SLUG FEET SQUARED.name: slug feet squared, slugs feet squared
SLUG FEET SQUARED.description: The slug square foot is a unit of moment of inertia in imperial units. It is equivalent to 32.17405 pound foot squared, or 1.35582 Kilogram Square Meters.

SLUGS FEET SQUARED.name: slug feet squared, slugs feet squared
SLUGS FEET SQUARED.description: The slug square foot is a unit of moment of inertia in imperial units. It is equivalent to 32.17405 pound foot squared, or 1.35582 Kilogram Square Meters.

BOOST CMHG.name: boost cmHg
BOOST CMHG.description: A centimeter of mercury is a unit of pressure. It is defined as the extra pressure generated by a column of mercury one centimeter high under the force of 1 gravity. It is equivalent to 1333.223 pascals, or 0.193367psi. This unit is used when defining the boost provided by superchargers or turbochargers on equipped planes.

BOOST INHG.name: boost inHg
BOOST INHG.description: An inch of mercury is a unit of pressure. It is defined as the extra pressure generated by a column of mercury one centimeter high under the force of 1 gravity. It is equivalent to 3386.39 pascals, or 0.491154psi. This unit is used when defining the boost provided by superchargers or turbochargers on equipped planes.

BOOST PSI.name: boost psi
BOOST PSI.description: The pound-force per square inch is an imperial unit of pressure. It is equivalent to 6894.76 pascals. This unit is used when defining the boost provided by superchargers or turbochargers on equipped planes.

NEWTON METER.name: Newton meter, Newton, meters, nm
NEWTON METER.description: The newton meter is a unit of torque in the International System of Units (SI). One newton-metre is equal to the torque resulting from a force of one newton applied perpendicularly to the end of a moment arm that is one metre long.

NEWTON.name: Newton meter, Newton, meters, nm
NEWTON.description: The newton meter is a unit of torque in the International System of Units (SI). One newton-metre is equal to the torque resulting from a force of one newton applied perpendicularly to the end of a moment arm that is one metre long.

NM.name: Newton meter, Newton, meters, nm
NM.description: The newton meter is a unit of torque in the International System of Units (SI). One newton-metre is equal to the torque resulting from a force of one newton applied perpendicularly to the end of a moment arm that is one metre long.

FOOT POUND.name: foot-pound, foot pound, ft-lbs, foot-pounds
FOOT POUND.description: The foot-pound is a unit of energy in the imperial unit of measure. It is the energy transferred upon applying a force of one pound-force through a linear displacement of one foot. The corresponding SI unit is the joule.

FT LBS.name: foot-pound, foot pound, ft-lbs, foot-pounds
FT LBS.description: The foot-pound is a unit of energy in the imperial unit of measure. It is the energy transferred upon applying a force of one pound-force through a linear displacement of one foot. The corresponding SI unit is the joule.

FOOT POUNDS.name: foot-pound, foot pound, ft-lbs, foot-pounds
FOOT POUNDS.description: The foot-pound is a unit of energy in the imperial unit of measure. It is the energy transferred upon applying a force of one pound-force through a linear displacement of one foot. The corresponding SI unit is the joule.

LBF FEET.name: lbf-feet
LBF FEET.description: A pound-foot is a unit of torque representing one pound of force acting at a perpendicular distance of one foot from a pivot point. Conversely one pound-foot is the moment about an axis that applies one pound-force at a radius of one foot.

KILOGRAM METER.name: kilogram meter, kilogram meters, kgf meter, kgf meters
KILOGRAM METER.description: A kilogram-force meter is an International System of Units (SI) unit of torque representing one kilogram-force applied perpendicularly to a one-meter long moment arm.

KILOGRAM METERS.name: kilogram meter, kilogram meters, kgf meter, kgf meters
KILOGRAM METERS.description: A kilogram-force meter is an International System of Units (SI) unit of torque representing one kilogram-force applied perpendicularly to a one-meter long moment arm.

KGF METER.name: kilogram meter, kilogram meters, kgf meter, kgf meters
KGF METER.description: A kilogram-force meter is an International System of Units (SI) unit of torque representing one kilogram-force applied perpendicularly to a one-meter long moment arm.

KGF METERS.name: kilogram meter, kilogram meters, kgf meter, kgf meters
KGF METERS.description: A kilogram-force meter is an International System of Units (SI) unit of torque representing one kilogram-force applied perpendicularly to a one-meter long moment arm.

POUNDAL FEET.name: poundal feet
POUNDAL FEET.description: One poundal is the force that accelerates a mass of 1 pound at a rate of one foot per second per second. So a poundal foot is a unit of torque representing one poundal of force acting at a perpendicular distance of one foot from a pivot point.

FRACTIONALLATLONDIGITS.name: FractionalLatLonDigits
FRACTIONALLATLONDIGITS.description: The number of fractional lat / lon digits.

PART.name: part
PART.description: This is a base unit that will be used to make conversions when using other units in RPN and SimVar calculations.

THIRD.name: third, thirds
THIRD.description: The input will be divided by 3.

THIRDS.name: third, thirds
THIRDS.description: The input will be divided by 3.

PERCENT.name: percent, percentage
PERCENT.description: Normally a value between 0 and 100, though sometimes values outside this range are possible (reverse thrust, for example).

PERCENTAGE.name: percent, percentage
PERCENTAGE.description: Normally a value between 0 and 100, though sometimes values outside this range are possible (reverse thrust, for example).

PERCENT OVER 100.name: percent over 100
PERCENT OVER 100.description: Normally a value between 0.0 and 1.0, though sometimes values outside this range are possible (reverse thrust, for example).

PERCENT SCALER 16K.name: percent scaler 16k
PERCENT SCALER 16K.description: This is a precentage value scaled by 16K, using the formula: VALUE / 16384.0

PERCENT SCALER 32K.name: percent scaler 32k
PERCENT SCALER 32K.description: This is a precentage value scaled by 32K, using the formula: VALUE / 32767.0

PERCENT SCALER 2POW23.name: percent scaler 2pow23
PERCENT SCALER 2POW23.description: This is a precentage value scaled by 223, using the formula: VALUE / 8388608.0

BEL.name: bel, bels
BEL.description: The bel is a unit used in the comparison of power levels in electrical communication or of intensities of sound, corresponding to an intensity ratio of 10 to 1.

BELS.name: bel, bels
BELS.description: The bel is a unit used in the comparison of power levels in electrical communication or of intensities of sound, corresponding to an intensity ratio of 10 to 1.

DECIBEL.name: decibel, decibels
DECIBEL.description: The decibel is a relative unit of measurement equal to one tenth of a bel.

DECIBELS.name: decibel, decibels
DECIBELS.description: The decibel is a relative unit of measurement equal to one tenth of a bel.

MORE THAN A HALF.name: more_than_a_half
MORE THAN A HALF.description: The input will be converted to either 0 (if it is less than a half of the "part" base value) or 1 (if it is more than half of the "part" base value)

TIMES.name: times
TIMES.description: The input value is a multiplier.

RATIO.name: ratio
RATIO.description: The input value is expected to be a ratio.

NUMBER.name: number, numbers
NUMBER.description: The input value is expected to be any real number.

NUMBERS.name: number, numbers
NUMBERS.description: The input value is expected to be any real number.

SCALER.name: scaler
SCALER.description: The input value is expected to be a scaler.

POSITION.name: position, position 16K, position 32K, position 128
POSITION.description: The input value will be converted to an integer position value either using the "part" base scale, or as a value between 0 and 16843, or 0 and , or as an integer between 0 and 128.

POSITION 16K.name: position, position 16K, position 32K, position 128
POSITION 16K.description: The input value will be converted to an integer position value either using the "part" base scale, or as a value between 0 and 16843, or 0 and , or as an integer between 0 and 128.

POSITION 32K.name: position, position 16K, position 32K, position 128
POSITION 32K.description: The input value will be converted to an integer position value either using the "part" base scale, or as a value between 0 and 16843, or 0 and , or as an integer between 0 and 128.

POSITION 128.name: position, position 16K, position 32K, position 128
POSITION 128.description: The input value will be converted to an integer position value either using the "part" base scale, or as a value between 0 and 16843, or 0 and , or as an integer between 0 and 128.

ENUM.name: Enum
ENUM.description: A positive or negative integer corresponding to the member of the enum

BOOL.name: Bool, Boolean
BOOL.description: The only reliable numeric equivalent is that 0 is returned for False. Non-zero values, especially both 1 and -1, are used to indicate True.

BOOLEAN.name: Bool, Boolean
BOOLEAN.description: The only reliable numeric equivalent is that 0 is returned for False. Non-zero values, especially both 1 and -1, are used to indicate True.

BCO16.name: Bco16
BCO16.description: This unit requires a four digit octal number, and is usually only used for transponder codes.

MASK.name: mask
MASK.description: This indicates that the value is a bitmask where one or more bits in the value will be true/false, and each bit will represent a specific item.

FLAGS.name: flags
FLAGS.description: This indicates a selection of one or more flag values combined into a single value.

STRING.name: string
STRING.description: This unit expects some kind of string input.

PER RADIAN.name: per radian
PER RADIAN.description: The input is value that will be a ratio "per radian".

PER DEGREE.name: per degree
PER DEGREE.description: The input is value that will be a ratio "per degree".

KEYFRAME.name: keyframe, keyframes
KEYFRAME.description: The input is for an animation keyframe and will be divided by 200.

KEYFRAMES.name: keyframe, keyframes
KEYFRAMES.description: The input is for an animation keyframe and will be divided by 200.

XYZ.name: XYZ
XYZ.description:
This unit signifies a 3 value struct with the values (all 32bit floats):
          
            x - a value representing an X position
            y - a value representing an Y position
            z - a value representing an Z position
          
          This struct unit is required by the following SimVars:
          
            STRUCT_BODY_ROTATION_ACCELERATION 
            STRUCT_BODY_ROTATION_VELOCITY 
            STRUCT_BODY_VELOCITY
            STRUCT_ENGINE_POSITION
            STRUCT_EYEPOINT_DYNAMIC_ANGLE
            STRUCT_EYEPOINT_DYNAMIC_OFFSET
            STRUCT_SURFACE_RELATIVE_VELOCITY
            STRUCT_WORLDVELOCITY
            STRUCT_WORLD_ACCELERATION
            STRUCT_WORLD_ROTATION_VELOCITY

PBH.name: PBH
PBH.description:
This unit signifies a 3 value struct with the values (all 32bit integers):
          
            pitch - the pitch value
            bank - the bank value
            heading - the heading value
          
          This struct unit is required by the following SimVars:
          
            LANDING_LIGHT_PBH
            STRUCT_PBH32

LATLONALTPBH.name: latlonaltpbh
LATLONALTPBH.description:
This unit signifies a 6 value struct with the values:
          
            lat - a latitude, expressed as a 64bit integer where the first 16bits are padding, the next 32bits are the integer value and the last 16bits are the fraction.
            lon - a longitude, expressed as 64bit integer where the lower 16bits are the fractional part, the upper 32 bits are the integer part and the rest is padding.
            alt - an altitude, expressed as a 64bit integer where the first 16bits are padding, the next 32bits are the integer value and the last 16bits are the fraction.
            pitch - the pitch value, expressed as 32bit integer
            bank - the bank value, expressed as 32bit integer
            heading - the heading value, expressed as 32bit integer
          
          This struct unit is required by the following SimVars:
          
            STRUCT_LATLONALTPBH

LATLONALT.name: latlonalt
LATLONALT.description:
This unit signifies a 6 value struct with the values:
          
            lat - a latitude, expressed as a 64bit integer where the first 16bits are padding, the next 32bits are the integer value and the last 16bits are the fraction.
            lon - a longitude, expressed as 64bit integer where the lower 16bits are the fractional part, the upper 32 bits are the integer part and the rest is padding.
            alt - an altitude, expressed as a 64bit integer where the first 16bits are padding, the next 32bits are the integer value and the last 16bits are the fraction.
          
          This struct unit is required by the following SimVars:
          
            ADF LATLONALT
            INNER_MARKER_LATLONALT
            MIDDLE_MARKER_LATLONALT
            NAV_DME_LATLONALT
            NAV_GS_LATLONALT
            NAV_VOR_LATLONALT
            OUTER_MARKER_LATLONALT
            STRUCT_LATLONALT

PID STRUCT.name: PID_STRUCT
PID STRUCT.description:
This unit signifies a 7 value struct containing PID controller state with the values (all 64bit floats):
          
            pid_p - the proportional value
            pid_i - the first integral value
            pid_i2 - the second integral value
            pid_d - the proportional value
            i_boundary - the first integral boundary value
            i2_boundary - the second integral boundary value
            d_boundary - the derivative boundary value
          
          This struct is returned by the following SimVars:
          
            STRUC_AIRSPEED_HOLD_PID_CONSTS
            STRUC_HEADING_HOLD_PID_CONSTS

POILIST.name: POIList
POILIST.description: This unit signifies that the returned value is an array of POI data. This unit is only used within the JS for HTML gauges.

GLASSCOCKPITSETTINGS.name: GlassCockpitSettings
GLASSCOCKPITSETTINGS.description:
This unit is only used when retrieving the cockpit struct within the JS for HTML gauges.
          For the contents of this struct, please see the section on the Glass Cockpit Settings Struct.

FUELLEVELS.name: FuelLevels
FUELLEVELS.description:
This unit is for retrieving the fuel levels of all tanks and will return a struct containing the following values (all 32bit floats):
          
            Center
            LeftMain
            RightMain
            LeftAux
            RightAux
            LeftTip
            RightTip
            Center2
            Center3
            External1
            External2

AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED ACQUISITION.name: AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED ACQUISITION
AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED ACQUISITION.description: Currently not used within the simulation.

AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED HOLD.name: AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED HOLD
AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED HOLD.description: returns whether airspeed hold is active (1, TRUE) or not (0, FALSE).

AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED HOLD CURRENT.name: AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED HOLD CURRENT
AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED HOLD CURRENT.description: Currently not used within the simulation.

AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED HOLD VAR.name: AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED HOLD VAR
AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED HOLD VAR.description: Returns the target holding airspeed for the autopilot.

AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED MAX CALCULATED.name: AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED MAX CALCULATED
AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED MAX CALCULATED.description: Returns the maximum calculated airspeed (kcas) limit set for the autopilot.

AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED MIN CALCULATED.name: AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED MIN CALCULATED
AUTOPILOT AIRSPEED MIN CALCULATED.description: Returns the minimum calculated airspeed (kcas) limit set for the autopilot.

AUTOPILOT ALT RADIO MODE.name: AUTOPILOT ALT RADIO MODE
AUTOPILOT ALT RADIO MODE.description: If enabled the Autopilot will use the Radio Altitude rather than the Indicated Altitude.

AUTOPILOT ALTITUDE ARM.name: AUTOPILOT ALTITUDE ARM
AUTOPILOT ALTITUDE ARM.description: Returns whether the autopilot is in Altitude Arm mode (1, TRUE) or not (0, FALSE).

AUTOPILOT ALTITUDE LOCK VAR.name: AUTOPILOT ALTITUDE LOCK VAR
AUTOPILOT ALTITUDE LOCK VAR.description: Set or get the slot index which the altitude hold mode will track when captured. See alt_mode_slot_index for more information.

AUTOPILOT ALTITUDE MANUALLY TUNABLE.name: AUTOPILOT ALTITUDE MANUALLY TUNABLE
AUTOPILOT ALTITUDE MANUALLY TUNABLE.description: Whether or not the autopilot altitude is manually tunable or not.

AUTOPILOT ALTITUDE SLOT INDEX.name: AUTOPILOT ALTITUDE SLOT INDEX
AUTOPILOT ALTITUDE SLOT INDEX.description:
Index of the slot that the autopilot will use for the altitude reference. Note that there are 3 slots (1, 2, 3) that you can set/get normally, however you can also target slot index 0. Writing to slot 0 will overwrite all other slots with the slot 0 value, and by default the autopilot will follow slot 0 if you have not selected any slot index.
          See alt_mode_slot_index for more information.

AUTOPILOT APPROACH ACTIVE.name: AUTOPILOT APPROACH ACTIVE
AUTOPILOT APPROACH ACTIVE.description: When true, the autopilot is currently flying the approach Flight Plan (the last legs).

AUTOPILOT APPROACH ARM.name: AUTOPILOT APPROACH ARM
AUTOPILOT APPROACH ARM.description: Returns true when the autopilot is active on the approach, once it reaches the adequate condition (in most cases, once it reaches the second-last waypoint of the flightplan).

AUTOPILOT APPROACH CAPTURED.name: AUTOPILOT APPROACH CAPTURED
AUTOPILOT APPROACH CAPTURED.description: Returns true when the lateral NAV mode is engaged and the angular deviation with the current tuned navigation frequency is less than 5°.

AUTOPILOT APPROACH HOLD.name: AUTOPILOT APPROACH HOLD
AUTOPILOT APPROACH HOLD.description: Returns whether pproach mode is active (1, TRUE) or not (0, FALSE).

AUTOPILOT APPROACH IS LOCALIZER.name: AUTOPILOT APPROACH IS LOCALIZER
AUTOPILOT APPROACH IS LOCALIZER.description: Returns true if the current approach is using a localizer.

AUTOPILOT AVIONICS MANAGED.name: AUTOPILOT AVIONICS MANAGED
AUTOPILOT AVIONICS MANAGED.description: Returns whether the autopilot has active managed avionics (1, TRUE) or not (0, FALSE).

AUTOPILOT BACKCOURSE HOLD.name: AUTOPILOT BACKCOURSE HOLD
AUTOPILOT BACKCOURSE HOLD.description: Returns whether the autopilot back course mode is active (1, TRUE) or not (0, FALSE).

AUTOPILOT BANK HOLD.name: AUTOPILOT BANK HOLD
AUTOPILOT BANK HOLD.description: Returns whether the autopilot bank hold mode is active (1, TRUE) or not (0, FALSE).

AUTOPILOT BANK HOLD REF.name: AUTOPILOT BANK HOLD REF
AUTOPILOT BANK HOLD REF.description:
The current bank-hold bank reference.
          Note that if you set this, the next frame the value will be overwritten by the engine, so you may need to write to this every game frame to ensure it maintains the required value.

AUTOPILOT CRUISE SPEED HOLD.name: AUTOPILOT CRUISE SPEED HOLD
AUTOPILOT CRUISE SPEED HOLD.description: Currently not used within the simulation.

AUTOPILOT DEFAULT PITCH MODE.name: AUTOPILOT DEFAULT PITCH MODE
AUTOPILOT DEFAULT PITCH MODE.description: The current default pitch mode of the autopilot as configured in the plane configuration with the parameter default_pitch_mode.
AUTOPILOT DEFAULT PITCH MODE.units:
Enum:
          
            0 = None
            1 = Pitch
            2 = Altitude Hold
            3 = Vertical Speed

AUTOPILOT DEFAULT ROLL MODE.name: AUTOPILOT DEFAULT ROLL MODE
AUTOPILOT DEFAULT ROLL MODE.description: The current default roll mode of the autopilot as configured in the plane configuration with the parameter default_bank_mode.
AUTOPILOT DEFAULT ROLL MODE.units:
Enum:
          
            0 = None
            1 = Wing Leveler
            2 = Heading
            3 = Roll Hold

AUTOPILOT DISENGAGED.name: AUTOPILOT DISENGAGED
AUTOPILOT DISENGAGED.description: Returns whether the autopilot has been disengaged (1, TRUE) or not (0, FALSE).

AUTOPILOT FLIGHT LEVEL CHANGE.name: AUTOPILOT FLIGHT LEVEL CHANGE
AUTOPILOT FLIGHT LEVEL CHANGE.description: Boolean, toggles the autopilot Flight Level Change mode

AUTOPILOT GLIDESLOPE ACTIVE.name: AUTOPILOT GLIDESLOPE ACTIVE
AUTOPILOT GLIDESLOPE ACTIVE.description: When true, the autopilot is receiving a signal from the runway beacon and is following the slope to reach the ground.

AUTOPILOT GLIDESLOPE ARM.name: AUTOPILOT GLIDESLOPE ARM
AUTOPILOT GLIDESLOPE ARM.description: Returns true when the autopilot is active on the glide slope.

AUTOPILOT GLIDESLOPE HOLD.name: AUTOPILOT GLIDESLOPE HOLD
AUTOPILOT GLIDESLOPE HOLD.description: Returns whether the autopilot glidslope hold is active (1, TRUE) or not (0, FALSE).

AUTOPILOT HEADING LOCK.name: AUTOPILOT HEADING LOCK
AUTOPILOT HEADING LOCK.description: Returns whether the autopilot heading lock is enabled (1, TRUE) or not (0, FALSE).

AUTOPILOT HEADING LOCK DIR.name: AUTOPILOT HEADING LOCK DIR
AUTOPILOT HEADING LOCK DIR.description: Specifies / Returns the locked in heading for the autopilot.

AUTOPILOT HEADING MANUALLY TUNABLE.name: AUTOPILOT HEADING MANUALLY TUNABLE
AUTOPILOT HEADING MANUALLY TUNABLE.description: Whether or not the autopilot heading is manually tunable or not.

AUTOPILOT HEADING SLOT INDEX.name: AUTOPILOT HEADING SLOT INDEX
AUTOPILOT HEADING SLOT INDEX.description: Index of the slot that the autopilot will use for the heading reference. Note that there are 3 slots (1, 2, 3) that you can set/get normally, however you can also target slot index 0. Writing to slot 0 will overwrite all other slots with the slot 0 value, and by default the autopilot will follow slot 0 if you have not selected any slot index.

AUTOPILOT MACH HOLD VAR.name: AUTOPILOT MACH HOLD VAR
AUTOPILOT MACH HOLD VAR.description: Returns the target holding mach airspeed for the autopilot.

AUTOPILOT MANAGED INDEX.name: AUTOPILOT MANAGED INDEX
AUTOPILOT MANAGED INDEX.description: Currently not used within the simulation.

AUTOPILOT MANAGED SPEED IN MACH.name: AUTOPILOT MANAGED SPEED IN MACH
AUTOPILOT MANAGED SPEED IN MACH.description: Returns whether the managed speed is in mach (1, TRUE) or not (0, FALSE).

AUTOPILOT MANAGED THROTTLE ACTIVE.name: AUTOPILOT MANAGED THROTTLE ACTIVE
AUTOPILOT MANAGED THROTTLE ACTIVE.description: Returns whether the autopilot managed throttle is active (1, TRUE) or not (0, FALSE).

AUTOPILOT MAX BANK.name: AUTOPILOT MAX BANK
AUTOPILOT MAX BANK.description: Returns the maximum banking angle for the autopilot, in radians.

AUTOPILOT MAX BANK ID.name: AUTOPILOT MAX BANK ID
AUTOPILOT MAX BANK ID.description: Returns the index of the current maximum bank setting of the autopilot.

AUTOPILOT MAX SPEED HOLD.name: AUTOPILOT MAX SPEED HOLD
AUTOPILOT MAX SPEED HOLD.description: Currently not used within the simulation.

AUTOPILOT NAV1 LOCK.name: AUTOPILOT NAV1 LOCK
AUTOPILOT NAV1 LOCK.description: Returns TRUE (1) if the autopilot Nav1 lock is applied, or 0 (FALSE) otherwise.

AUTOPILOT PITCH HOLD.name: AUTOPILOT PITCH HOLD
AUTOPILOT PITCH HOLD.description: Set to True if the autopilot pitch hold has is engaged.

AUTOPILOT PITCH HOLD REF.name: AUTOPILOT PITCH HOLD REF
AUTOPILOT PITCH HOLD REF.description: Returns the current autotpilot reference pitch.

AUTOPILOT RPM HOLD.name: AUTOPILOT RPM HOLD
AUTOPILOT RPM HOLD.description: True if autopilot rpm hold applied

AUTOPILOT RPM SLOT INDEX.name: AUTOPILOT RPM SLOT INDEX
AUTOPILOT RPM SLOT INDEX.description: Index of the slot that the autopilot will use for the RPM reference. Note that there are 3 slots (1, 2, 3) that you can set/get normally, however you can also target slot index 0. Writing to slot 0 will overwrite all other slots with the slot 0 value, and by default the autopilot will follow slot 0 if you have not selected any slot index.

AUTOPILOT SPEED SETTING.name: AUTOPILOT SPEED SETTING
AUTOPILOT SPEED SETTING.description: Currently not used within the simulation.

AUTOPILOT TAKEOFF POWER ACTIVE.name: AUTOPILOT TAKEOFF POWER ACTIVE
AUTOPILOT TAKEOFF POWER ACTIVE.description: Takeoff / Go Around power mode active

AUTOPILOT THROTTLE ARM.name: AUTOPILOT THROTTLE ARM
AUTOPILOT THROTTLE ARM.description: Returns whether the autopilot auto-throttle is armed (1, TRUE) or not (0, FALSE).

AUTOPILOT THROTTLE MAX THRUST.name: AUTOPILOT THROTTLE MAX THRUST
AUTOPILOT THROTTLE MAX THRUST.description: This can be used to set/get the thrust lever position for autopilot maximum thrust.

AUTOPILOT VERTICAL HOLD.name: AUTOPILOT VERTICAL HOLD
AUTOPILOT VERTICAL HOLD.description: True if autopilot vertical hold applied

AUTOPILOT VS SLOT INDEX.name: AUTOPILOT VS SLOT INDEX
AUTOPILOT VS SLOT INDEX.description: Index of the slot that the autopilot will use for the VS reference. Note that there are 3 slots (1, 2, 3) that you can set/get normally, however you can also target slot index 0. Writing to slot 0 will overwrite all other slots with the slot 0 value, and by default the autopilot will follow slot 0 if you have not selected any slot index.

ASSISTANCE LANDING ENABLED.name: ASSISTANCE LANDING ENABLED
ASSISTANCE LANDING ENABLED.description: Returns whether landing assistance has been enabled or not.

ASSISTANCE TAKEOFF ENABLED.name: ASSISTANCE TAKEOFF ENABLED
ASSISTANCE TAKEOFF ENABLED.description: Returns whether takeoff assistance has been enabled or not.

AI ANTISTALL STATE.name: AI ANTISTALL STATE
AI ANTISTALL STATE.description: The current state of the AI anti-stall system.

AI AUTOTRIM ACTIVE.name: AI AUTOTRIM ACTIVE
AI AUTOTRIM ACTIVE.description: Returns whether the AI auto-trim system is enabled or not.

AI AUTOTRIM ACTIVE AGAINST PLAYER.name: AI AUTOTRIM ACTIVE AGAINST PLAYER
AI AUTOTRIM ACTIVE AGAINST PLAYER.description: Returns whether the AI auto-trim system is enabled or not for AI controlled aircraft.

AI CONTROLS.name: AI CONTROLS
AI CONTROLS.description: Returns whether the AI control system is enabled or not.

AI CURSOR MODE ACTIVE.name: AI CURSOR MODE ACTIVE
AI CURSOR MODE ACTIVE.description: Returns whether the AI cursor mode is active or not.

DELEGATE CONTROLS TO AI.name: DELEGATE CONTROLS TO AI
DELEGATE CONTROLS TO AI.description: Returns whether the AI control system is active or not.

FLY ASSISTANT CANCEL DESTINATION.name: FLY ASSISTANT CANCEL DESTINATION
FLY ASSISTANT CANCEL DESTINATION.description: When set with any value this will cancel the current flight assistant destination.

FLY ASSISTANT CANCEL DESTINATION DISPLAY.name: FLY ASSISTANT CANCEL DESTINATION DISPLAY
FLY ASSISTANT CANCEL DESTINATION DISPLAY.description: When set with any value this will cancel the display of the current flight assistant destination.

FLY ASSISTANT COM AI LOCKED.name: FLY ASSISTANT COM AI LOCKED
FLY ASSISTANT COM AI LOCKED.description: Returns true when the copilot AI control is active and therefore COM AI is locked on active too.

FLY ASSISTANT HAVE DESTINATION.name: FLY ASSISTANT HAVE DESTINATION
FLY ASSISTANT HAVE DESTINATION.description: Returns true when a destination has been set in the flight assistant.

FLY ASSISTANT LANDING SPEED.name: FLY ASSISTANT LANDING SPEED
FLY ASSISTANT LANDING SPEED.description: Returns the POH range or an estimated value for this speed.

FLY ASSISTANT LANDING SPEED DISPLAY MODE.name: FLY ASSISTANT LANDING SPEED DISPLAY MODE
FLY ASSISTANT LANDING SPEED DISPLAY MODE.description: Returns the display mode of the speed, CSS side (only STALL SPEED is working and will turn red when below).
FLY ASSISTANT LANDING SPEED DISPLAY MODE.name_std: FLY ASSISTANT LANDING SPEED DISPLAY MODE

FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST COUNT.name: FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST COUNT
FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST COUNT.description: Number of elements in this category

FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST METADATA.name: FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST METADATA
FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST METADATA.description: Currently not used within the simulation.

FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST NAME.name: FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST NAME
FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST NAME.description: Returns the name of the element at the specified index.

FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST SELECTED.name: FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST SELECTED
FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST SELECTED.description: Returns the index of the currently selected element.

FLY ASSISTANT RIBBONS ACTIVE.name: FLY ASSISTANT RIBBONS ACTIVE
FLY ASSISTANT RIBBONS ACTIVE.description: Returns true when both ribbon assistances are active (taxi and landing), and can also be used to set them.

FLY ASSISTANT SET AS DESTINATION.name: FLY ASSISTANT SET AS DESTINATION
FLY ASSISTANT SET AS DESTINATION.description: When set with any value, it will set the selected element as the current destination.

FLY ASSISTANT STALL SPEED.name: FLY ASSISTANT STALL SPEED
FLY ASSISTANT STALL SPEED.description: Returns the flight assistant stall speed.

FLY ASSISTANT STALL SPEED DISPLAY MODE.name: FLY ASSISTANT STALL SPEED DISPLAY MODE
FLY ASSISTANT STALL SPEED DISPLAY MODE.description: Returns the flight assistant stall speed display mode.
FLY ASSISTANT STALL SPEED DISPLAY MODE.name_std: FLY ASSISTANT STALL SPEED DISPLAY MODE

FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED.name: FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED
FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED.description: Returns the flight assistant takeoff speed.

FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED DISPLAY MODE.name: FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED DISPLAY MODE
FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED DISPLAY MODE.description: Returns the flight assistant takeoff speed display mode.
FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED DISPLAY MODE.name_std: FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED DISPLAY MODE

FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED ESTIMATED.name: FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED ESTIMATED
FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED ESTIMATED.description: Can be set to override the estimated takeoff speed

ANTISKID BRAKES ACTIVE.name: ANTISKID BRAKES ACTIVE
ANTISKID BRAKES ACTIVE.description: True if antiskid brakes active. This can be set using the AntiSkidActive parameter.

AUTOBRAKES ACTIVE.name: AUTOBRAKES ACTIVE
AUTOBRAKES ACTIVE.description: Whether or not the AutoBrakes are currently active.

BRAKE LEFT POSITION.name: BRAKE LEFT POSITION
BRAKE LEFT POSITION.description:
Percent left brake.
          Note that this SimVar no longer sets the right brake percent and simply triggers a brake pressure increase regardless of the value passed.

BRAKE LEFT POSITION EX1.name: BRAKE LEFT POSITION EX1
BRAKE LEFT POSITION EX1.description: Triggers a brake pressure increase on the left brake regardless of the value passed.

BRAKE PARKING POSITION.name: BRAKE PARKING POSITION
BRAKE PARKING POSITION.description: Gets the parking brake position - either on (true) or off (false).

BRAKE RIGHT POSITION EX1.name: BRAKE RIGHT POSITION EX1
BRAKE RIGHT POSITION EX1.description: Triggers a brake pressure increase on the right brake regardless of the value passed.

REJECTED TAKEOFF BRAKES ACTIVE.name: REJECTED TAKEOFF BRAKES ACTIVE
REJECTED TAKEOFF BRAKES ACTIVE.description: Whether or not the rejected takeoff brakes are currently active.

TOE BRAKES AVAILABLE.name: TOE BRAKES AVAILABLE
TOE BRAKES AVAILABLE.description: True if toe brakes are available

CONTACT POINT COMPRESSION.name: CONTACT POINT COMPRESSION:index
CONTACT POINT COMPRESSION.description: The percentage value representing the amount the contact point is compressed. Index is from 0-19.

CONTACT POINT IS ON GROUND.name: CONTACT POINT IS ON GROUND:index
CONTACT POINT IS ON GROUND.description: Returns true if the indexed contact point is on the ground, or will return false otherwise. Index is from 0 - 19.

CONTACT POINT IS SKIDDING.name: CONTACT POINT IS SKIDDING:index
CONTACT POINT IS SKIDDING.description: Returns true if the indexed contact point is skidding, or will return false otherwise. Index is from 0 - 19.

CONTACT POINT POSITION.name: CONTACT POINT POSITION:index
CONTACT POINT POSITION.description: The currently extended position of the (retractable) contact point, expressed as a percentage. Index is from 0 - 19.

CONTACT POINT SKIDDING FACTOR.name: CONTACT POINT SKIDDING FACTOR:index
CONTACT POINT SKIDDING FACTOR.description: The skidding factor associated with the indexed contact point, from 0 to 1. Index is from 0 - 19.

CONTACT POINT WATER DEPTH.name: CONTACT POINT WATER DEPTH:index
CONTACT POINT WATER DEPTH.description: This returns the depth of the water for the indexed contact point. Index is from 0 - 19.

AUX WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.name: AUX WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE
AUX WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.description: Aux wheel rotation angle (rotation around the axis for the wheel).

AUX WHEEL RPM.name: AUX WHEEL RPM
AUX WHEEL RPM.description: Rpm of fourth set of gear wheels.

GEAR AUX STEER ANGLE.name: GEAR AUX STEER ANGLE
GEAR AUX STEER ANGLE.description: Aux wheel angle, negative to the left, positive to the right. The aux wheel is the fourth set of landing gear, sometimes used on helicopters.

GEAR AUX STEER ANGLE PCT.name: GEAR AUX STEER ANGLE PCT
GEAR AUX STEER ANGLE PCT.description: Aux steer angle as a percentage.

GEAR CENTER STEER ANGLE PCT.name: GEAR CENTER STEER ANGLE PCT
GEAR CENTER STEER ANGLE PCT.description: Center steer angle as a percentage.

GEAR DAMAGE BY SPEED.name: GEAR DAMAGE BY SPEED
GEAR DAMAGE BY SPEED.description: True if gear has been damaged by excessive speed.

GEAR EMERGENCY HANDLE POSITION.name: GEAR EMERGENCY HANDLE POSITION
GEAR EMERGENCY HANDLE POSITION.description: True if gear emergency handle applied.

GEAR HANDLE POSITION.name: GEAR HANDLE POSITION
GEAR HANDLE POSITION.description: The gear handle position, where 0 means the handle is retracted and 1 is the handle fully applied.

GEAR IS ON GROUND.name: GEAR IS ON GROUND:index
GEAR IS ON GROUND.description: True if the gear is on the ground.

GEAR IS SKIDDING.name: GEAR IS SKIDDING:index
GEAR IS SKIDDING.description: True if the gear is skidding.

GEAR LEFT STEER ANGLE PCT.name: GEAR LEFT STEER ANGLE PCT
GEAR LEFT STEER ANGLE PCT.description: Left steer angle as a percentage.

GEAR RIGHT STEER ANGLE PCT.name: GEAR RIGHT STEER ANGLE PCT
GEAR RIGHT STEER ANGLE PCT.description: Right steer angle as a percentage.

GEAR SPEED EXCEEDED.name: GEAR SPEED EXCEEDED
GEAR SPEED EXCEEDED.description: True if safe speed limit for gear exceeded.

GEAR STEER ANGLE PCT.name: GEAR STEER ANGLE PCT:index
GEAR STEER ANGLE PCT.description:
Alternative method of getting steer angle as a percentage. Index is one of the following:
          
            0 = center
            1 = left
            2 = right
            3 = aux

GEAR TAIL POSITION.name: GEAR TAIL POSITION
GEAR TAIL POSITION.description:
Percent tail gear extended.
          NOTE: This is a deprecated legacy SimVar and should not be used, as it will always return 0.

GEAR WARNING.name: GEAR WARNING:index
GEAR WARNING.description:
Gear warnings. Index can be one of the following:
          
            0 = unknown
            1 = normal
            2 = amphib
GEAR WARNING.units:
Enum:
          
            0 = None
            1 = Gear Up
            2 = Amphibious Gear Up
            3 = Amphibious Gear Down
            4 = On Ground Handle Up

GEAR WATER DEPTH.name: GEAR WATER DEPTH
GEAR WATER DEPTH.description: The depth of the gear in the water.

IS GEAR FLOATS.name: IS GEAR FLOATS
IS GEAR FLOATS.description: True if landing gear are floats

IS GEAR RETRACTABLE.name: IS GEAR RETRACTABLE
IS GEAR RETRACTABLE.description: True if gear can be retracted

IS GEAR SKIDS.name: IS GEAR SKIDS
IS GEAR SKIDS.description: True if landing gear is skids

IS GEAR SKIS.name: IS GEAR SKIS
IS GEAR SKIS.description: True if landing gear is skis

IS GEAR WHEELS.name: IS GEAR WHEELS
IS GEAR WHEELS.description: True if landing gear is wheels

LEFT WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.name: LEFT WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE
LEFT WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.description: Left wheel rotation angle (rotation around the axis for the wheel).

NOSEWHEEL LOCK ON.name: NOSEWHEEL LOCK ON
NOSEWHEEL LOCK ON.description: True if the nosewheel lock is engaged. This can be set using the NosewheelLock parameter.

NOSEWHEEL MAX STEERING ANGLE.name: NOSEWHEEL MAX STEERING ANGLE
NOSEWHEEL MAX STEERING ANGLE.description: Can be used to get or set the maximum permitted steering angle for the nose wheel of the aircraft.

RETRACT FLOAT SWITCH.name: RETRACT FLOAT SWITCH
RETRACT FLOAT SWITCH.description: True if retract float switch on

RETRACT LEFT FLOAT EXTENDED.name: RETRACT LEFT FLOAT EXTENDED
RETRACT LEFT FLOAT EXTENDED.units:
Percent
          (0 is fully retracted, 100 is fully extended)

RETRACT RIGHT FLOAT EXTENDED.name: RETRACT RIGHT FLOAT EXTENDED
RETRACT RIGHT FLOAT EXTENDED.units:
Percent
          (0 is fully retracted, 100 is fully extended)

RIGHT WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.name: RIGHT WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE
RIGHT WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.description: Right wheel rotation angle (rotation around the axis for the wheel).

TAILWHEEL LOCK ON.name: TAILWHEEL LOCK ON
TAILWHEEL LOCK ON.description: True if tailwheel lock applied. This can be set using the TailwheelLock parameter.

WATER LEFT RUDDER STEER ANGLE.name: WATER LEFT RUDDER STEER ANGLE
WATER LEFT RUDDER STEER ANGLE.description: Water left rudder angle, negative to the left, positive to the right.

WATER LEFT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT.name: WATER LEFT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT
WATER LEFT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT.description: Water left rudder angle as a percentage.
WATER LEFT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT.name_std: WATER LEFT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT

WATER RIGHT RUDDER STEER ANGLE.name: WATER RIGHT RUDDER STEER ANGLE
WATER RIGHT RUDDER STEER ANGLE.description: Water right rudder angle, negative to the left, positive to the right.

WATER RIGHT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT.name: WATER RIGHT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT
WATER RIGHT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT.description: Water right rudder as a percentage.
WATER RIGHT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT.name_std: WATER RIGHT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT

WATER RUDDER HANDLE POSITION.name: WATER RUDDER HANDLE POSITION
WATER RUDDER HANDLE POSITION.description: Position of the water rudder handle (0 handle retracted, 1 rudder handle applied).

WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.name: WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE:index
WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.description:
Wheel rotation angle (rotation around the axis for the wheel). Index is one of the following:
          
            0 = center
            1 = left
            2 = right
            3 = aux

WHEEL RPM.name: WHEEL RPM:index
WHEEL RPM.description:
Wheel rpm. Index is one of the following:
          
            0 = center
            1 = left
            2 = right
            3 = aux

AILERON TRIM DISABLED.name: AILERON TRIM DISABLED
AILERON TRIM DISABLED.description: Whether or not the Aileron Trim has been disabled.

ELEVATOR TRIM DISABLED.name: ELEVATOR TRIM DISABLED
ELEVATOR TRIM DISABLED.description: Whether or not the Elevator Trim has been disabled.

ELEVATOR TRIM DOWN LIMIT.name: ELEVATOR TRIM DOWN LIMIT
ELEVATOR TRIM DOWN LIMIT.description: Returns the maximum elevator trim value. This corresponds to the elevator_trim_down_limit in the Flight Model Config file.

ELEVATOR TRIM UP LIMIT.name: ELEVATOR TRIM UP LIMIT
ELEVATOR TRIM UP LIMIT.description: Returns the maximum elevator trim value. This corresponds to the elevator_trim_up_limit in the Flight Model Config file.

FLAP DAMAGE BY SPEED.name: FLAP DAMAGE BY SPEED
FLAP DAMAGE BY SPEED.description: True if flaps are damaged by excessive speed.

FLAP POSITION SET.name: FLAP POSITION SET
FLAP POSITION SET.description: Set the position of the flaps control.

FLAP SPEED EXCEEDED.name: FLAP SPEED EXCEEDED
FLAP SPEED EXCEEDED.description: True if safe speed limit for flaps exceeded.

FLAPS EFFECTIVE HANDLE INDEX.name: FLAPS EFFECTIVE HANDLE INDEX:index
FLAPS EFFECTIVE HANDLE INDEX.description: This returns the effective flaps handle index, after some of the conditions have potentially forced the state to change.

LEADING EDGE FLAPS LEFT ANGLE.name: LEADING EDGE FLAPS LEFT ANGLE
LEADING EDGE FLAPS LEFT ANGLE.description: Angle left leading edge flap extended. Use LEADING_EDGE_FLAPS_LEFT_PERCENT to set a value.

LEADING EDGE FLAPS LEFT INDEX.name: LEADING EDGE FLAPS LEFT INDEX
LEADING EDGE FLAPS LEFT INDEX.description: Index of left leading edge flap position.

LEADING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT ANGLE.name: LEADING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT ANGLE
LEADING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT ANGLE.description: Angle right leading edge flap extended. Use LEADING_EDGE_FLAPS_RIGHT_PERCENT to set a value.

LEADING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT INDEX.name: LEADING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT INDEX
LEADING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT INDEX.description: Index of right leading edge flap position.

TRAILING EDGE FLAPS LEFT ANGLE.name: TRAILING EDGE FLAPS LEFT ANGLE
TRAILING EDGE FLAPS LEFT ANGLE.description: Angle left trailing edge flap extended. Use TRAILING_EDGE_FLAPS_LEFT_PERCENT to set a value.

TRAILING EDGE FLAPS LEFT INDEX.name: TRAILING EDGE FLAPS LEFT INDEX
TRAILING EDGE FLAPS LEFT INDEX.description: Index of left trailing edge flap position.

TRAILING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT ANGLE.name: TRAILING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT ANGLE
TRAILING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT ANGLE.description: Angle right trailing edge flap extended. Use TRAILING_EDGE_FLAPS_RIGHT_PERCENT to set a value.

TRAILING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT INDEX.name: TRAILING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT INDEX
TRAILING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT INDEX.description: Index of right trailing edge flap position.

FLY BY WIRE ALPHA PROTECTION.name: FLY BY WIRE ALPHA PROTECTION
FLY BY WIRE ALPHA PROTECTION.description: Returns true if the fly-by-wire alpha protection is enabled or false otherwise.

FLY BY WIRE ELAC FAILED.name: FLY BY WIRE ELAC FAILED
FLY BY WIRE ELAC FAILED.description: True if the Elevators and Ailerons computer has failed.

FLY BY WIRE ELAC SWITCH.name: FLY BY WIRE ELAC SWITCH
FLY BY WIRE ELAC SWITCH.description: True if the fly by wire Elevators and Ailerons computer is on.

FLY BY WIRE FAC FAILED.name: FLY BY WIRE FAC FAILED
FLY BY WIRE FAC FAILED.description: True if the Flight Augmentation computer has failed.

FLY BY WIRE FAC SWITCH.name: FLY BY WIRE FAC SWITCH
FLY BY WIRE FAC SWITCH.description: True if the fly by wire Flight Augmentation computer is on.

FLY BY WIRE SEC FAILED.name: FLY BY WIRE SEC FAILED
FLY BY WIRE SEC FAILED.description: True if the Spoilers and Elevators computer has failed.

FLY BY WIRE SEC SWITCH.name: FLY BY WIRE SEC SWITCH
FLY BY WIRE SEC SWITCH.description: True if the fly by wire Spoilers and Elevators computer is on.

FOLDING WING HANDLE POSITION.name: FOLDING WING HANDLE POSITION
FOLDING WING HANDLE POSITION.description: True if the folding wing handle is engaged.

FOLDING WING LEFT PERCENT.name: FOLDING WING LEFT PERCENT
FOLDING WING LEFT PERCENT.description: Left folding wing position, 1.0 is fully folded.

FOLDING WING RIGHT PERCENT.name: FOLDING WING RIGHT PERCENT
FOLDING WING RIGHT PERCENT.description: Right folding wing position, 1.0 is fully folded.

RUDDER PEDAL POSITION.name: RUDDER PEDAL POSITION
RUDDER PEDAL POSITION.units:
Position (-16K to 0)
          -16K = left pedal pushed full in

RUDDER TRIM DISABLED.name: RUDDER TRIM DISABLED
RUDDER TRIM DISABLED.description: Whether or not the Rudder Trim has been disabled.

RUDDER TRIM PCT.name: RUDDER TRIM PCT
RUDDER TRIM PCT.description: The trim position of the rudder. Zero is no trim.

SPOILERS ARMED.name: SPOILERS ARMED
SPOILERS ARMED.description: Checks if autospoilers are armed (true) or not (false).

SPOILERS HANDLE POSITION.name: SPOILERS HANDLE POSITION
SPOILERS HANDLE POSITION.units:
Percent Over 100
          or
          Position
          (16K = down, 0 = up)

BLAST SHIELD POSITION.name: BLAST SHIELD POSITION:index
BLAST SHIELD POSITION.description: Indexed from 1, 100 is fully deployed, 0 flat on deck

CABLE CAUGHT BY TAILHOOK.name: CABLE CAUGHT BY TAILHOOK:index
CABLE CAUGHT BY TAILHOOK.description: A number 1 through 4 for the cable number caught by the tailhook. Cable 1 is the one closest to the stern of the carrier. A value of 0 indicates no cable was caught.

CATAPULT STROKE POSITION.name: CATAPULT STROKE POSITION:index
CATAPULT STROKE POSITION.description: Catapults are indexed from 1. This value will be 0 before the catapult fires, and then up to 100 as the aircraft is propelled down the catapult. The aircraft may takeoff before the value reaches 100 (depending on the aircraft weight, power applied, and other factors), in which case this value will not be further updated. This value could be used to drive a bogie animation.

HOLDBACK BAR INSTALLED.name: HOLDBACK BAR INSTALLED
HOLDBACK BAR INSTALLED.description: Holdback bars allow build up of thrust before takeoff from a catapult, and are installed by the deck crew of an aircraft carrier.

LAUNCHBAR HELD EXTENDED.name: LAUNCHBAR HELD EXTENDED
LAUNCHBAR HELD EXTENDED.description: This will be True if the launchbar is fully extended, and can be used, for example, to change the color of an instrument light.

LAUNCHBAR POSITION.name: LAUNCHBAR POSITION
LAUNCHBAR POSITION.description: Installed on aircraft before takeoff from a carrier catapult. Note that gear cannot retract with this extended. 100 = fully extended.

LAUNCHBAR SWITCH.name: LAUNCHBAR SWITCH
LAUNCHBAR SWITCH.description: If this is set to True the launch bar switch has been engaged.

NUMBER OF CATAPULTS.name: NUMBER OF CATAPULTS
NUMBER OF CATAPULTS.description: Maximum of 4. A model can contain more than 4 catapults, but only the first four will be read and recognized by the simulation.

CONCORDE NOSE ANGLE.name: CONCORDE NOSE ANGLE
CONCORDE NOSE ANGLE.description: The nose angle, where 0 is fully up.

CONCORDE VISOR NOSE HANDLE.name: CONCORDE VISOR NOSE HANDLE
CONCORDE VISOR NOSE HANDLE.units:
Enum:
          
            0:[index] visor up, nose down
            1:[index] visor down, nose up
            2:[index] visor down, nose 5 degrees
            3:[index] visor down, nose 12.5 degrees

CONCORDE VISOR POSITION PERCENT.name: CONCORDE VISOR POSITION PERCENT
CONCORDE VISOR POSITION PERCENT.description: The visor position expressed as a percentage where 0.0 = up and 1.0 = extended/down.

BUS LOOKUP INDEX.name: BUS LOOKUP INDEX
BUS LOOKUP INDEX.description:
This is a settable simvar meaning that it can both be read and set. Some of the simvars in this list are using this to lookup a value using two arguments (one argument in addition to the component index). For example to check the state of the connection between a "circuit.45" and the "bus.2" it would be written as follows:
          2 (>A:BUS LOOKUP INDEX, Number) (A:CIRCUIT CONNECTION ON:45, Bool)
          It should be notes that when BUS_LOOKUP_INDEX is not set (ie: it is 0) then TRUE will be returned if any of your bus connections are on.

BUS BREAKER PULLED.name: BUS BREAKER PULLED
BUS BREAKER PULLED.description: This will be true if the bus breaker is pulled. Requires a BUS_LOOKUP_INDEX and a bus index.

BUS CONNECTION ON.name: BUS CONNECTION ON
BUS CONNECTION ON.description: This will be true if the bus is connected. Requires a BUS_LOOKUP_INDEX and a bus index.

ELECTRICAL GENALT LOAD.name: ELECTRICAL GENALT LOAD
ELECTRICAL GENALT LOAD.description: This returns the percentage of the load output that is being consumed. This requires an alternator index when referencing.

ELECTRICAL GENALT BUS AMPS.name: ELECTRICAL GENALT BUS AMPS
ELECTRICAL GENALT BUS AMPS.description: The load handled by the alternator. This requires an alternator index when referencing.

ELECTRICAL GENALT BUS VOLTAGE.name: ELECTRICAL GENALT BUS VOLTAGE
ELECTRICAL GENALT BUS VOLTAGE.description: General alternator voltage. This requires an alternator index when referencing.

ELECTRICAL MAIN BUS VOLTAGE.name: ELECTRICAL MAIN BUS VOLTAGE
ELECTRICAL MAIN BUS VOLTAGE.description: The main bus voltage. Use a bus index when referencing.

ELECTRICAL OLD CHARGING AMPS.name: ELECTRICAL OLD CHARGING AMPS
ELECTRICAL OLD CHARGING AMPS.description:
Deprecated, do not use!
          Use ELECTRICAL BATTERY LOAD.

NEW ELECTRICAL SYSTEM.name: NEW ELECTRICAL SYSTEM
NEW ELECTRICAL SYSTEM.description: Is the aircraft using the new Electrical System or the legacy FSX one.

ALTERNATOR BREAKER PULLED.name: ALTERNATOR BREAKER PULLED
ALTERNATOR BREAKER PULLED.description: This will be true if the alternator breaker is pulled. Requires a BUS_LOOKUP_INDEX and an alternator index.

ALTERNATOR CONNECTION ON.name: ALTERNATOR CONNECTION ON
ALTERNATOR CONNECTION ON.description: This will be true if the alternator is connected. Requires a BUS_LOOKUP_INDEX and an alternator index.

GENERAL ENG MASTER ALTERNATOR.name: GENERAL ENG MASTER ALTERNATOR
GENERAL ENG MASTER ALTERNATOR.description: The alternator switch for a specific engine. Requires an engine index (1 - 4) when used.

APU BLEED PRESSURE RECEIVED BY ENGINE.name: APU BLEED PRESSURE RECEIVED BY ENGINE
APU BLEED PRESSURE RECEIVED BY ENGINE.description: Bleed air pressure received by the engine from the APU.
APU BLEED PRESSURE RECEIVED BY ENGINE.name_std: APU BLEED PRESSURE RECEIVED BY ENGINE

APU GENERATOR ACTIVE.name: APU GENERATOR ACTIVE:index
APU GENERATOR ACTIVE.description: Set or get whether an APU is active (true) or not (false). Takes an index to be able to have multiple generators on a single APU.

APU GENERATOR SWITCH.name: APU GENERATOR SWITCH:index
APU GENERATOR SWITCH.description: Enables or disables the APU for an engine. Takes an index to be able to have multiple generators on a single APU

APU ON FIRE DETECTED.name: APU ON FIRE DETECTED
APU ON FIRE DETECTED.description: Will return true if the APU is on fire, or false otherwise.

APU PCT RPM.name: APU PCT RPM
APU PCT RPM.description: Auxiliary power unit RPM, as a percentage

APU PCT STARTER.name: APU PCT STARTER
APU PCT STARTER.description: Auxiliary power unit starter, as a percentage

APU SWITCH.name: APU SWITCH
APU SWITCH.description: Boolean, whether or not the APU is switched on.

APU VOLTS.name: APU VOLTS:index
APU VOLTS.description: The volts from the APU to the selected engine. Takes an index to be able to have multiple generators on a single APU.

BLEED AIR APU.name: BLEED AIR APU
BLEED AIR APU.description: Boolean, returns whether or not the APU attempts to provide Bleed Air.

BATTERY BREAKER PULLED.name: BATTERY BREAKER PULLED
BATTERY BREAKER PULLED.description: This will be true if the battery breaker is pulled. Requires a BUS LOOKUP INDEX and a battery index.

BATTERY CONNECTION ON.name: BATTERY CONNECTION ON
BATTERY CONNECTION ON.description: This will be true if the battery is connected. Requires a BUS_LOOKUP_INDEX and a battery index.

ELECTRICAL BATTERY ESTIMATED CAPACITY PC.name: ELECTRICAL BATTERY ESTIMATED CAPACITY PCT
ELECTRICAL BATTERY ESTIMATED CAPACITY PC.description: Battery capacity over max capacity, 100 is full.

ELECTRICAL BATTERY LOAD.name: ELECTRICAL BATTERY LOAD
ELECTRICAL BATTERY LOAD.description: The load handled by the battery (negative values mean the battery is receiving current). Use a battery index when referencing.

ELECTRICAL BATTERY VOLTAGE.name: ELECTRICAL BATTERY VOLTAGE
ELECTRICAL BATTERY VOLTAGE.description: The battery voltage. Use a battery index when referencing.

ELECTRICAL HOT BATTERY BUS AMPS.name: ELECTRICAL HOT BATTERY BUS AMPS
ELECTRICAL HOT BATTERY BUS AMPS.description: Current available when battery switch is turned off

ELECTRICAL HOT BATTERY BUS VOLTAGE.name: ELECTRICAL HOT BATTERY BUS VOLTAGE
ELECTRICAL HOT BATTERY BUS VOLTAGE.description: Voltage available when battery switch is turned off

ELECTRICAL MASTER BATTERY.name: ELECTRICAL MASTER BATTERY
ELECTRICAL MASTER BATTERY.description: The battery switch position, true if the switch is ON. Use a battery index when referencing.

BREAKER ADF.name: BREAKER ADF
BREAKER ADF.description:
All these SimVars can be used to get or set the breaker state for the electrical system (either true or false).
          If the breaker is popped (set to false), then the associated circuit will not receive electricity.

CIRCUIT AUTOPILOT ON.name: CIRCUIT AUTOPILOT ON
CIRCUIT AUTOPILOT ON.description: Is electrical power available to this circuit

CIRCUIT AUTO BRAKES ON.name: CIRCUIT AUTO BRAKES ON
CIRCUIT AUTO BRAKES ON.description: Is electrical power available to this circuit

CIRCUIT AUTO FEATHER ON.name: CIRCUIT AUTO FEATHER ON
CIRCUIT AUTO FEATHER ON.description: Is electrical power available to this circuit. Please see the Note On Autofeathering for more information.

CIRCUIT AVIONICS ON.name: CIRCUIT AVIONICS ON
CIRCUIT AVIONICS ON.description: Is electrical power available to this circuit

CIRCUIT BREAKER PULLED.name: CIRCUIT BREAKER PULLED
CIRCUIT BREAKER PULLED.description: This will be true if the circuit breaker is pulled. Requires a BUS_LOOKUP_INDEX and a circuit index.

CIRCUIT CONNECTION ON.name: CIRCUIT CONNECTION ON
CIRCUIT CONNECTION ON.description: This will be true if the circuit is connected. Requires a BUS_LOOKUP_INDEX and a circuit index.

CIRCUIT FLAP MOTOR ON.name: CIRCUIT FLAP MOTOR ON
CIRCUIT FLAP MOTOR ON.description: Is electrical power available to the flap motor circuit

CIRCUIT GEAR MOTOR ON.name: CIRCUIT GEAR MOTOR ON
CIRCUIT GEAR MOTOR ON.description: Is electrical power available to the gear motor circuit

CIRCUIT GEAR WARNING ON.name: CIRCUIT GEAR WARNING ON
CIRCUIT GEAR WARNING ON.description: Is electrical power available to gear warning circuit

CIRCUIT GENERAL PANEL ON.name: CIRCUIT GENERAL PANEL ON
CIRCUIT GENERAL PANEL ON.description: Is electrical power available to the general panel circuit

CIRCUIT HYDRAULIC PUMP ON.name: CIRCUIT HYDRAULIC PUMP ON
CIRCUIT HYDRAULIC PUMP ON.description: Is electrical power available to the hydraulic pump circuit

CIRCUIT MARKER BEACON ON.name: CIRCUIT MARKER BEACON ON
CIRCUIT MARKER BEACON ON.description: Is electrical power available to the marker beacon circuit

CIRCUIT NAVCOM1 ON.name: CIRCUIT NAVCOM1 ON
CIRCUIT NAVCOM1 ON.description: Whether or not power is available to the NAVCOM1 circuit.

CIRCUIT NAVCOM2 ON.name: CIRCUIT NAVCOM2 ON
CIRCUIT NAVCOM2 ON.description: Whether or not power is available to the NAVCOM2 circuit.

CIRCUIT NAVCOM3 ON.name: CIRCUIT NAVCOM3 ON
CIRCUIT NAVCOM3 ON.description: Whether or not power is available to the NAVCOM3 circuit.

CIRCUIT ON.name: CIRCUIT ON
CIRCUIT ON.description: This will be true if the given circuit is functioning. Use a circuit index when referencing.

CIRCUIT PITOT HEAT ON.name: CIRCUIT PITOT HEAT ON
CIRCUIT PITOT HEAT ON.description: Is electrical power available to the pitot heat circuit

CIRCUIT POWER SETTING.name: CIRCUIT POWER SETTING
CIRCUIT POWER SETTING.description: This returns the percentage of use that the circuit is getting. This requires a circuit index when referencing.

CIRCUIT PROP SYNC ON.name: CIRCUIT PROP SYNC ON
CIRCUIT PROP SYNC ON.description: Is electrical power available to the propeller sync circuit

CIRCUIT STANDBY VACUUM ON.name: CIRCUIT STANDBY VACUUM ON
CIRCUIT STANDBY VACUUM ON.description: Is electrical power available to the vacuum circuit

CIRCUIT SWITCH ON.name: CIRCUIT SWITCH ON
CIRCUIT SWITCH ON.description: The circuit switch position, true if the switch is ON. Use a circuit index when referencing.

EXTERNAL POWER AVAILABLE.name: EXTERNAL POWER AVAILABLE
EXTERNAL POWER AVAILABLE.description: This will be true if the given external power source is available. Use an external power index when referencing.

EXTERNAL POWER BREAKER PULLED.name: EXTERNAL POWER BREAKER PULLED
EXTERNAL POWER BREAKER PULLED.description: Boolean, The state of the breaker of an external power source

EXTERNAL POWER CONNECTION ON.name: EXTERNAL POWER CONNECTION ON
EXTERNAL POWER CONNECTION ON.description: Boolean, The state of the connection between a bus and an external power source

EXTERNAL POWER ON.name: EXTERNAL POWER ON
EXTERNAL POWER ON.description: The external power switch position, true if the switch is ON. Use an external power index when referencing.

BLEED AIR ENGINE.name: BLEED AIR ENGINE:index
BLEED AIR ENGINE.description: Returns whether or not the indexed engine (see note) attempts to provide bleed air.

BLEED AIR SOURCE CONTROL.name: BLEED AIR SOURCE CONTROL:index
BLEED AIR SOURCE CONTROL.description:
The bleed air system source controller for an indexed engine (see note). This will work as follows:
          
            When engines and APU are activated, it will return 0 because it is in Auto.
            If the APU is removed, it will return 3 for engines only.
            If instead the engines are removed, it would return 2 for the APU only.
            If the APU and engines are removed, it would return 1 (so, off).

ENGINE MIXURE AVAILABLE.name: ENGINE MIXURE AVAILABLE
ENGINE MIXURE AVAILABLE.description: True if engine mixture is available for prop engines. Deprecated, do not use (mixture is always available)!

ENGINE TYPE.name: ENGINE TYPE
ENGINE TYPE.units:
Enum:
          
            0 = Piston
            1 = Jet
            2 = None
            3 = Helo(Bell) turbine
            4 = Unsupported
            5 = Turboprop

ENG ANTI ICE.name: ENG ANTI ICE:index
ENG ANTI ICE.description: Anti-ice switch for the indexed engine (see note), true if enabled false otherwise.

ENG COMBUSTION.name: ENG COMBUSTION:index
ENG COMBUSTION.description: True if the indexed engine (see note) is running, false otherwise.

ENG CYLINDER HEAD TEMPERATURE.name: ENG CYLINDER HEAD TEMPERATURE:index
ENG CYLINDER HEAD TEMPERATURE.description: The indexed engine (see note) cylinder head temperature.

ENG EXHAUST GAS TEMPERATURE.name: ENG EXHAUST GAS TEMPERATURE:index
ENG EXHAUST GAS TEMPERATURE.description: Exhaust gas temperature for the indexed engine (see note).

ENG EXHAUST GAS TEMPERATURE GES.name: ENG EXHAUST GAS TEMPERATURE GES:index
ENG EXHAUST GAS TEMPERATURE GES.description: Governed engine setting exhaust gas temperature for the indexed engine (see note).

ENG FAILED.name: ENG FAILED:index
ENG FAILED.description: Failure flag for the indexed engine (see note) that has failed.

ENG FUEL FLOW BUG POSITION.name: ENG FUEL FLOW BUG POSITION:index
ENG FUEL FLOW BUG POSITION.description: Fuel flow reference in pounds per hour for the indexed engine (see note).

ENG FUEL FLOW GPH.name: ENG FUEL FLOW GPH:index
ENG FUEL FLOW GPH.description: Engine fuel flow in gallons per hour for the indexed engine (see note).

ENG FUEL FLOW PPH.name: ENG FUEL FLOW PPH:index
ENG FUEL FLOW PPH.description: The indexed engine (see note) fuel flow in pounds per hour.

ENG FUEL FLOW PPH SSL.name: ENG FUEL FLOW PPH SSL:index
ENG FUEL FLOW PPH SSL.description:
Engine fuel flow in pounds per hour.
          Deprecated in favour of ENG FUEL FLOW PPH.

ENG HYDRAULIC PRESSURE.name: ENG HYDRAULIC PRESSURE:index
ENG HYDRAULIC PRESSURE.description: The indexed engine (see note) hydraulic pressure.

ENG HYDRAULIC QUANTITY.name: ENG HYDRAULIC QUANTITY:index
ENG HYDRAULIC QUANTITY.description: The indexed engine (see note)hydraulic fluid quantity, as a percentage of total capacity

ENG MANIFOLD PRESSURE.name: ENG MANIFOLD PRESSURE:index
ENG MANIFOLD PRESSURE.description: The indexed engine (see note) manifold pressure.

ENG MAX RPM.name: ENG MAX RPM
ENG MAX RPM.description: The indexed engine (see note) Maximum rpm.

ENG N1 RPM.name: ENG N1 RPM:index
ENG N1 RPM.description: The indexed engine (see note) N1 rpm.

ENG N2 RPM.name: ENG N2 RPM:index
ENG N2 RPM.description: The indexed engine (see note) N2 rpm.

ENG OIL PRESSURE.name: ENG OIL PRESSURE:index
ENG OIL PRESSURE.description: The indexed engine (see note) oil pressure.

ENG OIL QUANTITY.name: ENG OIL QUANTITY:index
ENG OIL QUANTITY.description: The indexed engine (see note) oil quantity as a percentage of full capacity.

ENG OIL TEMPERATURE.name: ENG OIL TEMPERATURE:index
ENG OIL TEMPERATURE.description: The indexed engine (see note) oil temperature.

ENG ON FIRE.name: ENG ON FIRE:index
ENG ON FIRE.description: The indexed engine (see note) on fire state.

ENG PRESSURE RATIO.name: ENG PRESSURE RATIO:index
ENG PRESSURE RATIO.description: The indexed engine (see note) pressure ratio.

ENG PRESSURE RATIO GES.name: ENG PRESSURE RATIO GES:index
ENG PRESSURE RATIO GES.description: Engine pressure ratio. Deprecated, do not use!

ENG RPM SCALER.name: ENG RPM SCALER:index
ENG RPM SCALER.description: RPM scalar value. Deprecated, do not use!

ESTIMATED FUEL FLOW.name: ESTIMATED FUEL FLOW:index
ESTIMATED FUEL FLOW.description: Estimated fuel flow to the indexed engine (see note) at cruise speed.

FULL THROTTLE THRUST TO WEIGHT RATIO.name: FULL THROTTLE THRUST TO WEIGHT RATIO
FULL THROTTLE THRUST TO WEIGHT RATIO.description: Full throttle thrust to weight ratio
FULL THROTTLE THRUST TO WEIGHT RATIO.name_std: FULL THROTTLE THRUST TO WEIGHT RATIO

GENERAL ENG ANTI ICE POSITION.name: GENERAL ENG ANTI ICE POSITION:index
GENERAL ENG ANTI ICE POSITION.description: The indexed engine (see note) anti-ice switch state - 0 (FALSE) is off and 1 (TRUE) is on.

GENERAL ENG COMBUSTION.name: GENERAL ENG COMBUSTION:index
GENERAL ENG COMBUSTION.description:
Set the indexed engine (see note) combustion flag to TRUE or FALSE. Note that this will not only stop all combustion, but it will also set the engine RPM to 0, regardless of the actual state of the simulation.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

GENERAL ENG COMBUSTION EX1.name: GENERAL ENG COMBUSTION EX1:index
GENERAL ENG COMBUSTION EX1.description: This SimVar is similar to GENERAL ENG COMBUSTION, in that it can also be used to enable or disable engine combustion. However this SimVar will not interfere with the current state of ths simulation. For example, if the aircraft has a turbine engine with auto_ignition enabled or it's a propeller engine with magnetos, then in the subsequent simulation frames this SimVar may be set to 1 (TRUE) again as the engine restarts automatically.

GENERAL ENG COMBUSTION SOUND PERCENT.name: GENERAL ENG COMBUSTION SOUND PERCENT:index
GENERAL ENG COMBUSTION SOUND PERCENT.description:
Percent of maximum sound being created by the indexed engine (see note).
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

GENERAL ENG DAMAGE PERCENT.name: GENERAL ENG DAMAGE PERCENT:index
GENERAL ENG DAMAGE PERCENT.description: Percent of total damage to the indexed engine (see note).

GENERAL ENG ELAPSED TIME.name: GENERAL ENG ELAPSED TIME:index
GENERAL ENG ELAPSED TIME.description: Total elapsed time since the indexed engine (see note) was started.

GENERAL ENG EXHAUST GAS TEMPERATURE.name: GENERAL ENG EXHAUST GAS TEMPERATURE:index
GENERAL ENG EXHAUST GAS TEMPERATURE.description: The indexed engine (see note) exhaust gas temperature.

GENERAL ENG FAILED.name: GENERAL ENG FAILED:index
GENERAL ENG FAILED.description: The indexed engine (see note) fail flag.

GENERAL ENG FIRE DETECTED.name: GENERAL ENG FIRE DETECTED:index
GENERAL ENG FIRE DETECTED.description: Detects if a fire has been detected in an indexed engine (see note) or not. If 0 (FALSE) no fire has been detected and if 1 (TRUE) then it has.

GENERAL ENG FUEL PRESSURE.name: GENERAL ENG FUEL PRESSURE:index
GENERAL ENG FUEL PRESSURE.description: The indexed engine (see note) fuel pressure.

GENERAL ENG FUEL PUMP ON.name: GENERAL ENG FUEL PUMP ON:index
GENERAL ENG FUEL PUMP ON.description: Whether the indexed engine (see note) fuel pump on (1, TRUE) or off (0, FALSE).

GENERAL ENG FUEL PUMP SWITCH.name: GENERAL ENG FUEL PUMP SWITCH:index
GENERAL ENG FUEL PUMP SWITCH.description: Fuel pump switch state the indexed engine (see note). If 0 (FALSE) the pump is off and if 1 (TRUE) then it is on.

GENERAL ENG FUEL PUMP SWITCH EX1.name: GENERAL ENG FUEL PUMP SWITCH EX1:index
GENERAL ENG FUEL PUMP SWITCH EX1.description: Equivalent to GENERAL ENG FUEL PUMP SWITCH but differentiates between ON and AUTO
GENERAL ENG FUEL PUMP SWITCH EX1.name_std: GENERAL ENG FUEL PUMP SWITCH EX1

GENERAL ENG FUEL USED SINCE START.name: GENERAL ENG FUEL USED SINCE START:index
GENERAL ENG FUEL USED SINCE START.description: Fuel used since the indexed engine (see note) was last started.
GENERAL ENG FUEL USED SINCE START.name_std: GENERAL ENG FUEL USED SINCE START

GENERAL ENG FUEL VALVE.name: GENERAL ENG FUEL VALVE:index
