GENERAL ENG FUEL VALVE.description: Fuel valve state for the indexed engine (see note). If 0 (FALSE) then the valve is closed and if 1 (TRUE) then it is open.

GENERAL ENG GENERATOR ACTIVE.name: GENERAL ENG GENERATOR ACTIVE:index
GENERAL ENG GENERATOR ACTIVE.description: Settable alternator (generator) on/off switch for the indexed engine (see note).

GENERAL ENG GENERATOR SWITCH.name: GENERAL ENG GENERATOR SWITCH:index
GENERAL ENG GENERATOR SWITCH.description: Alternator (generator) on/off switch state for the indexed engine (see note).

GENERAL ENG HOBBS ELAPSED TIME.name: GENERAL ENG HOBBS ELAPSED TIME:index
GENERAL ENG HOBBS ELAPSED TIME.description:
This can be used to find the time since the indexed engine (see note) started running. Similar to ElapsedTachometerTime, this records the time the engine has been running, but instead of taking a % of the time based on the Pct/RPM this takes the full time, but only if a threshold RPM/speed is reached. You can set the thresholds using the accumulated_time_hobbs_min_pct_rpm
          and accumulated_time_hobbs_min_knots parameters in the [GENERALENGINEDATA] section of the engines.cfg file.

GENERAL ENG MAX REACHED RPM.name: GENERAL ENG MAX REACHED RPM:index
GENERAL ENG MAX REACHED RPM.description: Maximum attained rpm for the indexed engine (see note).

GENERAL ENG MIXTURE LEVER POSITION.name: GENERAL ENG MIXTURE LEVER POSITION:index
GENERAL ENG MIXTURE LEVER POSITION.description: Percent of max mixture lever position for the indexed engine (see note).

GENERAL ENG OIL LEAKED PERCENT.name: GENERAL ENG OIL LEAKED PERCENT:index
GENERAL ENG OIL LEAKED PERCENT.description: Percent of max oil capacity leaked for the indexed engine (see note).

GENERAL ENG OIL PRESSURE.name: GENERAL ENG OIL PRESSURE:index
GENERAL ENG OIL PRESSURE.description: The indexed engine (see note) oil pressure.

GENERAL ENG OIL TEMPERATURE.name: GENERAL ENG OIL TEMPERATURE:index
GENERAL ENG OIL TEMPERATURE.description: The indexed engine (see note) oil temperature.

GENERAL ENG PCT MAX RPM.name: GENERAL ENG PCT MAX RPM:index
GENERAL ENG PCT MAX RPM.description:
Percent of max rated rpm for the indexed engine (see note).
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

GENERAL ENG PROPELLER LEVER POSITION.name: GENERAL ENG PROPELLER LEVER POSITION:index
GENERAL ENG PROPELLER LEVER POSITION.description: Percent of max prop lever position for the indexed engine (see note).

GENERAL ENG REVERSE THRUST ENGAGED.name: GENERAL ENG REVERSE THRUST ENGAGED
GENERAL ENG REVERSE THRUST ENGAGED.description: This will return 1 (TRUE) if the reverse thruster is engaged, or 0 (FALSE) otherwise.

GENERAL ENG RPM.name: GENERAL ENG RPM:index
GENERAL ENG RPM.description:
The RPM for an indexed engine (see note).
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

GENERAL ENG STARTER.name: GENERAL ENG STARTER:index
GENERAL ENG STARTER.description: The indexed engine (see note) starter on/off state.

GENERAL ENG THROTTLE LEVER POSITION.name: GENERAL ENG THROTTLE LEVER POSITION:index
GENERAL ENG THROTTLE LEVER POSITION.description: Percent of max throttle position for the indexed engine (see note).

GENERAL ENG THROTTLE MANAGED MODE.name: GENERAL ENG THROTTLE MANAGED MODE:index
GENERAL ENG THROTTLE MANAGED MODE.description: Current mode of the managed throttle for the indexed engine (see note).

MASTER IGNITION SWITCH.name: MASTER IGNITION SWITCH
MASTER IGNITION SWITCH.description: Aircraft master ignition switch (grounds all engines magnetos).

MAX EGT.name: MAX EGT
MAX EGT.description: The maximum EGT, as set using the egt_peak_temperature parameter in the engines.cfg file.

MAX OIL TEMPERATURE.name: MAX OIL TEMPERATURE
MAX OIL TEMPERATURE.description: The maximum oil temperature, as set using the parameter oil_temp_heating_constant in the engines.cfg file.

MAX RATED ENGINE RPM.name: MAX RATED ENGINE RPM
MAX RATED ENGINE RPM.description: Maximum rated rpm for the indexed engine (see note).

PANEL AUTO FEATHER SWITCH.name: PANEL AUTO FEATHER SWITCH:index
PANEL AUTO FEATHER SWITCH.description: Auto-feather arming switch for the indexed engine (see note). Please see the Note On Autofeathering for more information.

PROP AUTO CRUISE ACTIVE.name: PROP AUTO CRUISE ACTIVE
PROP AUTO CRUISE ACTIVE.description: True if prop auto cruise active

PROP AUTO FEATHER ARMED.name: PROP AUTO FEATHER ARMED:index
PROP AUTO FEATHER ARMED.description: Auto-feather armed state for the indexed engine (see note).

PROP BETA.name: PROP BETA:index
PROP BETA.description: The "prop beta" is the pitch of the blades of the propeller, and this can be used to retrieve the current pitch setting, per indexed engine (see note).

PROP BETA FORCED ACTIVE.name: PROP BETA FORCED ACTIVE
PROP BETA FORCED ACTIVE.description: This can be used to enable the propeller forced beta mode (1, TRUE) or disable it (0, FALSE), when being written to. When being read from, it will return TRUE (1) if the forced beta mode is enabled or FALSE (0) if it isn't. When enabled, the PROP BETA FORCED POSITION value will be used to drive the prop beta, while the internal coded simulation logic is used when this is disabled.

PROP BETA FORCED POSITION.name: PROP BETA FORCED POSITION
PROP BETA FORCED POSITION.description: Get or set the beta at which the prop is forced. Only valid when PROP BETA FORCED ACTIVE is TRUE (1).

PROP BETA MAX.name: PROP BETA MAX
PROP BETA MAX.description: The "prop beta" is the pitch of the blades of the propeller. This retrieves the maximum possible pitch value for all engines.

PROP BETA MIN.name: PROP BETA MIN
PROP BETA MIN.description: The "prop beta" is the pitch of the blades of the propeller. This retrieves the minimum possible pitch value for all engines.

PROP BETA MIN REVERSE.name: PROP BETA MIN REVERSE
PROP BETA MIN REVERSE.description: The "prop beta" is the pitch of the blades of the propeller. This retrieves the minimum possible pitch value when the propeller is in reverse for all engines.

PROP DEICE SWITCH.name: PROP DEICE SWITCH:index
PROP DEICE SWITCH.description: True if prop deice switch on for the indexed engine (see note).

PROP FEATHERED.name: PROP FEATHERED:index
PROP FEATHERED.description: This will return the feathered state of the propeller for an indexed engine (see note). The state is either feathered (true) or not (false).

PROP FEATHERING INHIBIT.name: PROP FEATHERING INHIBIT:index
PROP FEATHERING INHIBIT.description: Feathering inhibit flag for the indexed engine (see note).

PROP FEATHER SWITCH.name: PROP FEATHER SWITCH:index
PROP FEATHER SWITCH.description: Prop feather switch for the indexed engine (see note).

PROP RPM.name: PROP RPM:index
PROP RPM.description: Propeller rpm for the indexed engine (see note).

PROP SYNC ACTIVE.name: PROP SYNC ACTIVE:index
PROP SYNC ACTIVE.description: True if prop sync is active the indexed engine (see note).

PROP SYNC DELTA LEVER.name: PROP SYNC DELTA LEVER:index
PROP SYNC DELTA LEVER.description: Corrected prop correction input on slaved engine for the indexed engine (see note).

SHUTOFF VALVE PULLED.name: SHUTOFF VALVE PULLED
SHUTOFF VALVE PULLED.description: This checks if the shutoff valve to the engine has been pulled (true) or not (false). When pulled piston engines will be blocked from getting any fuel.

THROTTLE LOWER LIMIT.name: THROTTLE LOWER LIMIT
THROTTLE LOWER LIMIT.description: Percent throttle defining lower limit (negative for reverse thrust equipped airplanes).

TURB ENG AFTERBURNER PCT ACTIVE.name: TURB_ENG_AFTERBURNER_PCT_ACTIVE
TURB ENG AFTERBURNER PCT ACTIVE.description: ROTOR CYCLIC BLADE MAX PITCH POSITION

TURB ENG BLEED AIR.name: TURB ENG BLEED AIR:index
TURB ENG BLEED AIR.description: Bleed air pressure for the indexed engine (see note).

TURB ENG COMMANDED N1.name: TURB ENG COMMANDED N1:index
TURB ENG COMMANDED N1.description: Effective commanded N1 for the indexed turbine engine (see note).

TURB ENG CONDITION LEVER POSITION.name: TURB ENG CONDITION LEVER POSITION:index
TURB ENG CONDITION LEVER POSITION.description:
When the throttle is on idle position, this sets the condition levers to one of 3 positions to define the idle N1 target for the indexed engine (see note):
          
            Down position is the cut-off position that cuts the fuel to the engine, effectively shutting down the engine.
            Middle position requires N1 to reach the low idle value when throttle is in idle position (low idle value can be checked using the TURB_ENG_LOW_IDLE SimVar).
            High position requires N1 to reach the high idle value when throttle is in idle position (high idle value can be checked using the TURB_ENG_HIGH_IDLE SimVar).
          
          Note that this option requires several settings from the engines.cfg file to be set to specific values before working correctly:
          
            DisableMixtureControls needs to be set to 1 (TRUE).
            tp_idle_range should be set to 0 (since there is no mixture setting).
            idle_fuel_flow and idle_high_fuel_flow must be set to the same value (since there is no mixture setting to induce a variation between the 2).
            low_idle_n1 and high_idle_n1 to be correctly set.
TURB ENG CONDITION LEVER POSITION.units:
Enum:
          
            0 = fuel cut-off
            1 = low idle
            2 = high idle

TURB ENG CORRECTED FF.name: TURB ENG CORRECTED FF:index
TURB ENG CORRECTED FF.description: Corrected fuel flow for the indexed engine (see note).

TURB ENG CORRECTED N1.name: TURB ENG CORRECTED N1:index
TURB ENG CORRECTED N1.description: The indexed turbine engine (see note) corrected N1.

TURB ENG CORRECTED N2.name: TURB ENG CORRECTED N2:index
TURB ENG CORRECTED N2.description: The indexed turbine engine (see note) corrected N2.

TURB ENG FREE TURBINE TORQUE.name: TURB ENG FREE TURBINE TORQUE:index
TURB ENG FREE TURBINE TORQUE.description: The amount of free torque for the indexed turbine engine (see note).

TURB ENG FUEL AVAILABLE.name: TURB ENG FUEL AVAILABLE:index
TURB ENG FUEL AVAILABLE.description: True if fuel is available for the indexed engine (see note).

TURB ENG FUEL EFFICIENCY LOSS.name: TURB ENG FUEL EFFICIENCY LOSS:index
TURB ENG FUEL EFFICIENCY LOSS.description: This is used to control the fuel efficiency loss of the indexed engine, from 0 - no fuel efficiency loss - to 100 - double the fuel consumption.

TURB ENG FUEL FLOW PPH.name: TURB ENG FUEL FLOW PPH:index
TURB ENG FUEL FLOW PPH.description: The indexed engine (see note) fuel flow rate.

TURB ENG HIGH IDLE.name: TURB ENG HIGH IDLE:index
TURB ENG HIGH IDLE.description: Retrieves the high idle N1 value to be reached by the the indexed turboprop engine (see note) with throttle in idle position and condition lever in high idle position (condition lever position can be checked or set using the TURB_ENG_CONDITION_LEVER_POSITION SimVar).

TURB ENG IGNITION SWITCH.name: TURB ENG IGNITION SWITCH:index
TURB ENG IGNITION SWITCH.description: True if the the indexed turbine engine (see note) ignition switch is on.

TURB ENG IGNITION SWITCH EX1.name: TURB ENG IGNITION SWITCH EX1:index
TURB ENG IGNITION SWITCH EX1.description: Position of the the indexed turbine engine (see note) Ignition Switch. Similar to TURB_ENG_IGNITION_SWITCH but differentiates between ON and AUTO.

TURB ENG IS IGNITING.name: TURB ENG IS IGNITING:index
TURB ENG IS IGNITING.description: Whether or not the ignition system is currently running for the indexed engine (see note). Depends on TURB_ENG_IGNITION_SWITCH_EX1 Enum, the cfg var ignition_auto_type and current state of the plane.

TURB ENG ITT.name: TURB ENG ITT:index
TURB ENG ITT.description: Retrieve or set the ITT for the indexed engine (see note).

TURB ENG ITT COOLING EFFICIENCY LOSS.name: TURB ENG ITT COOLING EFFICIENCY LOSS:index
TURB ENG ITT COOLING EFFICIENCY LOSS.description: This is used to control the ITT cooling efficiency loss of the indexed engine, from 0 - no cooling efficiency loss - to 100 -engine recieves no ITT cooling.
TURB ENG ITT COOLING EFFICIENCY LOSS.name_std: TURB ENG ITT COOLING EFFICIENCY LOSS

TURB ENG JET THRUST.name: TURB ENG JET THRUST:index
TURB ENG JET THRUST.description: The indexed engine (see note) jet thrust.

TURB ENG LOW IDLE.name: TURB ENG LOW IDLE:index
TURB ENG LOW IDLE.description: Retrieves the low idle N1 value to be reached by the the indexed turboprop engine (see note) with throttle in idle position and condition lever in low idle position (condition lever position can be checked or set using the TURB_ENG_CONDITION_LEVER_POSITION SimVar).

TURB ENG MASTER STARTER SWITCH.name: TURB ENG MASTER STARTER SWITCH
TURB ENG MASTER STARTER SWITCH.description: True if the turbine engine master starter switch is on, false otherwise.

TURB ENG MAX TORQUE PERCENT.name: TURB ENG MAX TORQUE PERCENT:index
TURB ENG MAX TORQUE PERCENT.description: Percent of max rated torque for the indexed engine (see note).

TURB ENG N1.name: TURB ENG N1:index
TURB ENG N1.description:
The indexed turbine engine (see note) N1 value.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

TURB ENG N1 LOSS.name: TURB ENG N1 LOSS:index
TURB ENG N1 LOSS.description: This is used to control the N1 loss of the indexed engine, from 0 - no N1 loss - to 100 - 100% N1 loss.

TURB ENG N2.name: TURB ENG N2:index
TURB ENG N2.description:
The indexed turbine engine (see note) N2 value.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

TURB ENG NUM TANKS USED.name: TURB ENG NUM TANKS USED:index
TURB ENG NUM TANKS USED.description: Number of tanks currently being used by the indexed engine (see note).

TURB ENG PRESSURE RATIO.name: TURB ENG PRESSURE RATIO:index
TURB ENG PRESSURE RATIO.description: The indexed engine (see note) pressure ratio.

TURB ENG PRIMARY NOZZLE PERCENT.name: TURB ENG PRIMARY NOZZLE PERCENT:index
TURB ENG PRIMARY NOZZLE PERCENT.description: Percent thrust of primary nozzle for the indexed engine (see note).

TURB ENG REVERSE NOZZLE PERCENT.name: TURB ENG REVERSE NOZZLE PERCENT:index
TURB ENG REVERSE NOZZLE PERCENT.description:
Percent thrust reverser nozzles deployed for the indexed engine (see note).
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

TURB ENG TANKS USED.name: TURB ENG TANKS USED:index
TURB ENG TANKS USED.description:
Fuel tanks used by the indexed engine (see note), one or more of the following bit flags:
          
            Center 1 Bit 0
            Center 2 Bit 1
            Center 3 Bit 2
            Left Main Bit 3
            Left Aux Bit 4
            Left Tip Bit 5
            Right Main Bit 6
            Right Aux Bit 7
            Right Tip Bit 8
            External 1 Bit 9
            External 2 Bit 10

TURB ENG TANK SELECTOR.name: TURB ENG TANK SELECTOR:index
TURB ENG TANK SELECTOR.description: Fuel tank selected for the indexed engine (see note). See Fuel Tank Selection for a list of values.

TURB ENG THROTTLE COMMANDED N1.name: TURB ENG THROTTLE COMMANDED N1:index
TURB ENG THROTTLE COMMANDED N1.description: The indexed turbine engine (see note) commanded N1 for current throttle position.

TURB ENG THRUST EFFICIENCY LOSS.name: TURB ENG THRUST EFFICIENCY LOSS:index
TURB ENG THRUST EFFICIENCY LOSS.description: This can be used to control the thrust efficiency loss of the indexed engine, where a value of 0 is 100% of available thrust, and 100 is 0% available thrust.

TURB ENG VIBRATION.name: TURB ENG VIBRATION:index
TURB ENG VIBRATION.description: The indexed turbine engine (see note) vibration value.

TURB MAX ITT.name: TURB MAX ITT
TURB MAX ITT.description: Retrieve the itt_peak_temperature as set in the engines.cfg file.

RECIP CARBURETOR TEMPERATURE.name: RECIP CARBURETOR TEMPERATURE:index
RECIP CARBURETOR TEMPERATURE.description: Carburetor temperature the indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG ALTERNATE AIR POSITION.name: RECIP ENG ALTERNATE AIR POSITION:index
RECIP ENG ALTERNATE AIR POSITION.description: Alternate air control the indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG ANTIDETONATION TANK MAX QUANTI.name: RECIP ENG ANTIDETONATION TANK MAX QUANTITY:index
RECIP ENG ANTIDETONATION TANK MAX QUANTI.description: The maximum quantity of water/methanol mixture in the ADI tank for the indexed engine (see note). This value is set as part of the [ANTIDETONATION_SYSTEM.N] section in the aircraft configuration files.
RECIP ENG ANTIDETONATION TANK MAX QUANTI.name_std: RECIP ENG ANTIDETONATION TANK MAX QUANTITY

RECIP ENG ANTIDETONATION TANK QUANTITY.name: RECIP ENG ANTIDETONATION TANK QUANTITY:index
RECIP ENG ANTIDETONATION TANK QUANTITY.description: The quantity of water/methanol mixture currently in the ADI tank for the indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG ANTIDETONATION TANK VALVE.name: RECIP ENG ANTIDETONATION TANK VALVE:index
RECIP ENG ANTIDETONATION TANK VALVE.description: The status of the ADI tank valve for the indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG ANTIDETONATION FLOW RATE.name: RECIP ENG ANTIDETONATION FLOW RATE:index
RECIP ENG ANTIDETONATION FLOW RATE.description: This gives the actual flow rate of the Anti Detonation system for the indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG BRAKE POWER.name: RECIP ENG BRAKE POWER:index
RECIP ENG BRAKE POWER.description: Brake power produced by the indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG COOLANT RESERVOIR PERCENT.name: RECIP ENG COOLANT RESERVOIR PERCENT:index
RECIP ENG COOLANT RESERVOIR PERCENT.description: Percent coolant available for the indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG COWL FLAP POSITION.name: RECIP ENG COWL FLAP POSITION:index
RECIP ENG COWL FLAP POSITION.description: Percent cowl flap opened for the indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG CYLINDER HEAD TEMPERATURE.name: RECIP ENG CYLINDER HEAD TEMPERATURE:index
RECIP ENG CYLINDER HEAD TEMPERATURE.description: Engine cylinder head temperature for the indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG CYLINDER HEALTH.name: RECIP ENG CYLINDER HEALTH:index
RECIP ENG CYLINDER HEALTH.description: Index high 16 bits is engine number, low16 cylinder number, both indexed from 1.

RECIP ENG DETONATING.name: RECIP ENG DETONATING:index
RECIP ENG DETONATING.description: Set to 1 (TRUE) if the indexed engine (see note) is detonating.

RECIP ENG EMERGENCY BOOST ACTIVE.name: RECIP ENG EMERGENCY BOOST ACTIVE:index
RECIP ENG EMERGENCY BOOST ACTIVE.description: Whether emergency boost is active (1, TRUE) or not (0, FALSE) for the indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG EMERGENCY BOOST ELAPSED TIME.name: RECIP ENG EMERGENCY BOOST ELAPSED TIME:index
RECIP ENG EMERGENCY BOOST ELAPSED TIME.description:
The elapsed time that emergency boost has been active on the indexed engine (see note). The timer will start when boost is first activated.
          IMPORTANT! This timer does not reset. So if you set your time limit in the engines.cfg file to 315s and you spend 2 minutes with boost active, then pull back on the throttle for 1 minute, then engage boost again for 2 minutes, the simulation will consider that you spent 4 minutes with boost active. The 1 minute pause is not taken into account.
RECIP ENG EMERGENCY BOOST ELAPSED TIME.name_std: RECIP ENG EMERGENCY BOOST ELAPSED TIME

RECIP ENG ENGINE MASTER SWITCH.name: RECIP ENG ENGINE MASTER SWITCH:index
RECIP ENG ENGINE MASTER SWITCH.description: Whether or not the Engine Master switch is active on an indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG FUEL AVAILABLE.name: RECIP ENG FUEL AVAILABLE:index
RECIP ENG FUEL AVAILABLE.description: True if fuel is available for the indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG FUEL FLOW.name: RECIP ENG FUEL FLOW:index
RECIP ENG FUEL FLOW.description: The indexed engine (see note) fuel flow.

RECIP ENG FUEL NUMBER TANKS USED.name: RECIP ENG FUEL NUMBER TANKS USED:index
RECIP ENG FUEL NUMBER TANKS USED.description: Number of tanks currently being used by the indexed engine (see note).

            Center 1 Bit 0

            Left Main Bit 3

            External 2 Bit 10

RECIP ENG FUEL TANK SELECTOR.name: RECIP ENG FUEL TANK SELECTOR:index
RECIP ENG FUEL TANK SELECTOR.description: Fuel tank selected for the indexed engine (see note). See Fuel Tank Selection for a list of values.

RECIP ENG GLOW PLUG ACTIVE.name: RECIP ENG GLOW PLUG ACTIVE:index
RECIP ENG GLOW PLUG ACTIVE.description: Whether or not the Glow Plug is active on the indexed engine (see note)..

RECIP ENG LEFT MAGNETO.name: RECIP ENG LEFT MAGNETO:index
RECIP ENG LEFT MAGNETO.description: Left magneto state for the indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG MANIFOLD PRESSURE.name: RECIP ENG MANIFOLD PRESSURE:index
RECIP ENG MANIFOLD PRESSURE.description: The indexed engine (see note) manifold pressure.

RECIP ENG NITROUS TANK MAX QUANTITY.name: RECIP ENG NITROUS TANK MAX QUANTITY:index
RECIP ENG NITROUS TANK MAX QUANTITY.description: The maximum quantity of nitrous permitted per indexed engine (see note).
RECIP ENG NITROUS TANK MAX QUANTITY.name_std: RECIP ENG NITROUS TANK MAX QUANTITY

RECIP ENG NITROUS TANK QUANTITY.name: RECIP ENG NITROUS TANK QUANTITY:index
RECIP ENG NITROUS TANK QUANTITY.description: The quantity of nitrous per indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG NITROUS TANK VALVE.name: RECIP ENG NITROUS TANK VALVE
RECIP ENG NITROUS TANK VALVE.description: The statte of the nitrous tank valve for the indexed engine (see note). Either 1 (TRUE) for open or 0 (FALSE) for closed.

RECIP ENG NUM CYLINDERS.name: RECIP ENG NUM CYLINDERS:index
RECIP ENG NUM CYLINDERS.description: The number of cylinders for the indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG NUM CYLINDERS FAILED.name: RECIP ENG NUM CYLINDERS FAILED:index
RECIP ENG NUM CYLINDERS FAILED.description: The number of cylinders that have failed in the indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG PRIMER.name: RECIP ENG PRIMER:index
RECIP ENG PRIMER.description: The indexed engine (see note) primer state.

RECIP ENG RADIATOR TEMPERATURE.name: RECIP ENG RADIATOR TEMPERATURE:index
RECIP ENG RADIATOR TEMPERATURE.description: The indexed engine (see note) radiator temperature.

RECIP ENG RIGHT MAGNETO.name: RECIP ENG RIGHT MAGNETO:index
RECIP ENG RIGHT MAGNETO.description: The indexed engine (see note) right magneto state.

RECIP ENG STARTER TORQUE.name: RECIP ENG STARTER TORQUE:index
RECIP ENG STARTER TORQUE.description: Torque produced by the indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG SUPERCHARGER ACTIVE GEAR.name: RECIP ENG SUPERCHARGER ACTIVE GEAR:index
RECIP ENG SUPERCHARGER ACTIVE GEAR.description: Returns which of the supercharger gears is engaged for the indexed engine (see note).

RECIP ENG TURBINE INLET TEMPERATURE.name: RECIP ENG TURBINE INLET TEMPERATURE:index
RECIP ENG TURBINE INLET TEMPERATURE.description: The indexed engine (see note) turbine inlet temperature.

RECIP ENG TURBOCHARGER FAILED.name: RECIP ENG TURBOCHARGER FAILED:index
RECIP ENG TURBOCHARGER FAILED.description: The indexed engine (see note) turbo failed state.

RECIP ENG WASTEGATE POSITION.name: RECIP ENG WASTEGATE POSITION:index
RECIP ENG WASTEGATE POSITION.description: When the engines.cfg parameter turbocharged is TRUE, this SimVar will return the percentage that the turbo waste gate is closed for the indexed engine (see note). If the turbocharged variable is FALSE and the manifold_pressure_regulator parameter is TRUE, then this will return the percentage that the manifold pressure regulator is closed for the indexed engine.

RECIP MAX CHT.name: RECIP MAX CHT
RECIP MAX CHT.description: This will return the cylinder head temperature value set by the cht_heating_constant parameter in the engines.cfg file.

RECIP MIXTURE RATIO.name: RECIP MIXTURE RATIO:index
RECIP MIXTURE RATIO.description: Fuel / Air mixture ratio for the indexed engine (see note).

DECISION ALTITUDE MSL.name: DECISION ALTITUDE MSL
DECISION ALTITUDE MSL.description: Design decision altitude above mean sea level

DESIGN CRUISE ALT.name: DESIGN CRUISE ALT
DESIGN CRUISE ALT.description: This design constant represents the optimal altitude the aircraft should maintain when in cruise. It is derived from the cruise_alt setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg. Default is 1500ft.

DESIGN SPAWN ALTITUDE CRUISE.name: DESIGN SPAWN ALTITUDE CRUISE
DESIGN SPAWN ALTITUDE CRUISE.description: This design constant represents the spawn altitude for the aircraft when spawning in cruise. It is derived from the spawn_cruise_altitude setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg. Default is 1500ft.

DESIGN SPAWN ALTITUDE DESCENT.name: DESIGN SPAWN ALTITUDE DESCENT
DESIGN SPAWN ALTITUDE DESCENT.description: This design constant represents the spawn altitude for the aircraft when spawning in descent. It is derived from the spawn_descent_altitude setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg. Default is 500ft.

DESIGN SPEED CLIMB.name: DESIGN SPEED CLIMB
DESIGN SPEED CLIMB.description: This design constant represents the optimal climb speed for the aircraft. It is derived from the climb_speed setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg. Default value is -1.

DESIGN SPEED MIN ROTATION.name: DESIGN SPEED MIN ROTATION
DESIGN SPEED MIN ROTATION.description: This design constant represents the minimum speed required for aircraft rotation. It is derived from the rotation_speed_min setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg. Default value is -1.

DESIGN SPEED VC.name: DESIGN SPEED VC
DESIGN SPEED VC.description: This design constant represents the aircraft ideal cruising speed. It is derived from the cruise_speed setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg. The default value is computed an internal function that uses the estimated cruise altitude and estimated cruise percent power, according of the engine type, the number of engines, the density, the wing area and some drag parameters. Normally this value is set in the CFG file and the default value is never used.

DESIGN SPEED VS0.name: DESIGN SPEED VS0
DESIGN SPEED VS0.description: This design constant represents the the stall speed when flaps are fully extended. It is derived from the full_flaps_stall_speed setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg. Default value is 0.8 x VS.

DESIGN SPEED VS1.name: DESIGN SPEED VS1
DESIGN SPEED VS1.description: This design constant represents the stall speed when flaps are fully retracted. It is derived from the flaps_up_stall_speed setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg. Default value is 0.

DESIGN TAKEOFF SPEED.name: DESIGN TAKEOFF SPEED
DESIGN TAKEOFF SPEED.description: This design constant represents the aircraft ideal takoff speed. It is derived from the takeoff_speed setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg.

G LIMITER SETTING.name: G LIMITER SETTING
G LIMITER SETTING.description: This returns the setting of the G-limiter, as set using the GLimiterSetting parameter.

IS TAIL DRAGGER.name: IS TAIL DRAGGER
IS TAIL DRAGGER.description: True if the aircraft is a taildragger

MIN DRAG VELOCITY.name: MIN DRAG VELOCITY
MIN DRAG VELOCITY.description: Minimum drag velocity, in clean, with no input and no gears, when at 10000ft.

SEMIBODY LOADFACTOR Y.name: SEMIBODY LOADFACTOR Y
SEMIBODY LOADFACTOR Y.description: Acceleration along the axis Y divided by the gravity constant g (usually around 9.81m.s2)

SEMIBODY LOADFACTOR YDOT.name: SEMIBODY LOADFACTOR YDOT
SEMIBODY LOADFACTOR YDOT.description: Derivative of SEMIBODY LOADFACTOR Y in relation to time.

STALL ALPHA.name: STALL ALPHA
STALL ALPHA.description: The angle of attack which produces the maximum lift coefficient before entering into stall conditions.

STATIC PITCH.name: STATIC PITCH
STATIC PITCH.description: The angle at which static pitch stability is achieved.

TYPICAL DESCENT RATE.name: TYPICAL DESCENT RATE
TYPICAL DESCENT RATE.description: the typical (normal) descent rate for the aircraft.

WING FLEX PCT.name: WING FLEX PCT:index
WING FLEX PCT.description: The current wing flex. Different values can be set for each wing (for example, during banking). Set an index of 1 for the left wing, and 2 for the right wing.

YAW STRING ANGLE.name: YAW STRING ANGLE
YAW STRING ANGLE.description: The yaw string angle. Yaw strings are attached to gliders as visible indicators of the yaw angle. An animation of this is not implemented in ESP.

YAW STRING PCT EXTENDED.name: YAW STRING PCT EXTENDED
YAW STRING PCT EXTENDED.description: Yaw string angle as a percentage

ZERO LIFT ALPHA.name: ZERO LIFT ALPHA
ZERO LIFT ALPHA.description: The angle of attack at which the wing has zero lift.

CG AFT LIMIT.name: CG AFT LIMIT
CG AFT LIMIT.description:
Most backward authorized position of the CG according to the POH.
          NOTE: This is only valid for airplanes.

CG FEET.name: CG FEET
CG FEET.description:
The longitudinal CG position relative to the Reference Datum Position.
          NOTE: This is only valid for helicopters.

CG FEET AFT LIMIT.name: CG FEET AFT LIMIT
CG FEET AFT LIMIT.description:
The aft CG limit position relative to the Reference Datum Position.
          NOTE: This is only valid for helicopters.

CG FEET LATERAL.name: CG FEET LATERAL
CG FEET LATERAL.description:
The lateral CG position relative to the Reference Datum Position.
          NOTE: This is only valid for helicopters.

CG FEET LATERAL LEFT LIMIT.name: CG FEET LATERAL LEFT LIMIT
CG FEET LATERAL LEFT LIMIT.description:
The left hand lateral CG position relative to the Reference Datum Position.
          NOTE: This is only valid for helicopters.

CG FEET LATERAL RIGHT LIMIT.name: CG FEET LATERAL RIGHT LIMIT
CG FEET LATERAL RIGHT LIMIT.description:
The right hand lateral CG position relative to the Reference Datum Position.
          NOTE: This is only valid for helicopters.

CG FEET FWD LIMIT.name: CG FEET FWD LIMIT
CG FEET FWD LIMIT.description:
The forward CG limit position relative to the Reference Datum Position.
          NOTE: This is only valid for helicopters.

CG FWD LIMIT.name: CG FWD LIMIT
CG FWD LIMIT.description:
Most forward authorized position of the CG according to the POH.
          NOTE: This is only valid for airplanes.

CG PERCENT.name: CG PERCENT
CG PERCENT.description:
Longitudinal CG position as a percent of reference Chord.
          NOTE: This is only valid for airplanes.

CG PERCENT LATERAL.name: CG PERCENT LATERAL
CG PERCENT LATERAL.description:
Lateral CG position as a percent of reference Chord.
          NOTE: This is only valid for airplanes.

STATIC CG TO GROUND.name: STATIC CG TO GROUND
STATIC CG TO GROUND.description:
Static CG position with reference to the ground.
          NOTE: This is only valid for airplanes.

INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY LEFT BEND.name: INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY LEFT BEND
INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY LEFT BEND.description: Interactive Point Jetway constant, determining the desired left bend ratio of jetway hood

INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY LEFT DEPLOYMENT.name: INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY LEFT DEPLOYMENT
INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY LEFT DEPLOYMENT.description: Interactive Point Jetway constant, determining the desired left deployment angle of jetway hood

INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY RIGHT BEND.name: INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY RIGHT BEND
INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY RIGHT BEND.description: Interactive Point Jetway constant, determining the desired right bend ratio of jetway hood

INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY RIGHT DEPLOYMEN.name: INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY RIGHT DEPLOYMENT
INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY RIGHT DEPLOYMEN.description: Interactive Point Jetway constant, determining the desired right deployment angle of jetway hood

INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY TOP HORIZONTAL.name: INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY TOP HORIZONTAL
INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY TOP HORIZONTAL.description: Interactive Point Jetway constant, determining the desired top horizontal ratio of displacement of jetway hood

INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY TOP VERTICAL.name: INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY TOP VERTICAL
INTERACTIVE POINT JETWAY TOP VERTICAL.description: Interactive Point Jetway constant, determining the desired top vertical ratio of displacement of jetway hood

INTERACTIVE POINT GOAL.name: INTERACTIVE POINT GOAL
INTERACTIVE POINT GOAL.description: The Interactive Point goal percentage of opening (if it's for a door) or percentage of deployment (if it's for a hose or cable).

INTERACTIVE POINT OPEN.name: INTERACTIVE POINT OPEN
INTERACTIVE POINT OPEN.description: Interactive Point current percentage of opening (if door) or deployment (if hose/cable)

INTERACTIVE POINT POSX.name: INTERACTIVE POINT POSX
INTERACTIVE POINT POSX.description: Interactive Point X position relative to datum reference point

INTERACTIVE POINT POSY.name: INTERACTIVE POINT POSY
INTERACTIVE POINT POSY.description: Interactive Point Y position relative to datum reference point

INTERACTIVE POINT POSZ.name: INTERACTIVE POINT POSZ
INTERACTIVE POINT POSZ.description: Interactive Point Z position relative to datum reference point

INTERACTIVE POINT TYPE.name: INTERACTIVE POINT TYPE
INTERACTIVE POINT TYPE.units:
Enum:
          
            0: Main exit
            1: Cargo exit
            2: Emergency exit
            3: Fuel hose
            4: Ground Power cable
            99: Unknown (for error handling)

EMPTY WEIGHT CROSS COUPLED MOI.description: Empty weight cross coupled moment of inertia

EMPTY WEIGHT YAW MOI.description: Empty weight yaw moment of inertia

MAX GROSS WEIGHT.description: Maximum gross weight of the aircaft

TOTAL WEIGHT CROSS COUPLED MOI.description: Total weight cross coupled moment of inertia

FUEL CROSS FEED.name: FUEL CROSS FEED:index
FUEL CROSS FEED.description: Cross feed valve setting. This will return the current setting for the fuel crossfeed for the indexed engine, based on the current status of the simulation and the Cross Feed key events.
FUEL CROSS FEED.units:
Enum:
          
            0 = Closed
            1 = Open
            2 = Left to Right
            3 = Right to Left

FUEL DUMP ACTIVE.name: FUEL DUMP ACTIVE
FUEL DUMP ACTIVE.description: If 1 (TRUE) then the aircraft can dump fuel.

FUEL DUMP SWITCH.name: FUEL DUMP SWITCH
FUEL DUMP SWITCH.description: If set to 1 (TRUE) then the aircraft will dump fuel at the rate set by fuel_dump_rate parameter in the flight_model.cfg file.

FUEL LEFT CAPACITY.name: FUEL LEFT CAPACITY
FUEL LEFT CAPACITY.description: Maximum capacity in volume of all the tanks on the left side of the aircraft.

FUEL LEFT QUANTITY.name: FUEL LEFT QUANTITY
FUEL LEFT QUANTITY.description: Current quantity in volume of all the tanks on the left side of the aircraft.

FUEL PUMP.name: FUEL PUMP
FUEL PUMP.description: Currently not used within the simulation.

FUEL RIGHT CAPACITY.name: FUEL RIGHT CAPACITY
FUEL RIGHT CAPACITY.description: Maximum capacity in volume of all the tanks on the right side of the aircraft.

FUEL RIGHT QUANTITY.name: FUEL RIGHT QUANTITY
FUEL RIGHT QUANTITY.description: Current quantity in volume of all the tanks on the right side of the aircraft.

FUEL SELECTED QUANTITY.name: FUEL SELECTED QUANTITY:index
FUEL SELECTED QUANTITY.description: Quantity of fuel in the tank referenced by the indexed selector. When using the legacy fuel system, this SimVar will return the quantity of fuel in the tank pointed to by the selector you chose with the index. If passing an index higher than the number of selectors - or when using the modern fuel system - it will return the total fuel quantity available.

FUEL SELECTED QUANTITY PERCENT.name: FUEL SELECTED QUANTITY PERCENT:index
FUEL SELECTED QUANTITY PERCENT.description: Percent or capacity for the tank referenced by the indexed selector. When using the legacy fuel system, this SimVar will return the percentage of fuel in the tank pointed to by the selector you chose with the index. If passing an index higher than the number of selectors available - or when using the modern fuel system - it will return the percentage of total fuel quantity available.

FUEL SELECTED TRANSFER MODE.name: FUEL SELECTED TRANSFER MODE
FUEL SELECTED TRANSFER MODE.description:
The method of transfer for the fuel. Each of the available transfer options are explained below:
          
            off - Fuel transfer is switched off.
            auto - Automatically balance the fuel between the Center1 and Center2 tanks to maintain the center of gravity.
            forward - Fuel will be transferred forwards from the Center1 tank to the Center2 tank.
            aft - Fuel will be transferred aftwards from the Center2 tank to the Center1 tank.
            manual - Fuel will be transferred for 1 second from the Center1 tank to the Center2 tank at a rate of 1lbs/s.
            custom - This requires one or more pumps to have been defined using the fuel_transfer_pump.N parameter in the flight_model.cfg file, as well as their associated electrical circuits.
FUEL SELECTED TRANSFER MODE.units:
Enum:
          
            0 = off
            1 = auto
            2 = forward
            3 = aft
            4 = manual
            5 = custom

FUEL TOTAL CAPACITY.name: FUEL TOTAL CAPACITY
FUEL TOTAL CAPACITY.description: Total fuel capacity of the aircraft for all tanks.

FUEL TOTAL QUANTITY.name: FUEL TOTAL QUANTITY
FUEL TOTAL QUANTITY.description: Current total quantity of fuel in volume for all tanks of the aircraft.

FUEL TOTAL QUANTITY WEIGHT.name: FUEL TOTAL QUANTITY WEIGHT
FUEL TOTAL QUANTITY WEIGHT.description: Current total fuel weight for all tanks of the aircraft

FUEL TRANSFER PUMP ON.name: FUEL TRANSFER PUMP ON:index
FUEL TRANSFER PUMP ON.description: Returns 1 (TRUE) if the indexed pump is active.

FUEL WEIGHT PER GALLON.name: FUEL WEIGHT PER GALLON
FUEL WEIGHT PER GALLON.description: The weight of the fuel, per gallon.

NEW FUEL SYSTEM.name: NEW FUEL SYSTEM
NEW FUEL SYSTEM.description: Will return 1 (TRUE) if the aircraft is using the modern [FUEL_SYSTEM] or 0 (FALSE) for the legacy [FUEL].

NUM FUEL SELECTORS.name: NUM FUEL SELECTORS
NUM FUEL SELECTORS.description: The number of fuel selectors on the aircraft.

UNLIMITED FUEL.name: UNLIMITED FUEL
UNLIMITED FUEL.description: Will return 1 (TRUE) if the unlimited fuel flag has been enabled, or 0 (FALSE) otherwise.

UNUSABLE FUEL TOTAL QUANTITY.name: UNUSABLE FUEL TOTAL QUANTITY
UNUSABLE FUEL TOTAL QUANTITY.description: The total amount of fuel in all tanks of the aircraft which is not usable.

FUELSYSTEM ENGINE PRESSURE.name: FUELSYSTEM ENGINE PRESSURE:index
FUELSYSTEM ENGINE PRESSURE.description: The pressure of the fuel coming to the indexed engine. The index is the number of the engine N component as defined by the Engine.N parameter.

FUELSYSTEM JUNCTION SETTING.name: FUELSYSTEM JUNCTION SETTING:index
FUELSYSTEM JUNCTION SETTING.description: This will return the current Option for the indexed junction. The index is the number of the line N component as defined by the Junction.N parameter.

FUELSYSTEM LINE FUEL FLOW.name: FUELSYSTEM LINE FUEL FLOW:index
FUELSYSTEM LINE FUEL FLOW.description: The fuel flowing through the indexed line in Gallons per Hour. The index is the number of the line N component as defined by the Line.N parameter.

FUELSYSTEM LINE FUEL LEVEL.name: FUELSYSTEM LINE FUEL LEVEL:index
FUELSYSTEM LINE FUEL LEVEL.description: The level of fuel in the indexed line in Gallons. The index is the number of the line N component as defined by the Line.N parameter.

FUELSYSTEM LINE FUEL PRESSURE.name: FUELSYSTEM LINE FUEL PRESSURE:index
FUELSYSTEM LINE FUEL PRESSURE.description: The pressure in the indexed fuel line, measured in KiloPascal. The index is the number of the line N component as defined by the Line.N parameter.

FUELSYSTEM PUMP ACTIVE.name: FUELSYSTEM PUMP ACTIVE:index
FUELSYSTEM PUMP ACTIVE.description: Whether or not the indexed pump is actually active. The index is the number of the pump N component as defined by the Pump.N parameter.

FUELSYSTEM PUMP SWITCH.name: FUELSYSTEM PUMP SWITCH:index
FUELSYSTEM PUMP SWITCH.description: Whether or not the indexed pump is enabled. The index is the number of the pump N component as defined by the Pump.N parameter.

FUELSYSTEM TANK CAPACITY.name: FUELSYSTEM TANK CAPACITY:index
FUELSYSTEM TANK CAPACITY.description:
Total capacity of the indexed fuel tank. The index is the number of the tank N component as defined by the Tank.N parameter.
          NOTE: This SimVar can only be used with the modern Fuel System.

FUELSYSTEM TANK LEVEL.name: FUELSYSTEM TANK LEVEL:index
FUELSYSTEM TANK LEVEL.description:
Quantity of fuel available in the indexed fuel tank. The index is the number of the tank N component as defined by the Tank.N parameter.
          NOTE: This SimVar can only be used with the modern Fuel System.

FUELSYSTEM TANK QUANTITY.name: FUELSYSTEM TANK QUANTITY:index
FUELSYSTEM TANK QUANTITY.description:
Quantity of fuel currently available in the indexed fuel tank. The index is the number of the tank N component as defined by the Tank.N parameter.
          NOTE: If the fuel system Version is 2 or below, the index value will be one of the Fuel Tank Selection indices.

FUELSYSTEM TANK TOTAL QUANTITY.name: FUELSYSTEM TANK TOTAL QUANTITY:index
FUELSYSTEM TANK TOTAL QUANTITY.description:
Total quantity of fuel available in the indexed fuel tank, including any unusable fuel. The index is the number of the tank N component as defined by the Tank.N parameter.
          NOTE: If the fuel system Version is 2 or below, the index value will be one of the Fuel Tank Selection indices.

FUELSYSTEM TANK WEIGHT.name: FUELSYSTEM TANK WEIGHT:index
FUELSYSTEM TANK WEIGHT.description:
Weight of fuel available in the indexed fuel tank. The index is the number of the tank N component as defined by the Tank.N parameter.
          NOTE: If the fuel system Version is 2 or below, the index value will be one of the Fuel Tank Selection indices.

FUELSYSTEM TRIGGER STATUS.name: FUELSYSTEM TRIGGER STATUS:index
FUELSYSTEM TRIGGER STATUS.description: Whether or not the indexed trigger is active. The index is the number of the trigger N component as defined by the Trigger.N parameter.

FUELSYSTEM VALVE OPEN.name: FUELSYSTEM VALVE OPEN:index
FUELSYSTEM VALVE OPEN.description: Whether or not the indexed valve is actually fully opened. The index is the number of the valve N component as defined by the Valve.N parameter.

FUELSYSTEM VALVE SWITCH.name: FUELSYSTEM VALVE SWITCH:index
FUELSYSTEM VALVE SWITCH.description: Whether or not the indexed valve is set to be opened. The index is the number of the valve N component as defined by the Valve.N parameter.

          FUEL TANK CENTER3 CAPACITY

FUEL TANK LEFT MAIN QUANTITY.description: Current quantity in volume of the left main tank.

FUEL TANK LEFT TIP CAPACITY.description: Maximum capacity in volume of the left tip tank.

FUEL TANK LEFT TIP LEVEL.description: Percent of maximum capacity of the left tip tank.

FUEL TANK LEFT TIP QUANTITY.description: Current quantity in volume of the left tip tank.

FUEL TANK RIGHT AUX CAPACITY.description: Maximum capacity in volume of the right auxiliary tank.

FUEL TANK RIGHT AUX LEVEL.description: Percent of maximum capacity of the right auxiliary tank.

FUEL TANK RIGHT AUX QUANTITY.description: Current quantity in volume of the right auxiliary tank.

FUEL TANK RIGHT MAIN CAPACITY.description: Maximum capacity in volume of the right main tank.

FUEL TANK RIGHT MAIN QUANTITY.name: FUEL TANK RIGHT MAIN QUANTITY
FUEL TANK RIGHT MAIN QUANTITY.description: Current quantity in volume of the right main tank.

FUEL TANK RIGHT TIP QUANTITY.description: Current quantity in volume of the right tip tank.

FUEL TANK SELECTOR.description:

AMBIENT IN CLOUD.name: AMBIENT IN CLOUD
AMBIENT IN CLOUD.description: True if the aircraft is in a cloud.

CONTRAILS CONDITIONS MET.name: CONTRAILS CONDITIONS MET
CONTRAILS CONDITIONS MET.description: True if the aircraft has met the conditions required to spawn the contrail VFX.

IS USER SIM.name: IS USER SIM

STRUCTURAL ICE PCT.description: Amount of ice on aircraft structure. 100 is fully iced.

TOW CONNECTION.name: TOW CONNECTION
TOW CONNECTION.description: True if a towline is connected to both tow plane and glider.

WINDSHIELD RAIN EFFECT AVAILABLE.name: WINDSHIELD RAIN EFFECT AVAILABLE
WINDSHIELD RAIN EFFECT AVAILABLE.description: Is visual effect available on this aircraft.

ACCELERATION WORLD Y.name: ACCELERATION WORLD Y

ACCELERATION WORLD Z.name: ACCELERATION WORLD Z
ACCELERATION WORLD Z.description: Acceleration relative to the earth Z axis, in north/south direction.

SURFACE RELATIVE GROUND SPEED.name: SURFACE RELATIVE GROUND SPEED
SURFACE RELATIVE GROUND SPEED.description: The speed of the aircraft relative to the speed of the first surface directly underneath it. Use this to retrieve, for example, an aircraft's taxiing speed while it is moving on a moving carrier. It also applies to airborne aircraft, for example when a helicopter is successfully hovering above a moving ship, this value should be zero. The returned value will be the same as GROUND VELOCITY if the first surface beneath it is not moving.

GROUND VELOCITY.name: GROUND VELOCITY
GROUND VELOCITY.description:
Speed relative to the earths surface.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

PLANE ALT ABOVE GROUND MINUS CG.name: PLANE ALT ABOVE GROUND MINUS CG
PLANE ALT ABOVE GROUND MINUS CG.description: Altitude above the surface minus CG.
PLANE ALT ABOVE GROUND MINUS CG.name_std: PLANE ALT ABOVE GROUND MINUS CG

PLANE BANK DEGREES.name: PLANE BANK DEGREES
PLANE BANK DEGREES.description: Bank angle, although the name mentions degrees the units used are radians.

PLANE HEADING DEGREES MAGNETIC.name: PLANE HEADING DEGREES MAGNETIC
PLANE HEADING DEGREES MAGNETIC.description: Heading relative to magnetic north - although the name mentions degrees the units used are radians.

PLANE HEADING DEGREES TRUE.name: PLANE HEADING DEGREES TRUE
PLANE HEADING DEGREES TRUE.description: Heading relative to true north - although the name mentions degrees the units used are radians.

PLANE LATITUDE.name: PLANE LATITUDE
PLANE LATITUDE.description: Latitude of aircraft, North is positive, South negative.

PLANE LONGITUDE.name: PLANE LONGITUDE
PLANE LONGITUDE.description: Longitude of aircraft, East is positive, West negative.

PLANE PITCH DEGREES.name: PLANE PITCH DEGREES
PLANE PITCH DEGREES.description: Pitch angle, although the name mentions degrees the units used are radians.

PLANE TOUCHDOWN BANK DEGREES.name: PLANE TOUCHDOWN BANK DEGREES
PLANE TOUCHDOWN BANK DEGREES.description: This float represents the bank of the player's plane from the last touchdown.

PLANE TOUCHDOWN HEADING DEGREES MAGNETIC.name: PLANE TOUCHDOWN HEADING DEGREES MAGNETIC
PLANE TOUCHDOWN HEADING DEGREES MAGNETIC.description: This float represents the magnetic heading of the player's plane from the last touchdown.

PLANE TOUCHDOWN HEADING DEGREES TRUE.name: PLANE TOUCHDOWN HEADING DEGREES TRUE
PLANE TOUCHDOWN HEADING DEGREES TRUE.description: This float represents the true heading of the player's plane from the last touchdown.

PLANE TOUCHDOWN LATITUDE.name: PLANE TOUCHDOWN LATITUDE
PLANE TOUCHDOWN LATITUDE.description: This float represents the plane latitude for the last touchdown.

PLANE TOUCHDOWN LONGITUDE.name: PLANE TOUCHDOWN LONGITUDE
PLANE TOUCHDOWN LONGITUDE.description: This float represents the plane longitude for the last touchdown.

PLANE TOUCHDOWN NORMAL VELOCITY.name: PLANE TOUCHDOWN NORMAL VELOCITY
PLANE TOUCHDOWN NORMAL VELOCITY.description: This float represents the player's plane speed according to ground normal from the last touchdown.

PLANE TOUCHDOWN PITCH DEGREES.name: PLANE TOUCHDOWN PITCH DEGREES
PLANE TOUCHDOWN PITCH DEGREES.description: This float represents the pitch of the player's plane from the last touchdown.

RELATIVE WIND VELOCITY BODY X.name: RELATIVE WIND VELOCITY BODY X
RELATIVE WIND VELOCITY BODY X.description: Lateral (X axis) speed relative to wind.

RELATIVE WIND VELOCITY BODY Y.name: RELATIVE WIND VELOCITY BODY Y
RELATIVE WIND VELOCITY BODY Y.description: Vertical (Y axis) speed relative to wind.

RELATIVE WIND VELOCITY BODY Z.name: RELATIVE WIND VELOCITY BODY Z
RELATIVE WIND VELOCITY BODY Z.description: Longitudinal (Z axis) speed relative to wind.

ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY X.name: ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY X
ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY X.description: Rotation acceleration relative to aircraft X axis.

ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY Y.name: ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY Y
ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY Y.description: Rotation acceleration relative to aircraft Y axis.

ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY Z.name: ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY Z
ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY Z.description: Rotation acceleration relative to aircraft Z axis.

ROTATION VELOCITY BODY X.name: ROTATION VELOCITY BODY X
ROTATION VELOCITY BODY X.description: Rotation velocity relative to aircraft X axis.

ROTATION VELOCITY BODY Y.name: ROTATION VELOCITY BODY Y
ROTATION VELOCITY BODY Y.description: Rotation velocity relative to aircraft Y axis.

ROTATION VELOCITY BODY Z.name: ROTATION VELOCITY BODY Z
ROTATION VELOCITY BODY Z.description: Rotation velocity relative to aircraft Z axis.

SLOPE TO ATC RUNWAY.name: SLOPE TO ATC RUNWAY
SLOPE TO ATC RUNWAY.description: The slope between the plane and the expected landing position of the runway. Returns 0 if no runway is assigned.

VELOCITY BODY X.name: VELOCITY BODY X
VELOCITY BODY X.description: True lateral speed, relative to aircraft X axis.

VELOCITY BODY Y.name: VELOCITY BODY Y
VELOCITY BODY Y.description: True vertical speed, relative to aircraft Y axis.

VELOCITY BODY Z.name: VELOCITY BODY Z
VELOCITY BODY Z.description: True longitudinal speed, relative to aircraft Z axis.

VERTICAL SPEED.name: VERTICAL SPEED
VERTICAL SPEED.description: The current indicated vertical speed for the aircraft.

EYEPOINT POSITION.name: EYEPOINT POSITION
EYEPOINT POSITION.description: The eyepoint position relative to the reference datum position for the aircraft.

STRUC AIRSPEED HOLD PID CONSTS.name: STRUC AIRSPEED HOLD PID CONSTS
STRUC AIRSPEED HOLD PID CONSTS.description: Returns the various airspeed PID constants. This is generally only used for AI controlled aircraft and boats, although it may be useful when working with RTCs and the user aircraft.

STRUC HEADING HOLD PID CONSTS.name: STRUC HEADING HOLD PID CONSTS
STRUC HEADING HOLD PID CONSTS.description: Returns the various airspeed PID constants. This is generally only used for AI controlled aircraft and boats, although it may be useful when working with RTCs and the user aircraft.

STRUCT ENGINE POSITION.name: STRUCT ENGINE POSITION:index
STRUCT ENGINE POSITION.description: The position of the indexed engine relative to the Datum Reference Point for the aircraft.

STRUCT EYEPOINT DYNAMIC ANGLE.name: STRUCT EYEPOINT DYNAMIC ANGLE
STRUCT EYEPOINT DYNAMIC ANGLE.description: The angle of the eyepoint view. Zero, zero, zero is straight ahead.

STRUCT EYEPOINT DYNAMIC OFFSET.name: STRUCT EYEPOINT DYNAMIC OFFSET
STRUCT EYEPOINT DYNAMIC OFFSET.description: A variable offset away from the EYEPOINT POSITION.

STRUCT LATLONALT.name: STRUCT LATLONALT
STRUCT LATLONALT.description: Returns the latitude, longitude and altitude of the user aircraft.

STRUCT LATLONALTPBH.name: STRUCT LATLONALTPBH
STRUCT LATLONALTPBH.description: Returns the lattitude, longitude, altitude, pitch, bank and heading of the user aircraft.
STRUCT LATLONALTPBH.units: Returns a struct with 6 values: lat, lon, alt, pitch, bank, heading

AIRCRAFT WIND X.name: AIRCRAFT WIND X
AIRCRAFT WIND X.description: Wind component in aircraft lateral (X) axis.

AIRCRAFT WIND Y.name: AIRCRAFT WIND Y
AIRCRAFT WIND Y.description: Wind component in aircraft vertical (Y) axis.

AIRCRAFT WIND Z.name: AIRCRAFT WIND Z
AIRCRAFT WIND Z.description: Wind component in aircraft longitudinal (Z) axis.

AIRSPEED SELECT INDICATED OR TRUE.name: AIRSPEED SELECT INDICATED OR TRUE
AIRSPEED SELECT INDICATED OR TRUE.description: The airspeed, whether true or indicated airspeed has been selected.

AIRSPEED TRUE RAW.name: AIRSPEED TRUE RAW
AIRSPEED TRUE RAW.description: Equivalent to AIRSPEED TRUE, but does not account for wind when used to Set Airspeed value

TOTAL VELOCITY.name: TOTAL VELOCITY
TOTAL VELOCITY.description: Velocity regardless of direction. For example, if a helicopter is ascending vertically at 100 fps, getting this variable will return 100.

WINDSHIELD WIND VELOCITY.name: WINDSHIELD WIND VELOCITY
WINDSHIELD WIND VELOCITY.description: Longitudinal speed of wind on the windshield.

STANDARD ATM TEMPERATURE.name: STANDARD ATM TEMPERATURE
STANDARD ATM TEMPERATURE.description: Outside temperature on the standard ATM scale.

TOTAL AIR TEMPERATURE.name: TOTAL AIR TEMPERATURE
TOTAL AIR TEMPERATURE.description: Total air temperature is the air temperature at the front of the aircraft where the ram pressure from the speed of the aircraft is taken into account.

ADF LATLONALT.name: ADF LATLONALT:index
ADF LATLONALT.description: Returns the latitude, longitude and altitude of the station the radio equipment is currently tuned to, or zeros if the radio is not tuned to any ADF station. Index of 1 or 2 for ADF 1 and ADF 2.

ADF RADIAL MAG.name: ADF RADIAL MAG:index
ADF RADIAL MAG.description: Returns the magnetic bearing to the currently tuned ADF transmitter.

ADF SOUND.name: ADF SOUND:index
ADF SOUND.description: ADF audio flag. Index of 0 or 1.

ADF STANDBY AVAILABLE.name: ADF STANDBY AVAILABLE:index
ADF STANDBY AVAILABLE.description: True if ADF Standby is available

ADF VOLUME.name: ADF VOLUME
ADF VOLUME.description: Returns the volume of the ADF

ATC AIRLINE.name: ATC AIRLINE
ATC AIRLINE.description: The name of the Airline used by ATC, as a string with a maximum length of 50 characters.

ATC AIRPORT IS TOWERED.name: ATC AIRPORT IS TOWERED
ATC AIRPORT IS TOWERED.description: If the airport is controlled, this boolean is true.

ATC CLEARED IFR.name: ATC CLEARED IFR
ATC CLEARED IFR.description: Returns whether or not the user has filed an IFR flightplan that has been cleared by the sim ATC

ATC CLEARED LANDING.name: ATC CLEARED LANDING
ATC CLEARED LANDING.description: Whether the ATC has cleared the plane for landing.

ATC CLEARED TAKEOFF.name: ATC CLEARED TAKEOFF
ATC CLEARED TAKEOFF.description: Whether the ATC has cleared the plane for takeoff.

ATC CLEARED TAXI.name: ATC CLEARED TAXI
ATC CLEARED TAXI.description: Whether the ATC has cleared the plane for taxi.

ATC CURRENT WAYPOINT ALTITUDE.name: ATC CURRENT WAYPOINT ALTITUDE
ATC CURRENT WAYPOINT ALTITUDE.description: Returns the target altitude for the current ATC flightplan waypoint.

ATC FLIGHT NUMBER.name: ATC FLIGHT NUMBER
ATC FLIGHT NUMBER.description: Flight Number used by ATC, as a string with a maximum number of 6 characters.

ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF ALT.name: ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF ALT
ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF ALT.description: Altitude between the position of the aircraft and his closest waypoints in the flightplan.

ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF DISTANCE.name: ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF DISTANCE
ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF DISTANCE.description: Returns the lateral distance the user's plane is from the ATC flight plan track.

ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF HEADING.name: ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF HEADING
ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF HEADING.description: Heading between the position of the aircraft and his closest waypoints in the flightplan.

ATC HEAVY.name: ATC HEAVY
ATC HEAVY.description: Is this aircraft recognized by ATC as heavy.

ATC ID.name: ATC ID
ATC ID.description: ID used by ATC, as a string with a maximum number of 10 characters.

ATC IFR FP TO REQUEST.name: ATC IFR FP TO REQUEST
ATC IFR FP TO REQUEST.description: Returns true if the user has a valid IFR flight plan they can as for clearance for with ATC at the airport they are currently at.

ATC MODEL.name: ATC MODEL
ATC MODEL.description: Model used by ATC, as a string with a maximum number of 10 characters.

ATC ON PARKING SPOT.name: ATC ON PARKING SPOT
ATC ON PARKING SPOT.description: Is ATC aircraft on parking spot.

ATC PREVIOUS WAYPOINT ALTITUDE.name: ATC PREVIOUS WAYPOINT ALTITUDE
ATC PREVIOUS WAYPOINT ALTITUDE.description: Returns the target altitude for the previous ATC flightplan waypoint.

ATC RUNWAY AIRPORT NAME.name: ATC RUNWAY AIRPORT NAME
ATC RUNWAY AIRPORT NAME.description: The name of the airport of the runway assigned by the ATC. Returns "" if no runway is assigned.

ATC RUNWAY DISTANCE.name: ATC RUNWAY DISTANCE
ATC RUNWAY DISTANCE.description: This float represents the distance between the player's plane and the center of the runway selected by the ATC.

ATC RUNWAY END DISTANCE.name: ATC RUNWAY END DISTANCE
ATC RUNWAY END DISTANCE.description: This is a float corresponding to the horizontal distance between the player's plane and the end of the runway selected by the ATC.

ATC RUNWAY HEADING DEGREES TRUE.name: ATC RUNWAY HEADING DEGREES TRUE
ATC RUNWAY HEADING DEGREES TRUE.description: This float represents the true heading of the runway selected by the ATC.

ATC RUNWAY LENGTH.name: ATC RUNWAY LENGTH
ATC RUNWAY LENGTH.description: The length of the runway assigned by the ATC. Returns -1 if no runway is assigned.

ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION X.name: ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION X
ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION X.description: This is a float corresponding to the player's main gear relative X (transverse) position on the runway selected by the ATC.

ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION Y.name: ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION Y
ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION Y.description: This is a float corresponding to the player's main gear relative Y (height) position on the runway selected by the ATC.

ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION Z.name: ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION Z
ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION Z.description: This is a float corresponding to the player's main gear relative Z (longitudinal) position on the runway selected by the ATC.

ATC RUNWAY SELECTED.name: ATC RUNWAY SELECTED
ATC RUNWAY SELECTED.description: This is a boolean corresponding to whether or not the ATC has pre-selected a runway for the player's plane. If this is false, every other ATC RUNWAY * SimVar will return default values.

ATC RUNWAY START DISTANCE.name: ATC RUNWAY START DISTANCE
ATC RUNWAY START DISTANCE.description: This is a float corresponding to the horizontal distance between the player's plane and the start of the runway selected by the ATC.

ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION X.name: ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION X
ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION X.description: This float represents the player's main gear relative X (transverse) position according to the aiming point of the runway selected by the ATC.
ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION X.name_std: ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION X

ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Y.name: ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Y
ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Y.description: This float represents the player's main gear relative Y (height) position according to the aiming point of the runway selected by the ATC.
ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Y.name_std: ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Y

ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Z.name: ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Z
ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Z.description: This float represents the player's main relative Z (longitudinal) position according to the aiming point of the runway selected by the ATC.
ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Z.name_std: ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Z

ATC RUNWAY WIDTH.name: ATC RUNWAY WIDTH
ATC RUNWAY WIDTH.description: The width of the runway assigned by the ATC. Returns -1 if no runway is assigned.

ATC SUGGESTED MIN RWY LANDING.name: ATC SUGGESTED MIN RWY LANDING
ATC SUGGESTED MIN RWY LANDING.description: Suggested minimum runway length for landing. Used by ATC.

ATC SUGGESTED MIN RWY TAKEOFF.name: ATC SUGGESTED MIN RWY TAKEOFF
ATC SUGGESTED MIN RWY TAKEOFF.description: Suggested minimum runway length for takeoff. Used by ATC.

ATC TAXIPATH DISTANCE.name: ATC TAXIPATH DISTANCE
ATC TAXIPATH DISTANCE.description: Returns the lateral distance the user's plane is from the path of the currently issued ATC taxi instructions.

COM1 STORED FREQUENCY.name: COM1 STORED FREQUENCY
COM1 STORED FREQUENCY.description:
The stored COM 1/2/3 frequency value.  COM2 STORED FREQUENCY
          COM3 STORED FREQUENCY

COM ACTIVE BEARING.name: COM ACTIVE BEARING:index
COM ACTIVE BEARING.description: Gives the bearing (in degrees) of the active COM station (airport) or a value less than 0 if the station does not belong to an airport. Index is 1, 2 or 3.

COM ACTIVE DISTANCE.name: COM ACTIVE DISTANCE:index
COM ACTIVE DISTANCE.description: Gives the distance (in meters) to the active COM station (airport) or a value less than -180° if the station does not belong to an airport. Index is 1, 2 or 3.

COM ACTIVE FREQ IDENT.name: COM ACTIVE FREQ IDENT:index
COM ACTIVE FREQ IDENT.description: The identity of the station that is tuned on the indexed active COM radio. Index is 1, 2, or 3.

COM ACTIVE FREQ TYPE.name: COM ACTIVE FREQ TYPE:index
COM ACTIVE FREQ TYPE.description: The type of COM frequency for the active indexed COM system. Index is 1, 2, or 3.
COM ACTIVE FREQ TYPE.units:
String:
          
            "ATIS" - Atis
            "UNI" - Unicom
            "CTAF" - CTAF
            "GND" - Ground
            "TWR" - Tower
            "CLR" - Clearance
              
              Delivery
            
            "APPR" - Approach
            "DEP" - Departure
            "FSS" - FSS
            "AWS" - AWOS

COM ACTIVE LATLONALT.name: COM ACTIVE LATLONALT:index
COM ACTIVE LATLONALT.description:
This will return the latitude, longitude and altitude corresponding to the indexed COM station associated with the active COM frequency. If the station is not associated with an airport, then the lat/lon/alt values returned will be -15943°, 80°, -10000 (this means that you can simply check that the altitude value is greater than 0 to assure the validity of the returned struct).
          Index is 1, 2 or 3.

COM AVAILABLE.name: COM AVAILABLE:index
COM AVAILABLE.description: True if COM1, COM2 or COM3 is available (depending on the index, either 1, 2, or 3)

COM LATLONALT.name: COM LATLONALT:index
COM LATLONALT.description: Not currently used in the simulation.

COM RECEIVE.name: COM RECEIVE:index
COM RECEIVE.description: Whether or not the plane is receiving on the indexed com channel or not (either 1, 2, or 3 for the index).

COM RECEIVE ALL.name: COM RECEIVE ALL
COM RECEIVE ALL.description: Toggles all COM radios to receive on

COM RECEIVE EX1.name: COM RECEIVE EX1:index
COM RECEIVE EX1.description: Whether or not the plane is receiving on the indexed com channel. Index is 1, 2 or 3.

COM SPACING MODE.name: COM SPACING MODE:index
COM SPACING MODE.description: The COM radio frequency step. Index is 1, 2 or 3.

COM STANDBY FREQUENCY.name: COM STANDBY FREQUENCY:index
COM STANDBY FREQUENCY.description: Com standby frequency. Index is 1, 2 or 3.

COM STANDBY FREQ IDENT.name: COM STANDBY FREQ IDENT:index
COM STANDBY FREQ IDENT.description: The identity of the station that is tuned on the indexed standby COM radio. Index is 1, 2, or 3.

COM STANDBY FREQ TYPE.name: COM STANDBY FREQ TYPE:index
COM STANDBY FREQ TYPE.description: The type of COM frequency for the standby indexed COM system. Index is 1, 2, or 3.
COM STANDBY FREQ TYPE.units:
String:
          
            "ATIS" - Atis
            "UNI" - Unicom
            "CTAF" - CTAF
            "GND" - Ground
            "TWR" - Tower
            "CLR" - Clearance
              
              Delivery
            
            "APPR" - Approach
            "DEP" - Departure
            "FSS" - FSS
            "AWS" - AWOS

COM STATUS.name: COM STATUS:index
COM STATUS.description: Radio status flag for the indexed com channel. Index is 1, 2 or 3.
COM STATUS.units:
Enum:
          
            -1 = Invalid
            0 = OK
            1 = Does not exist
            2 = No electricity
            3 = Failed

COM TEST.name: COM TEST:index
COM TEST.description: Enter an index of 1, 2 or 3. Will return TRUE if the COM system is working, FALSE otherwise.

COM TRANSMIT.name: COM TRANSMIT:index
COM TRANSMIT.description: Audio panel com transmit state. Index of 1, 2 or 3.

COM VOLUME.name: COM VOLUME
COM VOLUME.description: The volume of the COM Radio.

FLARM AVAILABLE.name: FLARM AVAILABLE
FLARM AVAILABLE.description: Whether the FLARM is available (TRUE, 1) or not (FALSE, 0).

FLARM THREAT BEARING.name: FLARM THREAT BEARING
FLARM THREAT BEARING.description: The bearing of the FLARM threat aircraft, relative to track.

FLARM THREAT DATA.name: FLARM THREAT DATA
FLARM THREAT DATA.description:
The FLARM threat aircraft data structure, which contains data about the perceived threat, returned as a struct. Struct member variables are as follows:
          
            id (U62): the network id of the intruding plane so that they are remembered in order to compute their trajectory.
            bearing (FLOAT64): The threat bearing, in degrees (this is bearing from track axis and not bearing from the airplane axis).
            heading (FLOAT64): The threat heading.
            distance (FLOAT64): The distance between the aircraft and the threat, in meters.
            verticalBearing (FLOAT64): The vertical bearing between the aircraft and the threat, in degrees.
            relativeAltitude (FLOAT64): The relative altitude of the threat to the aircraft, in meters.
            timeToCollision (FLOAT64): The estimated time to a collision, in seconds.

FLARM THREAT DISTANCE.name: FLARM THREAT DISTANCE
FLARM THREAT DISTANCE.description: The distance to the FLARM threat object.

FLARM THREAT HEADING.name: FLARM THREAT HEADING
FLARM THREAT HEADING.description: The heading to the FLARM threat object.

FLARM THREAT RELATIVE ALTITUDE.name: FLARM THREAT RELATIVE ALTITUDE
FLARM THREAT RELATIVE ALTITUDE.description: The relative altitude of the threat object.

FLARM THREAT TIME TO COLLISION.name: FLARM THREAT TIME TO COLLISION
FLARM THREAT TIME TO COLLISION.description: The estimated time to a collision.

FLARM THREAT VERTICAL BEARING.name: FLARM THREAT VERTICAL BEARING
FLARM THREAT VERTICAL BEARING.description: The vertical bearing towards the threat.

GPS APPROACH APPROACH INDEX.name: GPS APPROACH APPROACH INDEX
GPS APPROACH APPROACH INDEX.description: Index of approach for given airport.

GPS APPROACH APPROACH TYPE.name: GPS APPROACH APPROACH TYPE
GPS APPROACH APPROACH TYPE.units:
Enum:
          
            0 = None
            1 = GPS
            2 = VOR
            3 = NDB
            4 = ILS
            5 = Localizer
            6 = SDF
            7 = LDA
            8 = VOR/ DME
            9 = NDB/ DME
            10 = RNAV
            11 = Backcourse

GPS APPROACH IS FINAL.name: GPS APPROACH IS FINAL
GPS APPROACH IS FINAL.description: Is approach transition final approach segment.

GPS APPROACH IS MISSED.name: GPS APPROACH IS MISSED
GPS APPROACH IS MISSED.description: Is approach segment missed approach segment.

GPS APPROACH SEGMENT TYPE.name: GPS APPROACH SEGMENT TYPE
GPS APPROACH SEGMENT TYPE.units:
Enum:
          
            0 = Line
            1 = Arc clockwise
            2 = Arc counter-clockwise

GPS APPROACH TIMEZONE DEVIATION.name: GPS APPROACH TIMEZONE DEVIATION
GPS APPROACH TIMEZONE DEVIATION.description: Deviation of local time from GMT.

GPS APPROACH WP TYPE.name: GPS APPROACH WP TYPE
GPS APPROACH WP TYPE.units:
Enum:
          
            0 = None
            1 = Fix
            2 = Procedure turn left
            3 = Procedure turn right
            4 = Dme arc left
            5 = Dme arc right
            6 = Holding left
            7 = Holding right
            8 = Distance
            9 = Altitude
            10 = Manual sequence
            11 = Vector to final

GPS CDI NEEDLE.name: GPS CDI NEEDLE
GPS CDI NEEDLE.description: The course deviation of the needle for a CDI instrument. The SimVar displays the deviation from -127 to +127. It returns a value if a flight plan is set (otherwise it will return 0) even if the autopilot isn't on GPS mode. Scaling can also be set through the GPS CDI SCALING simvar.

GPS CDI SCALING.name: GPS CDI SCALING
GPS CDI SCALING.description: The full scale deflection of the CDI due to GPS cross-track error, in meters.

GPS DRIVES NAV1.name: GPS DRIVES NAV1
GPS DRIVES NAV1.description: GPS is driving Nav 1 indicator. Note this setting will also affect the SimVars HSI_STATION_IDENT and HSI_BEARING.

GPS ETA.name: GPS ETA
GPS ETA.description: Estimated time of arrival at destination.

GPS ETE.name: GPS ETE
GPS ETE.description: Estimated time en route to destination.

GPS FLIGHTPLAN TOTAL DISTANCE.name: GPS FLIGHTPLAN TOTAL DISTANCE
GPS FLIGHTPLAN TOTAL DISTANCE.description: This is the complete flightplan length from start to end. Essentially the cumulative length of all the flight plan legs added together.

GPS GSI SCALING.name: GPS GSI SCALING
GPS GSI SCALING.description: The full scale deflection of the vertical GSI due to GPS glidepath deviation, in meters.

GPS HAS GLIDEPATH.name: GPS HAS GLIDEPATH
GPS HAS GLIDEPATH.description: Whether or not the GPS system has a presently available glidepath for guidance. Only applicable with GPS_OVERRIDDEN. When true and in GPS OVERRIDDEN, HSI_GSI_NEEDLE_VALID will also be true.

GPS HSI NEEDLE.name: GPS HSI NEEDLE
GPS HSI NEEDLE.description: The glide deviation of the needle for a CDI instrument. The simvar displays the deviation from -127 to +127. It returns a value if a flight plan is set (otherwise it will return 0) even if the autopilot isn't on GPS mode. Scaling can also be set through the GPS CDI SCALING simvar.

GPS IS ACTIVE WP LOCKED.name: GPS IS ACTIVE WP LOCKED
GPS IS ACTIVE WP LOCKED.description: Is switching to next waypoint locked.

GPS IS DIRECTTO FLIGHTPLAN.name: GPS IS DIRECTTO FLIGHTPLAN
GPS IS DIRECTTO FLIGHTPLAN.description: Is Direct To Waypoint mode active.

GPS OBS ACTIVE.name: GPS OBS ACTIVE
GPS OBS ACTIVE.description: Whether or not the OBS mode is currently active (disable the automatic sequencing of waypoints in GPS flight plan).

GPS OBS VALUE.name: GPS OBS VALUE
GPS OBS VALUE.description: This is the currently selected OBS course in degrees, from 0 to 360.

GPS OVERRIDDEN.name: GPS OVERRIDDEN
GPS OVERRIDDEN.description: When it is active, all sim GPS system updates are suspended. This must be set to TRUE to be able to correctly set to any other GPS SimVar.

GPS VERTICAL ANGLE ERROR.name: GPS VERTICAL ANGLE ERROR
GPS VERTICAL ANGLE ERROR.description: Vertical error in degrees from GlidePath.

GPS VERTICAL ERROR.name: GPS VERTICAL ERROR
GPS VERTICAL ERROR.description: Vertical deviation in meters from GlidePath.

GPS WP DESIRED TRACK.name: GPS WP DESIRED TRACK
GPS WP DESIRED TRACK.description: The required heading (magnetic) from the previous waypoint to the next waypoint.

GPS WP ETA.name: GPS WP ETA
GPS WP ETA.description: Estimated time of arrival at waypoint.

GPS WP ETE.name: GPS WP ETE
GPS WP ETE.description: Estimated time en route to waypoint.

GPS WP PREV VALID.name: GPS WP PREV VALID
GPS WP PREV VALID.description: Is previous waypoint valid (i.e. current waypoint is not the first waypoint).

HSI BEARING.name: HSI BEARING
HSI BEARING.description: If the GPS_DRIVES_NAV1 variable is true and the HSI BEARING VALID variable is true, this variable contains the HSI needle bearing. If the GPS DRIVES NAV1 variable is false and the HSI BEARING VALID variable is true, this variable contains the ADF1 frequency.

HSI BEARING VALID.name: HSI BEARING VALID
HSI BEARING VALID.description: This will return true if the HSI BEARING variable contains valid data.

HSI STATION IDENT.name: HSI STATION IDENT
HSI STATION IDENT.description: Returns the ident of the the next GPS waypoint, if GPS_DRIVES_NAV1 is true. If GPS DRIVES NAV1 is false, it returns the identity of the station that is tuned on nav radio 1.

INNER MARKER LATLONALT.name: INNER MARKER LATLONALT
INNER MARKER LATLONALT.description: Returns the latitude, longitude and altitude of the inner marker of an approach to a runway, if the aircraft is within the required proximity, otherwise it will return zeros.

MARKER BEACON SENSITIVITY HIGH.name: MARKER BEACON SENSITIVITY HIGH
MARKER BEACON SENSITIVITY HIGH.description: Whether or not the Marker Beacon is in High Sensitivity mode.

MARKER BEACON TEST MUTE.name: MARKER BEACON TEST MUTE
MARKER BEACON TEST MUTE.description: Whether or not the Marker Beacon is in Test/Mute mode.

MIDDLE MARKER LATLONALT.name: MIDDLE MARKER LATLONALT
MIDDLE MARKER LATLONALT.description: Returns the latitude, longitude and altitude of the middle marker.

OUTER MARKER LATLONALT.name: OUTER MARKER LATLONALT
OUTER MARKER LATLONALT.description: Returns the latitude, longitude and altitude of the outer marker.

NAV ACTIVE FREQUENCY.name: NAV ACTIVE FREQUENCY:index
NAV ACTIVE FREQUENCY.description: Nav active frequency. Index is 1 or 2.

NAV AVAILABLE.name: NAV AVAILABLE:index
NAV AVAILABLE.description: Flag if Nav equipped on aircraft.

NAV BACK COURSE FLAGS.name: NAV BACK COURSE FLAGS:index
NAV BACK COURSE FLAGS.units:
Flags:
          
            BIT0:[index] 1=back course available
            BIT1:[index] 1=localizer tuned in
            BIT2:[index] 1=on course
            BIT7:[index] 1=station active

NAV CLOSE DME.name: NAV CLOSE DME:index
NAV CLOSE DME.description:
Closest DME distance. Requires an index value from 1 to 4 to set which NAV to target.
          Note that this SimVar will only work if the NAV1_CLOSE_FREQ_SET key event has been set to 1 (TRUE).

NAV CLOSE FREQUENCY.name: NAV CLOSE FREQUENCY:index
NAV CLOSE FREQUENCY.description:
Closest Localizer course frequency. Requires an index value from 1 to 4 to set which NAV to target.
          Note that this SimVar will only work if the NAV1_CLOSE_FREQ_SET key event has been set to 1 (TRUE).

NAV CLOSE IDENT.name: NAV CLOSE IDENT:index
NAV CLOSE IDENT.description:
ICAO code. Requires an index value from 1 to 4 to set which NAV to target.
          Note that this SimVar will only work if the NAV1_CLOSE_FREQ_SET key event has been set to 1 (TRUE).

NAV CLOSE LOCALIZER.name: NAV CLOSE LOCALIZER:index
NAV CLOSE LOCALIZER.description:
Closest Localizer course heading. Requires an index value from 1 to 4 to set which NAV to target.
          Note that this SimVar will only work if the NAV1_CLOSE_FREQ_SET key event has been set to 1 (TRUE).

NAV CLOSE NAME.name: NAV CLOSE NAME:index
NAV CLOSE NAME.description:
Descriptive name. Requires an index value from 1 to 4 to set which NAV to target.
          Note that this SimVar will only work if the NAV1_CLOSE_FREQ_SET key event has been set to 1 (TRUE).

NAV CODES.name: NAV CODES
NAV CODES.description: Returns bit flags with the listed meaning.
NAV CODES.units:
Flags:
          
            BIT7:[index] 0= VOR 1= Localizer
            BIT6:[index] 1= glideslope available
            BIT5:[index] 1= no localizer backcourse
            BIT4:[index] 1= DME transmitter at glide slope
              
              transmitter
            
            BIT3:[index] 1= no nav signal available
            BIT2:[index] 1= voice available
            BIT1:[index] 1 = TACAN available
            BIT0:[index] 1= DME available

NAV GLIDE SLOPE.name: NAV GLIDE SLOPE
NAV GLIDE SLOPE.description:
The glide slope gradient. The value returned is an integer value formed as follows:
          sin(slope) * 65536 * 2
          So, for example, a glide slope of 2.7o would return a value of 6174. TO get the value in degrees, then use NAV_RAW_GLIDE_SLOPE instead.

NAV GLIDE SLOPE ERROR.name: NAV GLIDE SLOPE ERROR
NAV GLIDE SLOPE ERROR.description: Difference between current position and glideslope angle. Note that this provides 32 bit floating point precision, rather than the 8 bit integer precision of NAV GSI.

NAV GLIDE SLOPE LENGTH.name: NAV GLIDE SLOPE LENGTH
NAV GLIDE SLOPE LENGTH.description: The distance between the plane and the Glide beacon.

NAV GSI.name: NAV GSI
NAV GSI.description: Glideslope needle deflection (+/- 119). Note that this provides only 8 bit precision, whereas NAV GLIDE SLOPE ERROR provides 32 bit floating point precision.

NAV HAS CLOSE DME.name: NAV HAS CLOSE DME
NAV HAS CLOSE DME.description: Flag if found a close station with a DME.

NAV HAS CLOSE LOCALIZER.name: NAV HAS CLOSE LOCALIZER
NAV HAS CLOSE LOCALIZER.description: Flag if found a close localizer station.

NAV HAS DME.name: NAV HAS DME
NAV HAS DME.description: Flag if tuned station has a DME.

NAV HAS GLIDE SLOPE.name: NAV HAS GLIDE SLOPE
NAV HAS GLIDE SLOPE.description: Flag if tuned station has a glideslope.

NAV HAS LOCALIZER.name: NAV HAS LOCALIZER
NAV HAS LOCALIZER.description: Flag if tuned station is a localizer.

NAV HAS TACAN.name: NAV HAS TACAN
NAV HAS TACAN.description: Flag if Nav has a Tacan.

NAV LOC AIRPORT IDENT.name: NAV LOC AIRPORT IDENT
NAV LOC AIRPORT IDENT.description: The airport ICAO ident for the localizer that is currently tuned on the nav radio (like 'EGLL' or 'KJFK')

NAV LOC RUNWAY DESIGNATOR.name: NAV LOC RUNWAY DESIGNATOR
NAV LOC RUNWAY DESIGNATOR.description: The letter code for the runway that the currently tuned localizer is tuned to.
NAV LOC RUNWAY DESIGNATOR.units:
String
          
            'L' - Left
            'R' - Right
            'C' - Center
            'W' - Water
            'A' - A
            'B' - B

NAV LOC RUNWAY NUMBER.name: NAV LOC RUNWAY NUMBER
NAV LOC RUNWAY NUMBER.description: NAV LOC RUNWAY NUMBER - The number portion of the runway that the currently tuned localizer is tuned to (so if the runway was 15L, this would be 15).

NAV MAGVAR.name: NAV MAGVAR
NAV MAGVAR.description: Magnetic variation of tuned Nav station.

NAV RADIAL ERROR.name: NAV RADIAL ERROR
NAV RADIAL ERROR.description: Difference between current radial and OBS tuned radial.

NAV SOUND.name: NAV SOUND:index
NAV SOUND.description: Nav audio flag. Index of 1 or 2.

NAV STANDBY FREQUENCY.name: NAV STANDBY FREQUENCY:index
NAV STANDBY FREQUENCY.description: Nav standby frequency. Index is 1 or 2.

NAV TOFROM.name: NAV TOFROM
NAV TOFROM.description: Returns whether the Nav is going to or from the current radial (or is off).

NAV VOLUME.name: NAV VOLUME
NAV VOLUME.description: The volume of the Nav radio.

NAV VOR LATLONALT.name: NAV VOR LATLONALT:index
NAV VOR LATLONALT.description: Returns the VOR station latitude, longitude and altitude.

TACAN ACTIVE CHANNEL.name: TACAN ACTIVE CHANNEL:index
TACAN ACTIVE CHANNEL.description: The active channel used by the indexed Tacan receiver on the aircraft, from 1 to 127.

TACAN ACTIVE MODE.name: TACAN ACTIVE MODE:index
TACAN ACTIVE MODE.description: The active mode used by the indexed Tacan receiver on the aircraft, where 0 = X and 1 = Y.

TACAN AVAILABLE.name: TACAN AVAILABLE:index
TACAN AVAILABLE.description: Will be TRUE (1) if NAV1, NAV2, NAV3 or NAV4 can receive Tacan (depending on the index - 1, 2, 3, or 4), or FALSE (0) otherwise.

TACAN DRIVES NAV1.name: TACAN DRIVES NAV1:index
TACAN DRIVES NAV1.description: Tells whether the Tacan is driving the Nav 1 indicator (TRUE, 1) or not (FALSE, 0), for autopilot purposes.

TACAN OBS.name: TACAN OBS:index
TACAN OBS.description: The Tacan OBS setting, in degrees.

TACAN STANDBY CHANNEL.name: TACAN STANDBY CHANNEL:index
TACAN STANDBY CHANNEL.description: The standby channel used by the indexed Tacan receiver on the aircraft, from 1 to 127.

TACAN STANDBY MODE.name: TACAN STANDBY MODE:index
TACAN STANDBY MODE.description: Indicates the indexed Tacan receiver standby mode, where 0 = X and 1 = Y.

TACAN STATION CDI.name: TACAN STATION CDI:index
