TACAN STATION CDI.description: The CDI needle deflection amount(course deviation) to the station. Can be +/- 127.

TACAN STATION DISTANCE.name: TACAN STATION DISTANCE:index
TACAN STATION DISTANCE.description: The distance between the Tacan station position and the aircraft position. The index value refers to the Tacan receiver connected to the station (1 or 2).

TACAN STATION IDENT.name: TACAN STATION IDENT:index
TACAN STATION IDENT.description: The tuned station identifier for the indexed Tacan.

TACAN STATION LATLONALT.name: TACAN STATION LATLONALT:index
TACAN STATION LATLONALT.description: Retrieves the latitude, longitude and altitude of the Tacan station.

TACAN STATION RADIAL.name: TACAN STATION RADIAL:index
TACAN STATION RADIAL.description: The radial between the Tacan station and the aircraft.

TACAN STATION RADIAL ERROR.name: TACAN STATION RADIAL ERROR:index
TACAN STATION RADIAL ERROR.description: Difference between the current radial and OBS tuned radial, in degrees.

TACAN STATION TOFROM.name: TACAN STATION TOFROM:index
TACAN STATION TOFROM.description: Returns whether the indexed Tacan is going to or from the current radial (or is off).

TACAN VOLUME.name: TACAN VOLUME:index
TACAN VOLUME.description: The volume value of the indexed Tacan receiver on the aircraft.

AIRSPEED TRUE CALIBRATE.name: AIRSPEED TRUE CALIBRATE
AIRSPEED TRUE CALIBRATE.description: Angle of True calibration scale on airspeed indicator.

ANNUNCIATOR SWITCH.name: ANNUNCIATOR SWITCH
ANNUNCIATOR SWITCH.description: Currently not used in the simulation.

APPLY HEAT TO SYSTEMS.name: APPLY HEAT TO SYSTEMS
APPLY HEAT TO SYSTEMS.description: Used when too close to a fire.

AUDIO PANEL AVAILABLE.name: AUDIO PANEL AVAILABLE
AUDIO PANEL AVAILABLE.description: True if the audio panel is available.

AUDIO PANEL VOLUME.name: AUDIO PANEL VOLUME
AUDIO PANEL VOLUME.description: The Volume of the Audio Panel.

AVIONICS MASTER SWITCH.name: AVIONICS MASTER SWITCH:index
AVIONICS MASTER SWITCH.description: The avionics master switch position, true if the switch is ON. Use an avionics circuit index when referencing.

CABIN NO SMOKING ALERT SWITCH.name: CABIN NO SMOKING ALERT SWITCH
CABIN NO SMOKING ALERT SWITCH.description: True if the No Smoking switch is on.

CABIN SEATBELTS ALERT SWITCH.name: CABIN SEATBELTS ALERT SWITCH
CABIN SEATBELTS ALERT SWITCH.description: True if the Seatbelts switch is on.

DELTA HEADING RATE.name: DELTA HEADING RATE
DELTA HEADING RATE.description: Rate of turn of heading indicator.

ELT ACTIVATED.name: ELT ACTIVATED
ELT ACTIVATED.description: Whether or not the Emergency Locator Transmitter is active.

FIRE BOTTLE DISCHARGED.name: FIRE BOTTLE DISCHARGED
FIRE BOTTLE DISCHARGED.description: True if the fire bottle is discharged.

FIRE BOTTLE SWITCH.name: FIRE BOTTLE SWITCH
FIRE BOTTLE SWITCH.description: True if the fire bottle switch is on.

GLASSCOCKPIT AUTOMATIC BRIGHTNESS.name: GLASSCOCKPIT AUTOMATIC BRIGHTNESS
GLASSCOCKPIT AUTOMATIC BRIGHTNESS.description: This variable will return a value between 0 and 1 for the automatic brightness setting for glass cockpit displays, where 0 is the dimmest and 1 is the brightest. This value will vary depending on the time of day.

GPWS SYSTEM ACTIVE.name: GPWS SYSTEM ACTIVE
GPWS SYSTEM ACTIVE.description: True if the Ground Proximity Warning System is active.

GPWS WARNING.name: GPWS WARNING
GPWS WARNING.description: True if Ground Proximity Warning System installed.

HAS STALL PROTECTION.name: HAS STALL PROTECTION
HAS STALL PROTECTION.description: Will return whether the aircraft has stall protection (true) or not (false).

INDICATED ALTITUDE CALIBRATED.name: INDICATED ALTITUDE CALIBRATED
INDICATED ALTITUDE CALIBRATED.description: Indicated altitude with the altimeter calibrated to current sea level pressure.

INDICATED ALTITUDE EX1.name: INDICATED ALTITUDE EX1
INDICATED ALTITUDE EX1.description: Similar to INDICATED_ALTITUDE but doesn't affect actual plane position when setting this variable.

INTERCOM SYSTEM ACTIVE.name: INTERCOM SYSTEM ACTIVE
INTERCOM SYSTEM ACTIVE.description: Whether or not the intercom system is active.

IS ALTITUDE FREEZE ON.name: IS ALTITUDE FREEZE ON
IS ALTITUDE FREEZE ON.description: True if the altitude of the aircraft is frozen.

IS ATTITUDE FREEZE ON.name: IS ATTITUDE FREEZE ON
IS ATTITUDE FREEZE ON.description: True if the attitude (pitch, bank and heading) of the aircraft is frozen.

IS LATITUDE LONGITUDE FREEZE ON.name: IS LATITUDE LONGITUDE FREEZE ON
IS LATITUDE LONGITUDE FREEZE ON.description:
True if the lat/lon of the aircraft (either user or AI controlled) is frozen. If this variable returns true, it means that the latitude and longitude of the aircraft are not being controlled by ESP, so enabling, for example, a SimConnect client to control the position of the aircraft. This can also apply to altitude and attitude.
          
          Also refer to the range of KEY_FREEZE..... Event IDs.

KOHLSMAN SETTING HG.name: KOHLSMAN SETTING HG:index
KOHLSMAN SETTING HG.description:
The value for the given altimeter index in inches of mercury.
          IMPORTANT! In the system.cfg file, altimeters are indexed from 0, but the SimVar indexes from 1. So, altimeter 0 in that file is accessed using KOHLSMAN SETTING HG:1, 1 by KOHLSMAN SETTING HG:2, etc...

KOHLSMAN SETTING MB.name: KOHLSMAN SETTING MB:index
KOHLSMAN SETTING MB.description:
The value for the given altimeter index in millibars.
          IMPORTANT! In the system.cfg file, altimeters are indexed from 0, but the SimVar indexes from 1. So, altimeter 0 in that file is accessed using KOHLSMAN SETTING MB:1, 1 by KOHLSMAN SETTING MB:2, etc...

KOHLSMAN SETTING STD.name: KOHLSMAN SETTING STD:index
KOHLSMAN SETTING STD.description:
True if the indexed altimeter is in "Standard" mode, or false otherwise.
          IMPORTANT! In the system.cfg file, altimeters are indexed from 0, but the SimVar indexes from 1. So, altimeter 0 in that file is accessed using KOHLSMAN SETTING STD:1, 1 by KOHLSMAN SETTING STD:2, etc...

MANUAL FUEL PUMP HANDLE.name: MANUAL FUEL PUMP HANDLE
MANUAL FUEL PUMP HANDLE.description: Position of manual fuel pump handle. 1 is fully deployed.

PANEL ANTI ICE SWITCH.name: PANEL ANTI ICE SWITCH
PANEL ANTI ICE SWITCH.description: True if panel anti-ice switch is on.

PITOT ICE PCT.name: PITOT ICE PCT
PITOT ICE PCT.description: Amount of pitot ice. 100 is fully iced.

PRESSURE ALTITUDE.name: PRESSURE ALTITUDE
PRESSURE ALTITUDE.description: Standard Altitude, ie: at a 1013.25 hPa (1 atmosphere) setting.

PRESSURIZATION CABIN ALTITUDE.name: PRESSURIZATION CABIN ALTITUDE
PRESSURIZATION CABIN ALTITUDE.description: The current altitude of the cabin pressurization.

PRESSURIZATION CABIN ALTITUDE GOAL.name: PRESSURIZATION CABIN ALTITUDE GOAL
PRESSURIZATION CABIN ALTITUDE GOAL.description:
The set altitude of the cabin pressurization as initialised from the Design Cabin Pressure value in the systems.cfg file. Pressure is converted into an altitude using a standard condition table.
          You can adjust the goal pressure using the PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_ALT_INC and PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_ALT_DEC events.

PRESSURIZATION CABIN ALTITUDE RATE.name: PRESSURIZATION CABIN ALTITUDE RATE
PRESSURIZATION CABIN ALTITUDE RATE.description: The rate at which cabin pressurization changes.

PRESSURIZATION DUMP SWITCH.name: PRESSURIZATION DUMP SWITCH
PRESSURIZATION DUMP SWITCH.description: True if the cabin pressurization dump switch is on.

PRESSURIZATION PRESSURE DIFFERENTIAL.name: PRESSURIZATION PRESSURE DIFFERENTIAL
PRESSURIZATION PRESSURE DIFFERENTIAL.description: The difference in pressure between the set altitude pressurization and the current pressurization.

RAD INS SWITCH.name: RAD INS SWITCH
RAD INS SWITCH.description: True if Rad INS switch on.

SMOKESYSTEM AVAILABLE.name: SMOKESYSTEM AVAILABLE
SMOKESYSTEM AVAILABLE.description:
Smoke system available.
          NOTE: There is no default "smoke system" that this SimVar works on and this is a legacy variable that is available for use should you wish to use it but it affects nothing by default.

SMOKE ENABLE.name: SMOKE ENABLE
SMOKE ENABLE.description: Set to True to activate the smoke system, if one is available. Please see the notes for SMOKESYSTEM AVAILABLE for more information.

SPEAKER ACTIVE.name: SPEAKER ACTIVE
SPEAKER ACTIVE.description: Whether or not the speaker is active.

STALL PROTECTION OFF LIMIT.name: STALL PROTECTION OFF LIMIT
STALL PROTECTION OFF LIMIT.description: Alpha below which the Stall Protection can be disabled. See the [STALL PROTECTION] section for more information.

STALL PROTECTION ON GOAL.name: STALL PROTECTION ON GOAL
STALL PROTECTION ON GOAL.description: The alpha that the Stall Protection will attempt to reach when triggered. See the [STALL PROTECTION] section for more information.

STALL PROTECTION ON LIMIT.name: STALL PROTECTION ON LIMIT
STALL PROTECTION ON LIMIT.description: Alpha above which the Stall Protection timer starts. See the [STALL PROTECTION] section for more information.

STRUCTURAL DEICE SWITCH.name: STRUCTURAL DEICE SWITCH
STRUCTURAL DEICE SWITCH.description: True if the aircraft structure deice switch is on.

TAILHOOK HANDLE.name: TAILHOOK HANDLE
TAILHOOK HANDLE.description: True if the tailhook handle is engaged.

TOW RELEASE HANDLE.name: TOW RELEASE HANDLE
TOW RELEASE HANDLE.description: Position of tow release handle. 100 is fully deployed.

TRUE AIRSPEED SELECTED.name: TRUE AIRSPEED SELECTED
TRUE AIRSPEED SELECTED.description: True if True Airspeed has been selected.

TURN COORDINATOR BALL INV.name: TURN COORDINATOR BALL INV
TURN COORDINATOR BALL INV.description: Turn coordinator ball position inverted (upside down).

TURN INDICATOR RATE.name: TURN INDICATOR RATE
TURN INDICATOR RATE.description:
Turn indicator reading.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all near aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

TURN INDICATOR SWITCH.name: TURN INDICATOR SWITCH
TURN INDICATOR SWITCH.description: True if turn indicator switch is on.

WINDSHIELD DEICE SWITCH.name: WINDSHIELD DEICE SWITCH
WINDSHIELD DEICE SWITCH.description: True if the aircraft windshield deice switch is on.

WISKEY COMPASS INDICATION DEGREES.name: WISKEY COMPASS INDICATION DEGREES
WISKEY COMPASS INDICATION DEGREES.description:
Deprecated, do not use!
          Use MAGNETIC_COMPASS instead.

VARIOMETER MAC CREADY SETTING.name: VARIOMETER MAC CREADY SETTING
VARIOMETER MAC CREADY SETTING.description: The MacCready setting used to fly an optimal speed between thermals.

VARIOMETER NETTO.name: VARIOMETER NETTO
VARIOMETER NETTO.description: Variometer rate using Netto (Total Energy - polar sinkRate).

VARIOMETER SPEED TO FLY.name: VARIOMETER SPEED TO FLY
VARIOMETER SPEED TO FLY.description: Optimal speed to fly between thermals using polar curve and MacCready setting.

VARIOMETER SPEED TO FLY GLIDE RATIO.name: VARIOMETER SPEED TO FLY GLIDE RATIO
VARIOMETER SPEED TO FLY GLIDE RATIO.description: The glide ratio at optimal speed to fly.
VARIOMETER SPEED TO FLY GLIDE RATIO.name_std: VARIOMETER SPEED TO FLY GLIDE RATIO

VARIOMETER SWITCH.name: VARIOMETER SWITCH
VARIOMETER SWITCH.description: True if the variometer switch is on, false if it is not.

VARIOMETER TOTAL ENERGY.name: VARIOMETER TOTAL ENERGY
VARIOMETER TOTAL ENERGY.description:
The variometer rate using total energy.
          Total Energy = Potential Energy + Kinetic Energy

WATER BALLAST TANK CAPACITY.name: WATER BALLAST TANK CAPACITY:index
WATER BALLAST TANK CAPACITY.description: The capacity of the indexed water ballast tank.

WATER BALLAST TANK NUMBER.name: WATER BALLAST TANK NUMBER
WATER BALLAST TANK NUMBER.description: The number of water ballast tank available.

WATER BALLAST TANK QUANTITY.name: WATER BALLAST TANK QUANTITY:index
WATER BALLAST TANK QUANTITY.description: The quantity of water ballast in the indexed tank.

WATER BALLAST VALVE.name: WATER BALLAST VALVE
WATER BALLAST VALVE.description: True (1) if a water ballast valve is available, False (0) otherwise.

WATER BALLAST VALVE FLOW RATE.name: WATER BALLAST VALVE FLOW RATE
WATER BALLAST VALVE FLOW RATE.description: The flow rate of the water ballast valve.

WATER BALLAST EVERY VALVE OPEN.name: WATER BALLAST EVERY VALVE OPEN
WATER BALLAST EVERY VALVE OPEN.description: This variable will return 1 (TRUE) if all the ballast tank valves are open, or 0 (FALSE) otherwise.

IS ANY INTERIOR LIGHT ON.name: IS ANY INTERIOR LIGHT ON
IS ANY INTERIOR LIGHT ON.description: Will return true if any interior light is on or false otherwise.

LANDING LIGHT PBH.name: LANDING LIGHT PBH
LANDING LIGHT PBH.description: Landing light pitch bank and heading.

LIGHT BEACON.name: LIGHT BEACON
LIGHT BEACON.description:
Light switch state.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

LIGHT BEACON ON.name: LIGHT BEACON ON
LIGHT BEACON ON.description: Returns true if the target beacon light is functioning or if the switch is ON. Use beacon lightdef index.

LIGHT BACKLIGHT INTENSITY.name: LIGHT BACKLIGHT INTENSITY
LIGHT BACKLIGHT INTENSITY.description: Vehicle backlights current intensity (0 = off, 1 = full intensity).

LIGHT BRAKE ON.name: LIGHT BRAKE ON
LIGHT BRAKE ON.description: Returns true if the target brake light is functioning or if the switch is ON.

LIGHT CABIN ON.name: LIGHT CABIN ON
LIGHT CABIN ON.description: Returns true if the target cabin light is functioning or if the switch is ON. Use the cabin lightdef index.

LIGHT CABIN POWER SETTING.name: LIGHT CABIN POWER SETTING
LIGHT CABIN POWER SETTING.description: The current cabin light power setting. Requires the cabin lightdef index.

LIGHT GLARESHIELD.name: LIGHT GLARESHIELD
LIGHT GLARESHIELD.description: Whether or not the Light switch for the Glareshield is enabled.

LIGHT GLARESHIELD ON.name: LIGHT GLARESHIELD ON
LIGHT GLARESHIELD ON.description: Returns true if the target glareshield light is functioning or if the switch is ON. Use the glareshield lightdef index.

LIGHT GLARESHIELD POWER SETTING.name: LIGHT GLARESHIELD POWER SETTING
LIGHT GLARESHIELD POWER SETTING.description: The current glareshield light power setting. Requires the glareshield lightdef index.

LIGHT GYROLIGHT INTENSITY.name: LIGHT GYROLIGHT INTENSITY
LIGHT GYROLIGHT INTENSITY.description: Vehicle gyrolights current intensity (0 = off, 1 = full intensity).

LIGHT HEAD ON.name: LIGHT HEAD ON
LIGHT HEAD ON.description: Returns true if the target navigation light is functioning or if the switch is ON.

LIGHT HEADLIGHT INTENSITY.name: LIGHT HEADLIGHT INTENSITY
LIGHT HEADLIGHT INTENSITY.description: Vehicle headlights current intensity (0 = off, 1 = full intensity).

LIGHT LANDING ON.name: LIGHT LANDING ON
LIGHT LANDING ON.description: Returns true if the target landing light is functioning or if the switch is ON. Use landing lightdef index.

LIGHT LANDING.name: LIGHT LANDING
LIGHT LANDING.description:
Light switch state for landing light.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

LIGHT LOGO.name: LIGHT LOGO
LIGHT LOGO.description:
Light switch state for logo light.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

LIGHT LOGO ON.name: LIGHT LOGO ON
LIGHT LOGO ON.description: Returns true if the target logo light is functioning or if the switch is ON. Use the logo lightdef index.

LIGHT NAV ON.name: LIGHT NAV ON
LIGHT NAV ON.description: Returns true if the target navigation light is functioning or if the switch is ON. Use navigation lightdef index.

LIGHT NAV.name: LIGHT NAV
LIGHT NAV.description: Light switch state for the NAV light.

LIGHT ON STATES.name: LIGHT ON STATES
LIGHT ON STATES.description:
Bit mask:[index]
          
            0x0001:[index] Nav
            0x0002:[index] Beacon
            0x0004:[index] Landing
            0x0008:[index] Taxi
            0x0010:[index] Strobe
            0x0020:[index] Panel
            0x0040:[index] Recognition
            0x0080:[index] Wing
            0x0100:[index] Logo
            0x0200:[index] Cabin

LIGHT PANEL.name: LIGHT PANEL
LIGHT PANEL.description: Light switch state of the panel light.

LIGHT PANEL ON.name: LIGHT PANEL ON
LIGHT PANEL ON.description: Returns true if the target panel light is functioning or if the switch is ON. Use the panel lightdef index.

LIGHT PANEL POWER SETTING.name: LIGHT PANEL POWER SETTING
LIGHT PANEL POWER SETTING.description: The current panel light power setting. Requires the panel lightdef index.

LIGHT PEDESTRAL.name: LIGHT PEDESTRAL
LIGHT PEDESTRAL.description:
Whether or not the Light switch for the Pedestal is enabled.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

LIGHT PEDESTRAL ON.name: LIGHT PEDESTRAL ON
LIGHT PEDESTRAL ON.description: Returns true if the target pedestral light is functioning or if the switch is ON. Requires the pedestral lightdef index.

LIGHT PEDESTRAL POWER SETTING.name: LIGHT PEDESTRAL POWER SETTING
LIGHT PEDESTRAL POWER SETTING.description: The current pedestral light power setting. Requires the pedestral lightdef index.

LIGHT POTENTIOMETER.name: LIGHT POTENTIOMETER:index
LIGHT POTENTIOMETER.description: Adjust the potentiometer of the indexed lighting. Index is defined in the appropriate lightdef hashmap setting.

LIGHT RECOGNITION.name: LIGHT RECOGNITION
LIGHT RECOGNITION.description:
Light switch state for the recognition light.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

LIGHT RECOGNITION ON.name: LIGHT RECOGNITION ON
LIGHT RECOGNITION ON.description: Returns true if the target recognition light is functioning or if the switch is ON. Use the recognition lightdef index.

LIGHT STATES.name: LIGHT STATES
LIGHT STATES.description:
Same as LIGHT_ON_STATES.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

LIGHT STROBE.name: LIGHT STROBE
LIGHT STROBE.description:
Light switch state for the strobe lights.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

LIGHT STROBE ON.name: LIGHT STROBE ON
LIGHT STROBE ON.description:
Returns true if the target strobe light is functioning or if the switch is ON. Use the strobe lightdef index.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

LIGHT TAXI.name: LIGHT TAXI
LIGHT TAXI.description:
Light switch state for the taxi light.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

LIGHT TAXI ON.name: LIGHT TAXI ON
LIGHT TAXI ON.description: Returns true if the target taxi light is functioning or if the switch is ON. Use taxi lightdef index.

LIGHT WING.name: LIGHT WING
LIGHT WING.description:
Light switch state for the wing lights.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

LIGHT WING ON.name: LIGHT WING ON
LIGHT WING ON.description: Returns true if the target wing light is functioning or if the switch is ON. Use the wing lightdef index.

MANUAL INSTRUMENT LIGHTS.name: MANUAL INSTRUMENT LIGHTS
MANUAL INSTRUMENT LIGHTS.description: True if instrument lights are set manually.

STROBES AVAILABLE.name: STROBES AVAILABLE
STROBES AVAILABLE.description: True if strobe lights are available.

HYDRAULIC PRESSURE.name: HYDRAULIC PRESSURE:index
HYDRAULIC PRESSURE.description: Hydraulic system pressure. Indexes start at 1.

HYDRAULIC RESERVOIR PERCENT.name: HYDRAULIC RESERVOIR PERCENT:index
HYDRAULIC RESERVOIR PERCENT.description: Hydraulic pressure changes will follow changes to this variable. Indexes start at 1.

HYDRAULIC SWITCH.name: HYDRAULIC SWITCH
HYDRAULIC SWITCH.description: True if hydraulic switch is on.

DROPPABLE OBJECTS COUNT.name: DROPPABLE OBJECTS COUNT:index
DROPPABLE OBJECTS COUNT.description: The number of droppable objects at the station number identified by the index.

DROPPABLE OBJECTS TYPE.name: DROPPABLE OBJECTS TYPE:index
DROPPABLE OBJECTS TYPE.description: The type of droppable object at the station number identified by the index.

DROPPABLE OBJECTS UI NAME.name: DROPPABLE OBJECTS UI NAME:index
DROPPABLE OBJECTS UI NAME.description: Descriptive name, used in User Interface dialogs, of a droppable object, identified by index.

PAYLOAD STATION NUM SIMOBJECTS.name: PAYLOAD STATION NUM SIMOBJECTS:index
PAYLOAD STATION NUM SIMOBJECTS.description: The number of objects at the payload station.

PAYLOAD STATION OBJECT.name: PAYLOAD STATION OBJECT:index
PAYLOAD STATION OBJECT.description: Places the named object at the payload station identified by the index (starting from 1). The string is the Container name (refer to the title property of Simulation Object Configuration Files).

WARNING FUEL.name: WARNING FUEL
WARNING FUEL.description: This is the current state of the fuel warning, either on (true) or off (false).

WARNING FUEL LEFT.name: WARNING FUEL LEFT
WARNING FUEL LEFT.description: This is the current state of the left fuel tank warning, either on (true) or off (false).

WARNING FUEL RIGHT.name: WARNING FUEL RIGHT
WARNING FUEL RIGHT.description: This is the current state of the right fuel tank warning, either on (true) or off (false).

WARNING LOW HEIGHT.name: WARNING LOW HEIGHT
WARNING LOW HEIGHT.description: This is the current state of the low height warning, either on (true) or off (false).

WARNING OIL PRESSURE.name: WARNING OIL PRESSURE
WARNING OIL PRESSURE.description: This is the current state of the oil pressure warning, either on (true) or off (false).

WARNING VACUUM.name: WARNING VACUUM
WARNING VACUUM.description: This is the current state of the vacuum system warning, either on (true) or off (false).

WARNING VACUUM LEFT.name: WARNING VACUUM LEFT
WARNING VACUUM LEFT.description: This is the current state of the left vacuum system warning, either on (true) or off (false).

WARNING VACUUM RIGHT.name: WARNING VACUUM RIGHT
WARNING VACUUM RIGHT.description: This is the current state of the right vacuum system warning, either on (true) or off (false).

WARNING VOLTAGE.name: WARNING VOLTAGE
WARNING VOLTAGE.description: This is the current state of the electrical system voltage warning, either on (true) or off (false).

YOKE X POSITION WITH AP.name: YOKE X POSITION WITH AP
YOKE X POSITION WITH AP.description: Percent control deflection left/right (for animation). Also includes AP's inputs.

YOKE Y POSITION WITH AP.name: YOKE Y POSITION WITH AP
YOKE Y POSITION WITH AP.description: Percent control deflection fore/aft (for animation). Also includes AP's inputs.

EXIT POSX.name: EXIT POSX:index
EXIT POSX.description: Position of exit relative to datum reference point.

EXIT POSY.name: EXIT POSY:index
EXIT POSY.description: Position of exit relative to datum reference point.

EXIT POSZ.name: EXIT POSZ:index
EXIT POSZ.description: Position of exit relative to datum reference point.

CAMERA GAMEPLAY PITCH YAW.name: CAMERA GAMEPLAY PITCH YAW:index
CAMERA GAMEPLAY PITCH YAW.description: Returns either the pitch (index 0) or the yaw (index 1) of the current gameplay camera.

CAMERA REQUEST ACTION.name: CAMERA REQUEST ACTION
CAMERA REQUEST ACTION.description: This can be used to have the currently active camera perform a predefined action. Currently only 1 action is supported, but more may be added over time.
CAMERA REQUEST ACTION.units:
Enum:
          
            1 = Reset Active Camera (in VR this will recenter the headset view)

CAMERA STATE.name: CAMERA STATE
CAMERA STATE.description:
This can be used to get or set the camera "state", which will be one of the listed enum values.
          Note that not ALL possible enum values are shown, since some values are internal only, and some values will do nothing, but have been reserved for future expansion of the camera system.
          Also note that the value "9" is a special case, generally used only when working with in-sim panels and is used to go to the showcase cameras, defaulting to the last selected camera within this section (Drone, Fixed or Environment).
CAMERA STATE.units:
Enum:
          
            2 = Cockpit
            3 = External/Chase
            4 = Drone
            5 = Fixed on Plane
            6 = Environment
            7 = Six DoF
            8 = Gameplay
            9 = Showcase
            10 = Drone Aircraft
            11 = Waiting
            12 = World Map
            13 = Hangar RTC
            14 = Hangar Custom
            15 = Menu RTC
            16 = In-Game RTC
            17 = Replay
            19 = Drone Top-Down
            21 = Hangar
            24 = Ground
            25 = Follow Traffic Aircraft

CAMERA SUBSTATE.name: CAMERA SUBSTATE
CAMERA SUBSTATE.description: This variable can be used to get or set the camera "sub-state". The options here are generally only required when working with the in-sim panel UI. Note that the "locked" and "unlocked" state will be changed automatically if the following SimVars have their values changed: COCKPIT_CAMERA_HEADLOOK, CHASE_CAMERA_HEADLOOK.
CAMERA SUBSTATE.units:
Enum:
          
            1 = Locked (Fixed look or chase lock -
                
                The camera is locked in position)
            2 = Unlocked (Head look or Chase
                
                normal - The camera is "attached" to
                
                the mouse)
            3 = Quickview (the camera is
                
                currently using a Quickview)
            4 = Smart (The camera has Smart
                
                camera active)
            5 = Instrument (The camera is
                
                focused on an instruments panel)

CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX.name: CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX:index
CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX.description:
With this you can get or set both the type of view for the current camera, as well as the option index, which will be between 0 and the maximum index value (as retrieved using the CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX MAX SimVar). Supplying an index of 0 to the SimVar will get/set the type (from the selection of enum values listed), and using an index of 1 will get/set the option index, which is an integer value.
           
          Please see the Notes On View Types And Indices section below for more information.
CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX.units:
Enum (index = 0):
          
            0 = Unknown/default
            (External / Chase and Showcase /
                
                Drone / Fixed / Environment states)
            1 = Pilot View
            (Cockpit State)
            2 = Instruments
            (Cockpit State)
            3 = Quickview
            (Cockpit State)
            4 = Quickview External
            (External State)
            5 = View
            (Showcase / Drone / Fixed /
                
                Environment states)
          
          or
          Number (index = 1)

CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX MAX.name: CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX MAX:index
CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX MAX.description:
This variable can get the number of option indices related to a specific camera view type. The index value supplied to the SimVar should be one of the camera view type Enum values (see CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX), and the SimVar will return the number of options available for that camera type (counting from 1, so - for example - if the camera view type is "Quickview" and has 8 quickview settings, then CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX MAX:4 will return 8). Note that this value can be set after a flight has started, but it will have no effect since the number of camera options is initilaised once only and not updated (and the simulation may overwrite the value again even after setting it).
           
          Please see the Notes On View Types And Indices section below for more information.
CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX MAX.name_std: CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX MAX

GAMEPLAY CAMERA FOCUS.name: GAMEPLAY CAMERA FOCUS
GAMEPLAY CAMERA FOCUS.description:
This gets/sets the focus for the camera zoom, which can be either manual, or auto. The setting affects both the Cockpit and the External (Chase) cameras.
          The following SimVars can be used to get/set the level of zoom: COCKPIT_CAMERA_ZOOM or CHASE_CAMERA_ZOOM.

IS CAMERA RAY INTERSECT WITH NODE.name: IS CAMERA RAY INTERSECT WITH NODE
IS CAMERA RAY INTERSECT WITH NODE.description: This SimVar is used to check for a collision along a ray from the center of the user FOV and a model node. The available nodes that can be checked using this SimVar must be previously defined in the [CAMERA_RAY_NODE_COLLISION] of the cameras.cfg file. The SimVar requires a node index value between 1 and 10, corresponding to the node defined in the CFG file, and the SimVar will return 1 (TRUE) if there is a collision along the camera ray or 0 (FALSE) otherwise. You may also supply an index of 0 to perform a collision check for all defined nodes, in which case the SimVar will return 1 (TRUE) if there is a collision between the ray and any of the defined nodes. Supplying an index outside of the range of 1 to 10, or supplying an index for which no node has been defined, will return 0 (FALSE).
IS CAMERA RAY INTERSECT WITH NODE.name_std: IS CAMERA RAY INTERSECT WITH NODE

CHASE CAMERA HEADLOOK.name: CHASE CAMERA HEADLOOK
CHASE CAMERA HEADLOOK.description: This is used to get/set the look state of the chase (external) camera. Note that this value will also affect the CAMERA_SUBSTATE value, when the CAMERA_STATE is set to 3 (External/Chase).

CHASE CAMERA MOMENTUM.name: CHASE CAMERA MOMENTUM
CHASE CAMERA MOMENTUM.description: Sets/gets the momentum modifier of the chase (external) camera, which is controls how fast/slow the camera will stop moving when no longer being moved by the user. Default is 50%.

CHASE CAMERA SPEED.name: CHASE CAMERA SPEED
CHASE CAMERA SPEED.description: Sets/gets the translation speed modifier of the chase (external) camara, as a percentage. Default is 50%.

CHASE CAMERA ZOOM.name: CHASE CAMERA ZOOM
CHASE CAMERA ZOOM.description: Sets/gets the zoom/FOV modifier for the chase (external) camera. Note that when setting this value, it will affect the camera regardless of whether the GAMEPLAY_CAMERA_FOCUS is set to manual or automatic. Default is 50%.

CHASE CAMERA ZOOM SPEED.name: CHASE CAMERA ZOOM SPEED
CHASE CAMERA ZOOM SPEED.description: Sets/gets the speed modifier for when the zoom/FOV chase (external) camera changes zoom/FOV levels. Default is 50%.

CAMERA ACTION COCKPIT VIEW RESET.name: CAMERA ACTION COCKPIT VIEW RESET
CAMERA ACTION COCKPIT VIEW RESET.description: This can be used to reset the cockpit camera when the CAMERA_STATE is set to 2 (Cockpit). Essentially the same as the user pressing the default reset keys CTRL + Space.

CAMERA ACTION COCKPIT VIEW SAVE.name: CAMERA ACTION COCKPIT VIEW SAVE:index
CAMERA ACTION COCKPIT VIEW SAVE.description: This can be used to save a cockpit camera when the CAMERA_STATE is set to 2 (Cockpit). The index value given is the save "slot" that will be used, from 0 to 9. Essentially this is the same as the user pressing the default save keys CTRL + Alt + 0-9.

COCKPIT CAMERA HEADLOOK.name: COCKPIT CAMERA HEADLOOK
COCKPIT CAMERA HEADLOOK.description: This is used to get/set the look state of the cockpit camera. Note that this value will also affect the CAMERA_SUBSTATE value, when the CAMERA_STATE is set to 2 (Cockpit).

COCKPIT CAMERA HEIGHT.name: COCKPIT CAMERA HEIGHT
COCKPIT CAMERA HEIGHT.description: This can be used to get/set the cockpit camera height modifier expressed as a percentage. Default is 50%.

COCKPIT CAMERA INSTRUMENT AUTOSELECT.name: COCKPIT CAMERA INSTRUMENT AUTOSELECT
COCKPIT CAMERA INSTRUMENT AUTOSELECT.description: This can be used to get or set the autoselect option for the cockpit camera when viewing the instruments (ie: the CAMERA_SUBSTATE is 5). When enabled the camera will move automatically if the player mouse reaches the edge of the screen and there are instrument panels available on that side.

COCKPIT CAMERA MOMENTUM.name: COCKPIT CAMERA MOMENTUM
COCKPIT CAMERA MOMENTUM.description: Sets/gets the momentum modifier of the cockpit camera, which is controls how fast/slow the camera will stop moving when no longer being moved by the user. Default is 50%.

COCKPIT CAMERA SIDE.name: COCKPIT CAMERA SIDE
COCKPIT CAMERA SIDE.description: Not currently used in the simulation.

COCKPIT CAMERA SPEED.name: COCKPIT CAMERA SPEED
COCKPIT CAMERA SPEED.description: Sets/gets the translation speed modifier of the cockpit camara, as a percentage. Default is 50%.

COCKPIT CAMERA UPPER POSITION.name: COCKPIT CAMERA UPPER POSITION
COCKPIT CAMERA UPPER POSITION.description: Sets/gets the current "upper position" cockpit camera toggle. When 1 (TRUE), the camera is is in the upper position, and when 0 (FALSE) it is in the default position.

COCKPIT CAMERA ZOOM.name: COCKPIT CAMERA ZOOM
COCKPIT CAMERA ZOOM.description: Sets/gets the zoom/FOV modifier for the cockpit camera. Note that when setting this value, it will affect the camera regardless of whether the GAMEPLAY_CAMERA_FOCUS is set to manual or automatic. Default is 50%.

COCKPIT CAMERA ZOOM SPEED.name: COCKPIT CAMERA ZOOM SPEED
COCKPIT CAMERA ZOOM SPEED.description: Sets/gets the speed modifier for when the zoom/FOV cockpit camera changes zoom/FOV levels. Default is 50%.

DRONE CAMERA FOCUS.name: DRONE CAMERA FOCUS
DRONE CAMERA FOCUS.description: Sets/gets the focus modifier for the drone camera. Default is 50%, and a lower value will set the drone focus to things in the foreground and a higher level will set the drone focus to things in the background. Note that this is only taken into account when the DRONE_CAMERA_FOCUS_MODE is set to 3 (manual).

DRONE CAMERA FOCUS MODE.name: DRONE CAMERA FOCUS MODE
DRONE CAMERA FOCUS MODE.description: Sets/gets the current drone focus mode. When set to 3 (manual), the focus position will be based on the DRONE_CAMERA_FOCUS value.

DRONE CAMERA FOLLOW.name: DRONE CAMERA FOLLOW
DRONE CAMERA FOLLOW.description: Sets/gets the whether the drone camera is in follow mode or not.

DRONE CAMERA FOV.name: DRONE CAMERA FOV
DRONE CAMERA FOV.description: Sets/gets the zoom/FOV modifier for the drone camera. Default is 50%.

DRONE CAMERA LOCKED.name: DRONE CAMERA LOCKED
DRONE CAMERA LOCKED.description: Sets/gets the whether the drone camera is locked or not.

DRONE CAMERA SPEED ROTATION.name: DRONE CAMERA SPEED ROTATION
DRONE CAMERA SPEED ROTATION.description: Sets/gets the rotation speed modifier of the drone camara, as a percentage. Default is 50%.

DRONE CAMERA SPEED TRAVELLING.name: DRONE CAMERA SPEED TRAVELLING
DRONE CAMERA SPEED TRAVELLING.description: Sets/gets the translation speed modifier of the drone camara, as a percentage. Default is 50%.

SMART CAMERA ACTIVE.name: SMART CAMERA ACTIVE
SMART CAMERA ACTIVE.description: Sets/gets the whether the smart camera is active or not.

SMART CAMERA INFO.name: SMART CAMERA INFO:index
SMART CAMERA INFO.description:
Gets information on the smartcam system. The index sets what kind of information will be returned (or set):
          
            0 = Gets the number of smartcam targets in the smart camera list
            1 = Gets or sets the index of the currently selected smartcam target, counting from 0 (so index 0 is the first target in the list).

SMART CAMERA LIST.name: SMART CAMERA LIST:index
SMART CAMERA LIST.description: Retrieves the type of target for the indexed position in the smartcam list, counting from 0 (so index 0 is the first target in the list).
SMART CAMERA LIST.units:
Enum:
          
            0 = unknown POI
            1 = Follow POI
            2 = User POI
            3 = General POI
            4 = End OF Runway
            5 = Landing Runway
            6 = Flightpath
            7 = Object Interaction
            8 = Multiplayer OOI
            9 = Active Runway
            10 = Waypoint
            11 = Airport OOI
            12 = Flight Assistant Destination

SMART CAMERA LIST DESCRIPTION.name: SMART CAMERA LIST DESCRIPTION:index
SMART CAMERA LIST DESCRIPTION.description: This returns a localized string that represents the smartcam target specified by the given index. Indices count from 0 so index 0 is the first target in the list.

COLLECTIVE POSITION.name: COLLECTIVE POSITION
COLLECTIVE POSITION.description: The position of the helicopter\'s collective. 0 is fully up, 100 fully depressed.

DISK BANK ANGLE.name: DISK BANK ANGLE:index
DISK BANK ANGLE.description:
Rotor bank angle of the given rotor index. Index should be specified to 1 for main rotor and 2 for tail rotor.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

DISK BANK PCT.name: DISK BANK PCT:index
DISK BANK PCT.description:
Rotor bank percent of the given rotor index. Index should be specified to 1 for main rotor and 2 for tail rotor.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

DISK CONING PCT.name: DISK CONING PCT:index
DISK CONING PCT.description:
Rotor coning percent of the given rotor index. Index should be specified to 1 for main rotor and 2 for tail rotor.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

DISK PITCH ANGLE.name: DISK PITCH ANGLE:index
DISK PITCH ANGLE.description:
Rotor pitch angle of the given rotor index. Index should be specified to 1 for main rotor and 2 for tail rotor.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

DISK PITCH PCT.name: DISK PITCH PCT:index
DISK PITCH PCT.description:
Rotor pitch percent of the given rotor index. Index should be specified to 1 for main rotor and 2 for tail rotor.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

ROTOR BRAKE ACTIVE.name: ROTOR BRAKE ACTIVE
ROTOR BRAKE ACTIVE.description: Whether the rotor brake is active (1, TRUE) or not (0, FALSE).

ROTOR BRAKE HANDLE POS.name: ROTOR BRAKE HANDLE POS
ROTOR BRAKE HANDLE POS.description: The percentage actuated of the rotor brake handle.

ROTOR CHIP DETECTED.name: ROTOR CHIP DETECTED
ROTOR CHIP DETECTED.description: Whether the rotor chip is detected (1,TRUE) or not (0, FALSE).

ROTOR CLUTCH ACTIVE.name: ROTOR CLUTCH ACTIVE
ROTOR CLUTCH ACTIVE.description: Whether the rotor clutch is active (1, TRUE) or not (0, FALSE).

ROTOR CLUTCH SWITCH POS.name: ROTOR CLUTCH SWITCH POS
ROTOR CLUTCH SWITCH POS.description: The rotor clutch switch position, either on (1 TRUE) or off (0, FALSE).

ROTOR COLLECTIVE BLADE PITCH PCT.name: ROTOR COLLECTIVE BLADE PITCH PCT
ROTOR COLLECTIVE BLADE PITCH PCT.description:
The rotor collective blade pitch.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

ROTOR CYCLIC BLADE MAX PITCH POSITION.name: ROTOR CYCLIC BLADE MAX PITCH POSITION
ROTOR CYCLIC BLADE MAX PITCH POSITION.description:
The position (angle) at which blade has the maximum cyclic pitch.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.
ROTOR CYCLIC BLADE MAX PITCH POSITION.name_std: ROTOR CYCLIC BLADE MAX PITCH POSITION

ROTOR CYCLIC BLADE PITCH PCT.name: ROTOR CYCLIC BLADE PITCH PCT
ROTOR CYCLIC BLADE PITCH PCT.description:
The rotor cyclic blade (maximum) pitch.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

ROTOR GOV ACTIVE.name: ROTOR GOV ACTIVE
ROTOR GOV ACTIVE.description: Whether the rotor governor is active (1, TRUE) or not (0, FALSE).

ROTOR GOV SWITCH POS.name: ROTOR GOV SWITCH POS
ROTOR GOV SWITCH POS.description: The rotor governor switch position, either on (1 TRUE) or off (0, FALSE).

ROTOR LATERAL TRIM PCT.name: ROTOR LATERAL TRIM PCT
ROTOR LATERAL TRIM PCT.description:
The rotor lateral trim percentage.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

ROTOR LONGITUDINAL TRIM PCT.name: ROTOR LONGITUDINAL TRIM PCT
ROTOR LONGITUDINAL TRIM PCT.description:
The rotor longitudinal trim percentage.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

ROTOR ROTATION ANGLE.name: ROTOR ROTATION ANGLE:index
ROTOR ROTATION ANGLE.description:
Rotor rotation angle of the given rotor index. Index should be specified to 1 for main rotor and 2 for tail rotor.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

ROTOR RPM.name: ROTOR RPM:index
ROTOR RPM.description:
The indexed rotor RPM.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

ROTOR RPM PCT.name: ROTOR RPM PCT:index
ROTOR RPM PCT.description: Percent max rated rpm of the given rotor index. Index should be specified to 1 for main rotor and 2 for tail rotor.

STRUCT ROTOR POSITION.name: STRUCT ROTOR POSITION:index
STRUCT ROTOR POSITION.description: The position of the indexed rotor.

TAIL ROTOR BLADE PITCH PCT.name: TAIL ROTOR BLADE PITCH PCT
TAIL ROTOR BLADE PITCH PCT.description: The pitch position of the tailrotor blades.

ENG ROTOR RPM.name: ENG ROTOR RPM:index
ENG ROTOR RPM.description:
Returns the indexed rotor RPM.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

HELICOPTER MASTER THROTTLE POSITION.name: HELICOPTER_MASTER_THROTTLE_POSITION
HELICOPTER MASTER THROTTLE POSITION.description: Returns the position of the master throttle as a value between 0 and 1.

IS ATTACHED TO SLING.name: IS ATTACHED TO SLING
IS ATTACHED TO SLING.description: Set to true if this object is attached to a sling.

NUM SLING CABLES.name: NUM SLING CABLES
NUM SLING CABLES.description: The number of sling cables (not hoists) that are configured for the helicopter.

SLING ACTIVE PAYLOAD STATION.name: SLING ACTIVE PAYLOAD STATION:index, param
SLING ACTIVE PAYLOAD STATION.description: The payload station (identified by the parameter) where objects will be placed from the sling (identified by the index).

SLING CABLE BROKEN.name: SLING CABLE BROKEN:index
SLING CABLE BROKEN.description: THis will be True (1) if the indexed cable is broken, or False (0) otherwise.

SLING CABLE EXTENDED LENGTH.name: SLING CABLE EXTENDED LENGTH:index
SLING CABLE EXTENDED LENGTH.description: The length of the indexed cable extending from the aircraft.

SLING HOIST PERCENT DEPLOYED.name: SLING HOIST PERCENT DEPLOYED:index
SLING HOIST PERCENT DEPLOYED.description: The percentage of the full length of the sling cable deployed.

SLING HOIST SWITCH.name: SLING HOIST SWITCH:index
SLING HOIST SWITCH.description: This will be True (1) if the hoist is enabled or False (0) otherwise.

SLING HOOK IN PICKUP MODE.name: SLING HOOK IN PICKUP MODE
SLING HOOK IN PICKUP MODE.description: This will be True (1) if the hook is in pickup mode or False (0) otherwise. When True, the hook will be capable of picking up another object.

SLING OBJECT ATTACHED.name: SLING OBJECT ATTACHED:index
SLING OBJECT ATTACHED.description:
If the SimVar units are set as boolean, this will return True (1) if a sling object is attached, or False (0) otherwise.
          If the SimVar units are set as a string, tis will return the container title of the object.
          Note that there can be multiple sling positions, indexed from 1. The sling positions are set in the Aircraft Configuration File.

ENG ELECTRICAL LOAD.name: ENG ELECTRICAL LOAD:index
ENG ELECTRICAL LOAD.description: The electrical load on the indexed engine.

ENG FUEL PRESSURE.name: ENG FUEL PRESSURE:index
ENG FUEL PRESSURE.description: The fuel pressure for the indexed engine.

ENG TRANSMISSION PRESSURE.name: ENG TRANSMISSION PRESSURE:index
ENG TRANSMISSION PRESSURE.description: The transmission pressure of the indexed engine.

ENG TRANSMISSION TEMPERATURE.name: ENG TRANSMISSION TEMPERATURE:index
ENG TRANSMISSION TEMPERATURE.description: The transmission temperature of the indexed engine.

ENG TURBINE TEMPERATURE.name: ENG TURBINE TEMPERATURE:index
ENG TURBINE TEMPERATURE.description: The tubine temperature for the indexed engine.

ANIMATION DELTA TIME.name: ANIMATION DELTA TIME
ANIMATION DELTA TIME.description: Difference of time between the current frame and the last frame where this SimObject has been animated

ARTIFICIAL GROUND ELEVATION.name: ARTIFICIAL GROUND ELEVATION
ARTIFICIAL GROUND ELEVATION.description: In case scenery is not loaded for AI planes, this variable can be used to set a default surface elevation.

CRASH FLAG.name: CRASH FLAG
CRASH FLAG.description: Flag value that indicates the cause of a crash.
CRASH FLAG.units:
Enum:
          
            0:[index] None
            2:[index] Mountain
            4:[index] General
            6:[index] Building
            8:[index] Splash
            10:[index] Gear up
            12:[index] Overstress
            14:[index] Building
            16:[index] Aircraft
            18:[index] Fuel Truck

CRASH SEQUENCE.name: CRASH SEQUENCE
CRASH SEQUENCE.description: The state of the crash event sequence.
CRASH SEQUENCE.units:
Enum:
          
            0:[index] off
            1:[index] complete
            3:[index] reset
            4:[index] pause
            11:[index] start

HAND ANIM STATE.name: HAND ANIM STATE
HAND ANIM STATE.description: What frame of the hand is currently used.
HAND ANIM STATE.units:
Enum:
          
            0 = Hover
            1 = Index push/Point
            2 = Pinch large
            3 = Pinch medium
            4 = Pinch small
            5 = Pinch lateral
            6 = Press all/Fist
            7 = Toggle lever up/down
            8 = Thumb push
            9 = Holde yoke thin
            10 = Hold throttle
            11 = Hold yokes
            12 = Push/pull lever

IDLE ANIMATION ID.name: IDLE ANIMATION ID
IDLE ANIMATION ID.description: The ID of the idle animation for the sim object.

PARACHUTE OPEN.name: PARACHUTE OPEN
PARACHUTE OPEN.description: This will be TRUE if the parachute has opened and FALSE otherwise. Currently this is only applied to the Parachute SimObject used by Winches.

REALISM CRASH DETECTION.name: REALISM CRASH DETECTION
REALISM CRASH DETECTION.description: True indicates crash detection is turned on.

REALISM CRASH WITH OTHERS.name: REALISM CRASH WITH OTHERS
REALISM CRASH WITH OTHERS.description: True indicates crashing with other aircraft is possible.

TRACK IR ENABLE.name: TRACK IR ENABLE
TRACK IR ENABLE.description: Returns true if Track IR is enabled or not.

TOTAL WORLD VELOCITY.name: TOTAL WORLD VELOCITY
TOTAL WORLD VELOCITY.description: Speed relative to the earths center.

USER INPUT ENABLED.name: USER INPUT ENABLED
USER INPUT ENABLED.description: Is input allowed from the user.

VELOCITY WORLD X.name: VELOCITY WORLD X
VELOCITY WORLD X.description:
Speed relative to earth, in East/West direction.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

VELOCITY WORLD Y.name: VELOCITY WORLD Y
VELOCITY WORLD Y.description:
Speed relative to earth, in vertical direction.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

VELOCITY WORLD Z.name: VELOCITY WORLD Z
VELOCITY WORLD Z.description:
Speed relative to earth, in North/South direction.
          NOTE: This is available in multiplayer to all far aircraft. See here for more information: Note On SimVars In Multiplayer.

AMBIENT VISIBILITY.name: AMBIENT VISIBILITY
AMBIENT VISIBILITY.description: Ambient visibility (only measures ambient particle visibility - related to ambient density).

AMBIENT WIND DIRECTION.name: AMBIENT WIND DIRECTION
AMBIENT WIND DIRECTION.description: Wind direction, relative to true north.

DENSITY ALTITUDE.name: DENSITY ALTITUDE
DENSITY ALTITUDE.description:
The density altitude is the altitude relative to standard atmospheric conditions at which the air density would be equal to the indicated air density at the place of observation. The calculation is as follows:
          density_altitude = pressure_altitude + 118.8 * (outside_air_temp - ISA_temp)

STRUCT AMBIENT WIND.name: STRUCT AMBIENT WIND
STRUCT AMBIENT WIND.description: X (latitude), Y (vertical) and Z (longitude) components of the wind.

AI DESIRED SPEED.name: AI DESIRED SPEED
AI DESIRED SPEED.description: The desired speed of the AI object.

AI WAYPOINT LIST.name: AI WAYPOINT LIST
AI WAYPOINT LIST.description: A list of waypoints that an AI controlled object should follow.

AI CURRENT WAYPOINT.name: AI CURRENT WAYPOINT
AI CURRENT WAYPOINT.description: The current waypoint in the list.

AI DESIRED HEADING.name: AI DESIRED HEADING
AI DESIRED HEADING.description: The desired heading of the AI object.

AI GROUNDTURNTIME.name: AI GROUNDTURNTIME
AI GROUNDTURNTIME.description: The time required by the AI aircraft to make a 90o turn.

AI GROUNDCRUISESPEED.name: AI GROUNDCRUISESPEED
AI GROUNDCRUISESPEED.description: The ground cruising speed for the AI aircraft.

AI GROUNDTURNSPEED.name: AI GROUNDTURNSPEED
AI GROUNDTURNSPEED.description: The ground turning speed for the AI aircraft.

AI TRAFFIC ISIFR.name: AI TRAFFIC ISIFR
AI TRAFFIC ISIFR.description: This can be used to request whether the AI aircraft is IFR or VFR. Note that if an aircraft does not have a flight plan, the value returned will be 0 (or false).

AI TRAFFIC STATE.name: AI TRAFFIC STATE
AI TRAFFIC STATE.description:
This will return a string describing an AI aircraft state. If the aircraft is under ATC control the string will be one of the following:
          
            "init"
            "sleep"
            "flt plan"
            "startup"
            "preflight support"
            "clearance"
            "push back 1"
            "push back 2"
            "pre taxi out"
            "taxi out"
            "takeoff 1"
            "takeoff 2"
            "T&G depart"
            "enroute"
            "pattern"
            "landing"
            "rollout"
            "go around"
            "taxi in"
            "shutdown"
            "postflight support" 
          
           
          If the aircraft is not under ATC control, the string will be one of these:
          
            "Sleep"
            "Waypoint"
            "Takeoff"
            "Landing"
            "Taxi"
          
           
          Note that if an aircraft does not have a flight plan, the value returned will be an empty string "".

AI TRAFFIC CURRENT AIRPORT.name: AI TRAFFIC CURRENT AIRPORT
AI TRAFFIC CURRENT AIRPORT.description: The ICAO code of the current airport. If an aircraft does not have a flight plan, the value returned will be an empty string "".

AI TRAFFIC ASSIGNED RUNWAY.name: AI TRAFFIC ASSIGNED RUNWAY
AI TRAFFIC ASSIGNED RUNWAY.description: The assigned runway name (for example: "32R"). If an aircraft does not have a flight plan, the value returned will be an empty string "".

AI TRAFFIC ASSIGNED PARKING.name: AI TRAFFIC ASSIGNED PARKING
AI TRAFFIC ASSIGNED PARKING.description:
The assigned parking name. The string will take the form:
          Name + Number, Type ( radius )
          For example:
          
            "Ramp 1, RAMP sml (10m)"
            "Gate G 4, RAMP lrg (18m)"
          
          If an aircraft does not have a flight plan, the value returned will be an empty string "".

AI TRAFFIC FROMAIRPORT.name: AI TRAFFIC FROMAIRPORT
AI TRAFFIC FROMAIRPORT.description:
The ICAO code of the departure airport in the current schedule. 
          This variable is only valid for aircraft generated by the traffic database that have schedules. If an aircraft does not have a schedule, the value returned will an empty string"".

AI TRAFFIC TOAIRPORT.name: AI TRAFFIC TOAIRPORT
AI TRAFFIC TOAIRPORT.description:
The ICAO code of the destination airport in the current schedule. 
          This variable is only valid for aircraft generated by the traffic database that have schedules. If an aircraft does not have a schedule, the value returned will an empty string"".

AI TRAFFIC ETD.name: AI TRAFFIC ETD
AI TRAFFIC ETD.description:
The estimated time of departure for the current schedule entry, given as the number of seconds difference from the current simulation time. This can be negative if ETD is earlier than the current simulation time
          This variable is only valid for aircraft generated by the traffic database that have schedules. If an aircraft does not have a schedule, the value returned will be 0.

AI TRAFFIC ETA.name: AI TRAFFIC ETA
AI TRAFFIC ETA.description:
Estimated time of arrival for the current schedule entry, given as the number of seconds difference from the current simulated time. This can be negative if ETA is earlier than the current simulated time.
          This variable is only valid for aircraft generated by the traffic database that have schedules. If an aircraft does not have a schedule, the value returned will be 0.

STRUCT PBH32.name: STRUCT PBH32
STRUCT PBH32.description: Returns a pitch, bank and heading value (for what will depend on the SimVar being used).

STRUCT REALISM VARS.name: STRUCT REALISM VARS
STRUCT REALISM VARS.description: Not currently used in the simulation.

STRUCT WORLD ACCELERATION.name: STRUCT WORLD ACCELERATION
STRUCT WORLD ACCELERATION.description: The world acceleration for each axis. Individual world acceleration values are in the Aircraft Position and Speed section.
STRUCT WORLD ACCELERATION.units: SIMCONNECT_DATA_XYZ structure, feet per second squared

BOMB AMMO.name: BOMB AMMO
BOMB AMMO.description: The amount of bomb ammunition available.

CANNON AMMO.name: CANNON AMMO
CANNON AMMO.description: The amount of cannon ammunition available.

GUN AMMO.name: GUN AMMO
GUN AMMO.description: The amount of gun ammunition available.

ROCKET AMMO.name: ROCKET AMMO
ROCKET AMMO.description: The amount of rocket ammunition available.

BAGGAGELOADER ANGLE CURRENT.name: BAGGAGELOADER ANGLE CURRENT
BAGGAGELOADER ANGLE CURRENT.description: Current angle of the baggage loader ramp, relative to the ground.

BAGGAGELOADER ANGLE TARGET.name: BAGGAGELOADER ANGLE TARGET
BAGGAGELOADER ANGLE TARGET.description: Target angle of the baggage loader ramp, relative to the ground.

BAGGAGELOADER END RAMP Y.name: BAGGAGELOADER END RAMP Y

AP_BANK_HOLD_ON.multiplayer: Turns on the autopilot bank hold mode.

AP_BC_HOLD.multiplayer: Toggles the backcourse mode for the localizer hold

AP_BC_HOLD_OFF.name: AP_BC_HOLD_OFF
AP_BC_HOLD_OFF.multiplayer: Turns off backcourse mode for localizer hold

AP_BC_HOLD_ON.name: AP_BC_HOLD_ON
AP_BC_HOLD_ON.multiplayer: Turns localizer back course hold mode on/armed

AP_LOC_HOLD_ON.name: AP_LOC_HOLD_ON
AP_LOC_HOLD_ON.multiplayer: Turns AP localizer hold on/armed and glide-slope hold mode off

AP_MACH_VAR_DEC.name: AP_MACH_VAR_DEC
AP_MACH_VAR_DEC.description: [0]: the Index of the engine to target (1 - 4)
AP_MACH_VAR_DEC.multiplayer:
Decrements the reference mach by the amount set in the systems.cfg using the mach_increment parameter.
          NOTE: along with the AP_MACH_VAR_DEC, AP_MACH_VAR_SET, and AP_MACH_VAR_SET_EX1 keys, this value is clamped to to the values given in the systems.cfg by the parameters min_Mach_ref and max_Mach_ref (or their default values if not set).

AP_MACH_VAR_INC.name: AP_MACH_VAR_INC
AP_MACH_VAR_INC.description: [0]: Index of the engine to target (1 - 4)
AP_MACH_VAR_INC.multiplayer:
Increments the reference mach by the amount set in the systems.cfg using the mach_increment parameter.
          NOTE: along with the AP_MACH_VAR_INC, AP_MACH_VAR_SET, and AP_MACH_VAR_SET_EX1 keys, this value is clamped to to the values given in the systems.cfg by the parameters min_Mach_ref and max_Mach_ref (or their default values if not set).

AP_MACH_VAR_SET.name: AP_MACH_VAR_SET
AP_MACH_VAR_SET.description:
[0]: Integer mach value / 100 (eg: 100 as value results as mach 1)
          [1]: Index of the engine to target (1 - 4)
AP_MACH_VAR_SET.multiplayer:
Sets the mach reference.
          NOTE: along with the AP_MACH_VAR_DEC, AP_MACH_VAR_INC, and AP_MACH_VAR_SET_EX1 keys, this value is clamped to to the values given in the systems.cfg by the parameters min_Mach_ref and max_Mach_ref (or their default values if not set).

AP_MACH_VAR_SET_EX1.name: AP_MACH_VAR_SET_EX1
AP_MACH_VAR_SET_EX1.description:
[0]: Integer mach value \ 1000000 (eg: 1000 as value results as mach 0.001)
          [1]: Index of the engine to target (1 - 4)
AP_MACH_VAR_SET_EX1.multiplayer:
Sets the mach reference using a precise value.
          NOTE: along with the AP_MACH_VAR_DEC, AP_MACH_VAR_INC, and AP_MACH_VAR_SET keys, this value is clamped to to the values given in the systems.cfg by the parameters min_Mach_ref and max_Mach_ref (or their default values if not set).

AP_MANAGED_SPEED_IN_MACH_OFF.name: AP_MANAGED_SPEED_IN_MACH_OFF
AP_MANAGED_SPEED_IN_MACH_OFF.multiplayer: Turns off the use of the mach value to compute airspeed used by AP.

AP_MANAGED_SPEED_IN_MACH_ON.name: AP_MANAGED_SPEED_IN_MACH_ON
AP_MANAGED_SPEED_IN_MACH_ON.multiplayer: Turns on the use of the mach value to compute airspeed used by AP.

AP_MANAGED_SPEED_IN_MACH_SET.name: AP_MANAGED_SPEED_IN_MACH_SET
AP_MANAGED_SPEED_IN_MACH_SET.multiplayer: Sets the use of the mach value to compute airspeed used by AP.

AP_MANAGED_SPEED_IN_MACH_TOGGLE.name: AP_MANAGED_SPEED_IN_MACH_TOGGLE
AP_MANAGED_SPEED_IN_MACH_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggle the use of the mach value to compute airspeed used by AP.

AP_MASTER_ALT.name: AP_MASTER_ALT
AP_MASTER_ALT.multiplayer:
No longer used in the simulation.
          Use AP_MASTER instead.

AP_MAX_BANK_ANGLE_SET.name: AP_MAX_BANK_ANGLE_SET
AP_MAX_BANK_ANGLE_SET.multiplayer: Set the bank angle for the aircraft and override the predefined max bank angle of the aircraft.

AP_MAX_BANK_INC.name: AP_MAX_BANK_INC
AP_MAX_BANK_INC.multiplayer:
Increment the AP max bank angle index.
          Note that if there is only one index possible then using this event will do nothing. However if there are 2 or more available indices, this event will increase the index by 1, and when the number passes the maximum available indices - 1, it will loop back around again to index 0. For example, if you have 3 indices, the maximum index is 2, and incrementing past that will go to index 0.
          NOTE: for further information on indices, please see the AP_MAX_BANK_SET event.

AP_MAX_BANK_DEC.name: AP_MAX_BANK_DEC
AP_MAX_BANK_DEC.multiplayer:
Decrement the AP max bank angle index.
          Note that if there is only one index possible then using this event will do nothing. However if there are 2 or more available indices, this event will decrease the index by 1, and when the number passes 0, it will loop back around again to the max index - 1 position. For example, if there are 4 indices, and you decrement from 0, the new index will be 3.
          NOTE: for further information on indices, please see the AP_MAX_BANK_SET event.

AP_MAX_BANK_SET.name: AP_MAX_BANK_SET
AP_MAX_BANK_SET.description: [0]: the index to use for max bank angle.
AP_MAX_BANK_SET.multiplayer:
Sets the autopilot max bank angle index to the parameter [0] value, where the value is clamped between 0 and the number of available indices. The indices correspond to the number of values set for the max_bank table, plus index 0 which corresponds to the auto banking system. When auto_max_bank is enabled, setting the index to 0 will turn on the AP auto banking.
          To give an example, if the max_bank table has 2 values and auto_max_bank is enabled, then the indices for this event would be:
          
            0: use auto banking
            1: use the first value in the max_bank table
            2: use the second value in the max_bank table.
          
          If auto banking is not enabled, then setting this to 0 will have no effect.

AP_MAX_BANK_VELOCITY_SET.name: AP_MAX_BANK_VELOCITY_SET
AP_MAX_BANK_VELOCITY_SET.multiplayer: Set the bank velocity of the aircraft and overrides the predifined maximum bank velocity of the aircraft.

AP_N1_HOLD.name: AP_N1_HOLD
AP_N1_HOLD.multiplayer: Autopilot, hold the N1 percentage at its current level.

AP_N1_REF_SET.name: AP_N1_REF_SET
AP_N1_REF_SET.description:
[0]: Integer N1 reference value
          [1]: Index of the engine to target (1 - 4)

AP_NAV_SELECT_SET.name: AP_NAV_SELECT_SET
AP_NAV_SELECT_SET.multiplayer: Sets the NAV (1 or 2) which is used by the Nav hold modes

AP_PANEL_ALTITUDE_ON.name: AP_PANEL_ALTITUDE_ON
AP_PANEL_ALTITUDE_ON.multiplayer: Turns altitude hold mode on (without capturing current altitude)

AP_PANEL_HEADING_ON.name: AP_PANEL_HEADING_ON
AP_PANEL_HEADING_ON.multiplayer: Turns heading mode on (without capturing current heading)

AP_PANEL_VS_OFF.multiplayer: Turn off the AP mode that maintains a vertical speed.

AP_PANEL_VS_ON.name: AP_PANEL_VS_ON
AP_PANEL_VS_ON.multiplayer: Turn on the AP mode that maintains a vertical speed.

AP_PANEL_VS_SET.name: AP_PANEL_VS_SET
AP_PANEL_VS_SET.multiplayer: Enables or diables the AP mode that maintains a vertical speed.

AP_PANEL_VS_HOLD.name: AP_PANEL_VS_HOLD
AP_PANEL_VS_HOLD.multiplayer: Toggles the AP mode that maintains a vertical speed.

AP_PITCH_LEVELER.name: AP_PITCH_LEVELER
AP_PITCH_LEVELER.multiplayer: Toggles the AP mode that maintains the pitch and sets the pitch reference to 0°.

AP_PITCH_LEVELER_OFF.name: AP_PITCH_LEVELER_OFF
AP_PITCH_LEVELER_OFF.multiplayer: Turns off the AP mode that maintains the pitch and sets the pitch reference to 0°.

AP_PITCH_LEVELER_ON.name: AP_PITCH_LEVELER_ON
AP_PITCH_LEVELER_ON.multiplayer: Turns on the AP mode that maintains the pitch and sets the pitch reference to 0°.

AP_PITCH_REF_INC_DN.name: AP_PITCH_REF_INC_DN
AP_PITCH_REF_INC_DN.multiplayer: Decrements the pitch reference for pitch hold mode

AP_PITCH_REF_INC_UP.name: AP_PITCH_REF_INC_UP
AP_PITCH_REF_INC_UP.multiplayer: Increments the pitch reference for pitch hold mode

AP_PITCH_REF_SELECT.name: AP_PITCH_REF_SELECT
AP_PITCH_REF_SELECT.multiplayer: Selects pitch reference for use with +/-

AP_PITCH_REF_SET.name: AP_PITCH_REF_SET
AP_PITCH_REF_SET.multiplayer: Sets the pitch reference value that will be maintained by the AP pitch hold mode. The pitch value supplied as parameter [0] will be divided by 16384 before being multiplied by the max_pitch value.

AP_RPM_SLOT_INDEX_SET.name: AP_RPM_SLOT_INDEX_SET
AP_RPM_SLOT_INDEX_SET.multiplayer: Sets the managed index for the RPM hold mode.

AP_SPD_VAR_SET.name: AP_SPD_VAR_SET
AP_SPD_VAR_SET.description:
[0]: value in Knots.
          [1]: the managed index, from 1 to 4, or 0.

AP_SPD_VAR_SET_EX1.name: AP_SPD_VAR_SET_EX1
AP_SPD_VAR_SET_EX1.description:
[0]: value in Knots.
          [1]: the managed index, from 1 to 4, or 0.
AP_SPD_VAR_SET_EX1.multiplayer: Set the airspeed reference, in knots, for the maintain speed AP mode. The speed supplied as parameter [0] will be divided by 100 to give you more precision with the value, for example: giving 55050 will result in an airspeed hold of 550.50 knots. For parameter [1], giving a value of 0 instead of a single index from 1 to 4, then the speed value will be copied to all managed indices.

AP_SPEED_SLOT_INDEX_SET.name: AP_SPEED_SLOT_INDEX_SET
AP_SPEED_SLOT_INDEX_SET.multiplayer: Sets the managed index for the speed hold mode.

AP_VS_HOLD.name: AP_VS_HOLD
AP_VS_HOLD.multiplayer: Toggles the AP mode that maintains a vertical speed.

AP_VS_OFF.name: AP_VS_OFF
AP_VS_OFF.multiplayer: Turn off the AP mode that maintains a vertical speed.

AP_VS_ON.name: AP_VS_ON
AP_VS_ON.multiplayer: Turn on the AP mode that maintains a vertical speed.

AP_VS_SET.name: AP_VS_SET
AP_VS_SET.multiplayer: Sets the AP mode that maintains a vertical speed.

AP_VS_SLOT_INDEX_SET.name: AP_VS_SLOT_INDEX_SET
AP_VS_SLOT_INDEX_SET.multiplayer: Sets the managed index for the vertical speed hold mode.

AP_VS_VAR_SET_CURRENT.name: AP_VS_VAR_SET_CURRENT
AP_VS_VAR_SET_CURRENT.multiplayer: Sets the current managed index vertical speed reference to be the current vertical speed (the current index can be set using AP_VS_SLOT_INDEX_SET). If no vertical speed indicator is on the aircraft, the vertical speed reference will calculated based on the world Y-axis velocity. Note that the resulting value will be clamped between the CFG parameters min_vertical_speed_ref and max_vertical_speed_ref.

AP_VS_VAR_SET_ENGLISH.name: AP_VS_VAR_SET_ENGLISH
AP_VS_VAR_SET_ENGLISH.multiplayer: Sets reference vertical speed in feet per minute

AP_VS_VAR_SET_METRIC.name: AP_VS_VAR_SET_METRIC
AP_VS_VAR_SET_METRIC.multiplayer: Sets vertical speed reference in meters per minute

AP_PANEL_SPEED_HOLD_TOGGLE.name: AP_PANEL_SPEED_HOLD_TOGGLE
AP_PANEL_SPEED_HOLD_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turns airspeed hold mode on with current airspeed

AP_PANEL_MACH_HOLD_TOGGLE.name: AP_PANEL_MACH_HOLD_TOGGLE
AP_PANEL_MACH_HOLD_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Sets mach hold reference to current mach

AUTOPILOT_DISENGAGE_SET.name: AUTOPILOT_DISENGAGE_SET
AUTOPILOT_DISENGAGE_SET.description: [0]: boolean value to enable/disable the disengage value
AUTOPILOT_DISENGAGE_SET.multiplayer: Set if the AP should be disengaged or not.

AUTOPILOT_DISENGAGE_TOGGLE.name: AUTOPILOT_DISENGAGE_TOGGLE
AUTOPILOT_DISENGAGE_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggle the status of the AP disengage value.

AUTOPILOT_PANEL_AIRSPEED_SET.name: AUTOPILOT_PANEL_AIRSPEED_SET
AUTOPILOT_PANEL_AIRSPEED_SET.multiplayer: Not currently used in the simulation.

AUTOPILOT_PANEL_CRUISE_SPEED.name: AUTOPILOT_PANEL_CRUISE_SPEED
AUTOPILOT_PANEL_CRUISE_SPEED.multiplayer:
No longer used in the simulation.
          Previously used by the Concorde flight model.

AUTOPILOT_PANEL_MAX_SPEED.name: AUTOPILOT_PANEL_MAX_SPEED
AUTOPILOT_PANEL_MAX_SPEED.multiplayer:
No longer used in the simulation.
          Previously used by the Concorde flight model.

ALTITUDE_SLOT_INDEX_SET.multiplayer: Sets the index for the SimVar AUTOPILOT ALTITUDE LOCK VAR which the altitude hold mode will track when captured. See alt_mode_slot_index for more information.

FLIGHT_LEVEL_CHANGE.name: FLIGHT_LEVEL_CHANGE
FLIGHT_LEVEL_CHANGE.multiplayer: Toggles the autopilot FLC mode on or off. When on, the AP will adjust the engine power to try and fly the aircraft at a pitch attitude corresponding to the desired flight profile (climb or descent), while maintaining the airspeed reference.

FLIGHT_LEVEL_CHANGE_OFF.name: FLIGHT_LEVEL_CHANGE_OFF
FLIGHT_LEVEL_CHANGE_OFF.multiplayer: Turns off the autopilot FLC mode.

FLIGHT_LEVEL_CHANGE_ON.name: FLIGHT_LEVEL_CHANGE_ON
FLIGHT_LEVEL_CHANGE_ON.multiplayer: Turn on the autopilot FLC mode. This mode adjusts engine power to fly the aircraft at a pitch attitude corresponding to the desired flight profile (climb or descent), while maintaining the airspeed reference.

VS_SLOT_INDEX_SET.name: VS_SLOT_INDEX_SET
VS_SLOT_INDEX_SET.multiplayer: Set autopilot vertical speed slot index.

AIRSPEED_BUG_SELECT.name: AIRSPEED_BUG_SELECT
AIRSPEED_BUG_SELECT.multiplayer: Selects the airspeed reference for use with +/-

ALTITUDE_BUG_SELECT.name: ALTITUDE_BUG_SELECT
ALTITUDE_BUG_SELECT.multiplayer: Selects the altitude reference for use with +/-

AUTO_THROTTLE_DISCONNECT.name: AUTO_THROTTLE_DISCONNECT
AUTO_THROTTLE_DISCONNECT.description: [0]: The engine to target. Use 0 to target all engines, or 1 to 4 to target a specific engine.
AUTO_THROTTLE_DISCONNECT.multiplayer: Disconnect the AutoThrottle of the AP for one engine or all engines.

AUTOBRAKE_DISARM.name: AUTOBRAKE_DISARM
AUTOBRAKE_DISARM.multiplayer:
Sets the autobrake switch to either :
          
            the off position (position 1) when the auto_brakes parameter is greater than 0.
            the RTO position (position 0) when the auto_brakes parameter is 0.

AUTOBRAKE_HI_SET.name: AUTOBRAKE_HI_SET
AUTOBRAKE_HI_SET.multiplayer: Sets the autobrake switch to the maximum position (ie: the auto_brakes number, so that the maximum braking force will be applied).

AUTOBRAKE_LO_SET.name: AUTOBRAKE_LO_SET
AUTOBRAKE_LO_SET.multiplayer: Sets the autobrake switch to the minimum position (position 2, the first position after the off position).

AUTOBRAKE_MED_SET.name: AUTOBRAKE_MED_SET
AUTOBRAKE_MED_SET.multiplayer: Sets the autobrake switch to a medium position (the exact position will depend on the number of autobreaks defined by the auto_brakes parameter).

DECREASE_AUTOBRAKE_CONTROL.name: DECREASE_AUTOBRAKE_CONTROL
DECREASE_AUTOBRAKE_CONTROL.multiplayer: Decrements the autobrake level by 1. When the level reaches 0, autobreaks will be off, and the event will no longer decrement further.

FLY_BY_WIRE_ELAC_TOGGLE.name: FLY_BY_WIRE_ELAC_TOGGLE
FLY_BY_WIRE_ELAC_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turn on or off the fly by wire Elevators and Ailerons computer.

FLY_BY_WIRE_FAC_TOGGLE.name: FLY_BY_WIRE_FAC_TOGGLE
FLY_BY_WIRE_FAC_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turn on or off the fly by wire Flight Augmentation computer.

FLY_BY_WIRE_SEC_TOGGLE.name: FLY_BY_WIRE_SEC_TOGGLE
FLY_BY_WIRE_SEC_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turn on or off the fly by wire Spoilers and Elevators computer.

GPWS_SWITCH_TOGGLE.name: GPWS_SWITCH_TOGGLE
GPWS_SWITCH_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turn the ground proximity warning system (GPWS) on or off.

HEADING_BUG_SELECT.name: HEADING_BUG_SELECT
HEADING_BUG_SELECT.multiplayer: Selects the heading bug for use with +/-

HEADING_BUG_SET.name: HEADING_BUG_SET
HEADING_BUG_SET.multiplayer: Set the heading hold reference bug in degrees. The event takes integer values only, from 0o to 360o.

AP_HEADING_BUG_SET_EX1.name: AP_HEADING_BUG_SET_EX1
AP_HEADING_BUG_SET_EX1.multiplayer:
Set the heading hold reference bug. This is the same as the HEADING_BUG_SET event only it permits a much greater degree of precision by permitting the input of a larger integer value that is then transformed by the simulation into a floating point heading. The way this works is that the integer value you supply is multiplied by (360/16384) to give the correct higher precision value, for example if you supply the value 477, you're heading would be calculated like this:
          input value: 477
process: 477 * (360/16384)
actual value: 10.504o

INCREASE_AUTOBRAKE_CONTROL.name: INCREASE_AUTOBRAKE_CONTROL
INCREASE_AUTOBRAKE_CONTROL.multiplayer: Increases the autobrake level by 1. When the level reaches the auto_brakes value, the event will no longer increment further.

SET_AUTOBRAKE_CONTROL.name: SET_AUTOBRAKE_CONTROL
SET_AUTOBRAKE_CONTROL.multiplayer: Uses the input parameter [0] to set the autobreak level from 0 (off) to the value set for the auto_brakes parameter (maximum breaking). If a value greater than that specified for auto_brakes is given as input, it will be clamped to the auto_brakes value.

SYNC_FLIGHT_DIRECTOR_PITCH.name: SYNC_FLIGHT_DIRECTOR_PITCH
SYNC_FLIGHT_DIRECTOR_PITCH.multiplayer: Synchronizes flight director pitch with current aircraft pitch

VSI_BUG_SELECT.name: VSI_BUG_SELECT
VSI_BUG_SELECT.multiplayer: Selects the vertical speed reference for use with +/-
