ANTI_ICE_GRADUAL_SET_ENG1.multiplayer: Sets the engine 1/2/3/4 anti-ice switch to a value between 0 and 16384.

ANTI_ICE_ON.name: ANTI_ICE_ON
ANTI_ICE_ON.multiplayer:
Sets anti-ice switches on
          Controlled engines are set through the SimVar ENGINE CONTROL SELECT.

ANTI_ICE_OFF.name: ANTI_ICE_OFF
ANTI_ICE_OFF.multiplayer:
Sets anti-ice switches off.
          Controlled engines are set through the SimVar ENGINE CONTROL SELECT.

ANTI_ICE_SET.name: ANTI_ICE_SET
ANTI_ICE_SET.multiplayer: Sets anti-ice switches from argument (0,1). Controlled engines are set through the SimVar ENGINE CONTROL SELECT.

ANTI_ICE_TOGGLE.name: ANTI_ICE_TOGGLE
ANTI_ICE_TOGGLE.multiplayer:
Toggle anti-ice switches.
          Controlled engines are set through the SimVar ENGINE CONTROL SELECT.

ANTI_ICE_TOGGLE_ENG1.name: ANTI_ICE_TOGGLE_ENG1
ANTI_ICE_TOGGLE_ENG1.multiplayer: Toggle engine 1/2/3/4 anti-ice switch on (1) or off (0).

AXIS_CONDITION_LEVER_1_SET.name: AXIS_CONDITION_LEVER_1_SET
AXIS_CONDITION_LEVER_1_SET.multiplayer:
Sets the condition lever position based on the percentage final value of axis the input where:
          
            0% - 33.3% = cutoff
            33.3% - 66.6% = low idle
            66.6% - 100% = high

CONDITION_LEVER_CUT_OFF.name: CONDITION_LEVER_CUT_OFF
CONDITION_LEVER_CUT_OFF.multiplayer:
Sets the condition lever for the indexed engine to the cutoff position, which cuts the fuel flow.
          Not currently used in the simulation.

CONDITION_LEVER_DEC.name: CONDITION_LEVER_DEC
CONDITION_LEVER_DEC.multiplayer:
Decrements the condition lever position by one for the indexed engine. The possible lever positions are as follows:
          
            0 for cutoff
            1 for low idle
            2 for high

CONDITION_LEVER_HIGH_IDLE.name: CONDITION_LEVER_HIGH_IDLE
CONDITION_LEVER_HIGH_IDLE.multiplayer:
Sets the condition lever for the indexed engine to the high position (2).
          Not currently used in the simulation.

CONDITION_LEVER_INC.name: CONDITION_LEVER_INC
CONDITION_LEVER_INC.multiplayer:
Increments the condition lever position by one for the indexed engine. The possible lever positions are as follows:
          
            0 for cutoff
            1 for low idle
            2 for high

CONDITION_LEVER_LOW_IDLE.name: CONDITION_LEVER_LOW_IDLE
CONDITION_LEVER_LOW_IDLE.multiplayer:
Sets the condition lever for the indexed engine to the low position (1).
          Not currently used in the simulation.

CONDITION_LEVER_SET.name: CONDITION_LEVER_SET
CONDITION_LEVER_SET.multiplayer:
Sets the condition lever for the all engines to the given position, which is one of the following:
          
            0 for cutoff
            1 for low idle
            2 for high

CONDITION_LEVER_1_CUT_OFF.name: CONDITION_LEVER_1_CUT_OFF
CONDITION_LEVER_1_CUT_OFF.multiplayer:
Sets the condition lever for engine 1/2/3/4 to the cutoff position, which cuts the fuel flow.
          Not currently used in the simulation.

CONDITION_LEVER_1_DEC.name: CONDITION_LEVER_1_DEC
CONDITION_LEVER_1_DEC.multiplayer:
Decreases the condition lever position by one for engine 1/2/3/4. The possible lever positions are as follows:
          
            0 for cutoff
            1 for low idle
            2 for high

CONDITION_LEVER_1_HIGH_IDLE.name: CONDITION_LEVER_1_HIGH_IDLE
CONDITION_LEVER_1_HIGH_IDLE.multiplayer:
Sets the condition lever for engine 1/2/3/4 to the high position (2).
          Not currently used in the simulation.

CONDITION_LEVER_1_INC.name: CONDITION_LEVER_1_INC
CONDITION_LEVER_1_INC.multiplayer:
Increments the condition lever position by one for engine 1/2/3/4. The possible lever positions are as follows:
          
            0 for cutoff
            1 for low idle
            2 for high

CONDITION_LEVER_1_LOW_IDLE.name: CONDITION_LEVER_1_LOW_IDLE
CONDITION_LEVER_1_LOW_IDLE.multiplayer:
Sets the condition lever for engine 1/2/3/4 to the low position (1).
          Not currently used in the simulation.

CONDITION_LEVER_1_SET.name: CONDITION_LEVER_1_SET
CONDITION_LEVER_1_SET.multiplayer:
Sets the condition lever for engine 1/2/3/4 to the given position, which is one of the following:
          
            0 for cutoff
            1 for low idle
            2 for high

MIXTURE_LEAN.name: MIXTURE_LEAN
MIXTURE_LEAN.multiplayer: Set mixture levers to max lean

MIXTURE1_LEAN.name: MIXTURE1_LEAN
MIXTURE1_LEAN.multiplayer: Set mixture lever 1/2/3/4 to max lean

MIXTURE_RICH.name: MIXTURE_RICH
MIXTURE_RICH.multiplayer: Set mixture levers to max rich

MIXTURE1_RICH.name: MIXTURE1_RICH
MIXTURE1_RICH.multiplayer: Set mixture lever 1/2/3/4 to max rich

SHUTOFF_VALVE_TOGGLE.name: SHUTOFF_VALVE_TOGGLE
SHUTOFF_VALVE_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggle the status of the fuel shutoff valve (used on piston engine to enable/disable fuel arrival).

SHUTOFF_VALVE_ON.name: SHUTOFF_VALVE_ON
SHUTOFF_VALVE_ON.multiplayer: Turns on the fuel shutoff valve (used on piston engines to enable fuel arrival).

SHUTOFF_VALVE_OFF.name: SHUTOFF_VALVE_OFF
SHUTOFF_VALVE_OFF.multiplayer: Turns off the fuel shutoff valve (used on piston engines to disable fuel arrival).

MAGNETO_SET.name: MAGNETO_SET
MAGNETO_SET.multiplayer:
Sets all engine magnetos (0,1)
          Not currently used in the simulation.

MAGNETO1_SET.name: MAGNETO1_SET
MAGNETO1_SET.multiplayer:
Set engine 1/2/3/4 magneto switch
          Not currently used in the simulation.

MAGNETO_START.name: MAGNETO_START
MAGNETO_START.multiplayer: Set all engine magnetos on and toggle starters

MAGNETO1_START.name: MAGNETO1_START
MAGNETO1_START.multiplayer: Set engine 1/2/3/4 magnetos on and toggle starter

COWLFLAP1_SET.name: COWLFLAP1_SET
COWLFLAP1_SET.description:
[0]: position from 0 to 16983  COWLFLAP2_SET
          COWLFLAP3_SET
          COWLFLAP4_SET
COWLFLAP1_SET.multiplayer: Sets engine 1/2/3/4 cowl flap lever position (0 to 16383)

ENGINE.name: ENGINE
ENGINE.multiplayer: Sets engines for 1,2,3,4 selection (to be followed by SELECT_n)

ENGINE_BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_SET.name: ENGINE_BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_SET
ENGINE_BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_SET.description:
[0]: The engine index to target (from 1 to 4)
          [1]: Set to TRUE/FALSE to set the engine as source (TRUE) or not (FALSE)
ENGINE_BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_SET.multiplayer: Sets if the indexed engine is a source to the bleed air system or not.

ENGINE_BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_TOGGLE.name: ENGINE_BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_TOGGLE
ENGINE_BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_TOGGLE.description: [0]: The engine index to target (from 1 to 4, or 0 for all engines)
ENGINE_BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggles the indexed engine as a source to the bleed air system. Note that if you supply 0 instead of a single engine index, then the event will target all engines.

AXIS_PROPELLER_SET.name: AXIS_PROPELLER_SET
AXIS_PROPELLER_SET.multiplayer: Set propeller levers exact value (-16383 to +16383)

AXIS_PROPELLER1_SET.name: AXIS_PROPELLER1_SET
AXIS_PROPELLER1_SET.multiplayer: Set propeller lever 1/2/3/4 exact value (-16383 to +16383)

PROP_FORCE_BETA_OFF.name: PROP_FORCE_BETA_OFF
PROP_FORCE_BETA_OFF.description: [0]: The engine index to target (from 1 to 4, or 0 for all engines)
PROP_FORCE_BETA_OFF.multiplayer: This key allows you to disable the propeller Force Beta mode, in which case the internal coded simulation logic to drive the beta is used instead of the value from PROP BETA FORCED POSITION.

PROP_FORCE_BETA_ON.name: PROP_FORCE_BETA_ON
PROP_FORCE_BETA_ON.description: [0]: The engine index to target (from 1 to 4, or 0 for all engines)
PROP_FORCE_BETA_ON.multiplayer: This keys allows you to enable the propeller Force Beta mode, in which case the sim logic to drive the beta is ignored and instead the value from PROP BETA FORCED POSITION is used.

PROP_FORCE_BETA_SET.name: PROP_FORCE_BETA_SET
PROP_FORCE_BETA_SET.description:
[0]: The engine index to target (from 1 to 4, or 0 for all engines)
          [1]: Whether or not to force the prop beta (Boolean).
PROP_FORCE_BETA_SET.multiplayer: This key allows you to set the propeller to be in Force Beta mode, in which case the internal coded simulation logic that normally drives the beta is ignored and instead the value from PROP BETA FORCED POSITION is used.

PROP_FORCE_BETA_TOGGLE.name: PROP_FORCE_BETA_TOGGLE
PROP_FORCE_BETA_TOGGLE.description: [0]: The engine index to target (from 1 to 4, or 0 for all engines)
PROP_FORCE_BETA_TOGGLE.multiplayer: This key allows you to toggle between the normal and Force Beta mode. If enabled, the Force Beta mode will prevent the internal coded simulation logic from driving the beta and instead allow you to control it with the value from PROP BETA FORCED POSITION.

PROP_FORCE_BETA_VALUE_SET.name: PROP_FORCE_BETA_VALUE_SET
PROP_FORCE_BETA_VALUE_SET.description:
[0]: The engine index to target (from 1 to 4, or 0 for all engines)
          [1]: The angle that the prop should be forced to. This is stored as the 16k representation of an angle between -180 degrees and + 180 degrees
PROP_FORCE_BETA_VALUE_SET.multiplayer: This key allows you to set the value that the prop will attempt to reach when in Forced Beta mode (this will have the same effect as setting the PROP BETA FORCED POSITION SimVar).

PROP_PITCH_HI.name: PROP_PITCH_HI
PROP_PITCH_HI.multiplayer: Set prop pitch levers min (hi pitch)

PROP_PITCH1_HI.name: PROP_PITCH1_HI
PROP_PITCH1_HI.multiplayer: Set prop pitch lever 1/2/3/4 min (hi pitch)

PROP_PITCH_HI_EX1.name: PROP_PITCH_HI_EX1
PROP_PITCH_HI_EX1.multiplayer: Set prop pitch levers min (hi pitch)

PROP_PITCH1_HI_EX1.name: PROP_PITCH1_HI_EX1
PROP_PITCH1_HI_EX1.multiplayer: Set prop pitch lever 1/2/3/4 min (hi pitch)

PROP_PITCH_LO.name: PROP_PITCH_LO
PROP_PITCH_LO.multiplayer: Set prop pitch levers max (lo pitch)

PROP_PITCH1_LO.name: PROP_PITCH1_LO
PROP_PITCH1_LO.multiplayer: Set prop pitch lever 1/2/3/4 max (lo pitch)

PROP_PITCH_LO_EX1.name: PROP_PITCH_LO_EX1
PROP_PITCH_LO_EX1.multiplayer: Set prop pitch levers max (lo pitch)

PROP_PITCH1_LO_EX1.name: PROP_PITCH1_LO_EX1
PROP_PITCH1_LO_EX1.multiplayer: Set prop pitch lever 1/2/3/4 max (lo pitch)

PROP_PITCH1_SET.name: PROP_PITCH1_SET
PROP_PITCH1_SET.multiplayer: Set prop pitch lever 1/2/3/4 exact value (0 to 16383)

AXIS_THROTTLE_MINUS.name: AXIS_THROTTLE_MINUS
AXIS_THROTTLE_MINUS.multiplayer: Subtracts the given value from the throttle of all engines (the final position will depend on the min_throttle_limit value).

AXIS_THROTTLE_PLUS.name: AXIS_THROTTLE_PLUS
AXIS_THROTTLE_PLUS.multiplayer: Adds to the throttle of all engines a value comprised between 0 and 16384.

SET_REVERSE_THRUST_OFF.name: SET_REVERSE_THRUST_OFF
SET_REVERSE_THRUST_OFF.multiplayer: Turn off throttle reverse thrust for all engines.

SET_REVERSE_THRUST_ON.name: SET_REVERSE_THRUST_ON
SET_REVERSE_THRUST_ON.multiplayer: Turn on throttle reverse thrust for all engines.

SET_THROTTLE1_REVERSE_THRUST_OFF.name: SET_THROTTLE1_REVERSE_THRUST_OFF
SET_THROTTLE1_REVERSE_THRUST_OFF.multiplayer: Turn off the throttle reverse thrust for engine 1/2/3/4.

SET_THROTTLE1_REVERSE_THRUST_ON.name: SET_THROTTLE1_REVERSE_THRUST_ON
SET_THROTTLE1_REVERSE_THRUST_ON.multiplayer: Turn on the throttle reverse thrust for engine 1/2/3/4.

TOGGLE_THROTTLE1_REVERSE_THRUST.name: TOGGLE_THROTTLE1_REVERSE_THRUST
TOGGLE_THROTTLE1_REVERSE_THRUST.multiplayer: Toggle on or off the reverse thruster for engine 1/2/3/4

ISOLATE_TURBINE_SET.name: ISOLATE_TURBINE_SET
ISOLATE_TURBINE_SET.multiplayer:
Setting this to TRUE will "isolate" the engine, effectively nullyfing the engine drag and thrust.
          This key takes two parameters: an engine number (from 1 to 4 to flag a specific engine, or 0 to affect all engines), and a TRUE / FALSE second parameter to set the engine isolation.
          IMPORTANT: This event is only applicable to the DarkStar aircraft and should not be used for your own aircraft.

ISOLATE_TURBINE_ON.name: ISOLATE_TURBINE_ON
ISOLATE_TURBINE_ON.multiplayer:
Using this key will "isolate" the given engine, effectively nullyfing the engine drag and thrust.
          This key takes an engine number as a parameter (from 1 to 4 to flag a specific engine, or 0 to affect all engines).
          IMPORTANT: This event is only applicable to the DarkStar aircraft and should not be used for your own aircraft.

ISOLATE_TURBINE_OFF.name: ISOLATE_TURBINE_OFF
ISOLATE_TURBINE_OFF.multiplayer:
Using this key will end the "isolation" for the engine, effectively enabling the engine drag and thrust again.
          This key takes an engine number as a parameter (from 1 to 4 to flag a specific engine, or 0 to affect all engines).
          IMPORTANT: This event is only applicable to the DarkStar aircraft and should not be used for your own aircraft.

ISOLATE_TURBINE_TOGGLE.name: ISOLATE_TURBINE_TOGGLE
ISOLATE_TURBINE_TOGGLE.multiplayer:
This key can be used to toggle an engines "isolated" state, where an isolated engine has its drag and thrust effectively nullified.
          This key takes an engine number as a parameter (from 1 to 4 to flag a specific engine, or 0 to affect all engines).
          IMPORTANT: This event is only applicable to the DarkStar aircraft and should not be used for your own aircraft.

TURBINE_IGNITION_SWITCH_TOGGLE.name: TURBINE_IGNITION_SWITCH_TOGGLE
TURBINE_IGNITION_SWITCH_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turn the turbine ignition switch on or off.

SET_STARTER1_HELD.name: SET_STARTER1_HELD
SET_STARTER1_HELD.multiplayer: Set the Starter for engine 1 to on or off. If set to on (TRUE) the starter will stay on, and setting the event to off (FALSE) will disable the starter, but only after the engine RPM is above the 50% threshold. To disable the starter immediately you should use STARTER1_SET, and note that turbine engines will need both these events triggered to off (FALSE).

SET_STARTER2_HELD.name: SET_STARTER2_HELD
SET_STARTER2_HELD.multiplayer: Set the Starter for engine 2 to on or off. If set to on (TRUE) the starter will stay on, and setting the event to off (FALSE) will disable the starter, but only after the engine RPM is above the 50% threshold. To disable the starter immediately you should use STARTER2_SET, and note that turbine engines will need both these events triggered to off (FALSE).

SET_STARTER3_HELD.name: SET_STARTER3_HELD
SET_STARTER3_HELD.multiplayer: Set the Starter for engine 3 to on or off. If set to on (TRUE) the starter will stay on, and setting the event to off (FALSE) will disable the starter, but only after the engine RPM is above the 50% threshold. To disable the starter immediately you should use STARTER3_SET, and note that turbine engines will need both these events triggered to off (FALSE).

SET_STARTER4_HELD.name: SET_STARTER4_HELD
SET_STARTER4_HELD.multiplayer: Set the Starter for engine 4 to on or off. If set to on (TRUE) the starter will stay on, and setting the event to off (FALSE) will disable the starter, but only after the engine RPM is above the 50% threshold. To disable the starter immediately you should use STARTER4_SET, and note that turbine engines will need both these events triggered to off (FALSE).

SET_STARTER_ALL_HELD.name: SET_STARTER_ALL_HELD
SET_STARTER_ALL_HELD.multiplayer: Set the Starter for all engines to on or off. If set to on (TRUE) the starter will stay on until set to off (FALSE) with another call to the event.

STARTER_SET.name: STARTER_SET
STARTER_SET.multiplayer: Set the status of the current controlled engine starters to On/Off. Controlled engines are set through the SimVar ENGINE CONTROL SELECT.

STARTER1_SET.name: STARTER1_SET
STARTER1_SET.multiplayer: Set the Starter for engine 1 to on or off. Note that the starter will only stay on for a short time before switching itself off again on piston engines. If you wish the starter to stay on, use SET_STARTER1_HELD.

STARTER2_SET.name: STARTER2_SET
STARTER2_SET.multiplayer: Set the Starter for engine 1 to on or off. Note that the starter will only stay on for a short time before switching itself off again on piston engines. If you wish the starter to stay on, use SET_STARTER2_HELD.

STARTER3_SET.name: STARTER3_SET
STARTER3_SET.multiplayer: Set the Starter for engine 1 to on or off. Note that the starter will only stay on for a short time before switching itself off again on piston engines. If you wish the starter to stay on, use SET_STARTER3_HELD.

STARTER4_SET.name: STARTER4_SET
STARTER4_SET.multiplayer: Set the Starter for engine 1 to on or off. Note that the starter will only stay on for a short time before switching itself off again on piston engines. If you wish the starter to stay on, use SET_STARTER4_HELD.

AILERON_CENTER.name: AILERON_CENTER
AILERON_CENTER.multiplayer:
Centers aileron position. Note that this is simply an alias for the CENTER_AILER_RUDDER event.
          Not currently used in the simulation.

AILERON_LEFT.name: AILERON_LEFT
AILERON_LEFT.multiplayer: Increments the left aileron by 1°. Note that this is simply an alias for the AILERONS_LEFT event.

AILERON_RIGHT.name: AILERON_RIGHT
AILERON_RIGHT.multiplayer: Increments the right aileron by 1°. Note that this is simply an alias for the AILERONS_RIGHT event.

AILERON_TRIM_DISABLED_SET.name: AILERON_TRIM_DISABLED_SET
AILERON_TRIM_DISABLED_SET.multiplayer: Enable (1, TRUE) or disable (0, FALSE) the aileron trim.

AILERON_TRIM_DISABLED_TOGGLE.name: AILERON_TRIM_DISABLED_TOGGLE
AILERON_TRIM_DISABLED_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggle the aileron trim disabled option between on (1) and off (0).

AILERON_TRIM_LEFT.name: AILERON_TRIM_LEFT
AILERON_TRIM_LEFT.multiplayer: Increments the left aileron trim by 0.001.

AILERON_TRIM_RIGHT.name: AILERON_TRIM_RIGHT
AILERON_TRIM_RIGHT.multiplayer: Increments the right aileron trim by 0.001.

AILERON_TRIM_SET_EX1.name: AILERON_TRIM_SET_EX1
AILERON_TRIM_SET_EX1.multiplayer: Sets the aileron trim with extra precision.

CENTER_AILER_RUDDER.name: CENTER_AILER_RUDDER
CENTER_AILER_RUDDER.multiplayer: Centers the aileron and rudder positions.

AXIS_ELEV_TRIM_SET.name: AXIS_ELEV_TRIM_SET
AXIS_ELEV_TRIM_SET.multiplayer: Sets the elevator trim position (input will be normalised to a value between -1 and 1).

AXIS_ELEVATOR_SET.name: AXIS_ELEVATOR_SET
AXIS_ELEVATOR_SET.multiplayer: Sets the elevator position (input will be normalised to a value between -1 and 1). Note that this is simply an alias for the ELEVATOR_SET event.

ELEV_DOWN.name: ELEV_DOWN
ELEV_DOWN.multiplayer:
Decrements the elevator by -0.05 (to a minimum of -1). When the key is released the elevator will return to it's original position.
          Note that this is simply an alias for the ELEVATOR_DOWN event.

ELEV_TRIM_DN.name: ELEV_TRIM_DN
ELEV_TRIM_DN.multiplayer: Decrements the elevator trim by -0.0005. Holding down the key will cause the trim to decrement faster over time.

ELEV_TRIM_UP.name: ELEV_TRIM_UP
ELEV_TRIM_UP.multiplayer: Increments the elevator trim by 0.0005. Holding down the key will cause the trim to increment faster over time.

ELEV_UP.name: ELEV_UP
ELEV_UP.multiplayer:
Increments elevator by 0.05 (to a maximum of 1). When the key is released the elevator will return to it's original position.
          Note that this is simply an alias for the ELEVATOR_UP event.

ELEVATOR_DOWN.name: ELEVATOR_DOWN
ELEVATOR_DOWN.multiplayer: Decrements the elevator by -0.05 (to a minimum of -1). When the key is released the elevator will return to it's original position.

ELEVATOR_SET.name: ELEVATOR_SET
ELEVATOR_SET.multiplayer: Sets elevator position (input will be normalised to a value between -1 and 1).

ELEVATOR_TRIM_DISABLED_SET.name: ELEVATOR_TRIM_DISABLED_SET
ELEVATOR_TRIM_DISABLED_SET.multiplayer: Sets the Elevator Trim Disabled to be on (TRUE) or off (FALSE).

ELEVATOR_TRIM_DISABLED_TOGGLE.name: ELEVATOR_TRIM_DISABLED_TOGGLE
ELEVATOR_TRIM_DISABLED_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggles the Elevator Trim Disabled between on (1, TRUE) and off (0, FALSE).

ELEVATOR_UP.name: ELEVATOR_UP
ELEVATOR_UP.multiplayer: Increments the elevator by 0.05 (to a maximum of 1). When the key is released the elevator will return to it's original position.

AXIS_FLAPS_SET.name: AXIS_FLAPS_SET
AXIS_FLAPS_SET.multiplayer: Sets flap handle to closest increment (-16383 - +16383)

FLAPS_1.name: FLAPS_1
FLAPS_1.multiplayer: Sets flap handle to first extension position

FLAPS_2.name: FLAPS_2
FLAPS_2.multiplayer: Sets flap handle to second extension position

FLAPS_3.name: FLAPS_3
FLAPS_3.multiplayer: Sets flap handle to third extension position

FLAPS_4.name: FLAPS_4
FLAPS_4.multiplayer: Sets flap handle to fourth extension position

FLAPS_DOWN.name: FLAPS_DOWN
FLAPS_DOWN.multiplayer: Sets flap handle to full extension position

FLAPS_SET.name: FLAPS_SET
FLAPS_SET.multiplayer: Sets flap handle to closest increment (0 to 16383)

FLAPS_UP.name: FLAPS_UP
FLAPS_UP.multiplayer: Sets flap handle to full retract position

CENTER_NT361_CHECK.name: CENTER_NT361_CHECK
CENTER_NT361_CHECK.multiplayer: Check to see if NT 361 Flight Trainer should be centered

CHVPP_LEFT_HAT_UP.name: CHVPP_LEFT_HAT_UP
CHVPP_LEFT_HAT_UP.multiplayer: CH Virtual Pilot Pro up - left hat keypress.

CHVPP_LEFT_HAT_DOWN.name: CHVPP_LEFT_HAT_DOWN
CHVPP_LEFT_HAT_DOWN.multiplayer: CH Virtual Pilot Pro down - left hat keypress.

CHVPP_AP_ALT_WING.name: CHVPP_AP_ALT_WING
CHVPP_AP_ALT_WING.multiplayer: CH Virtual Pilot Pro altitude hold and wing level.

MOUSE_AS_YOKE_RESUME.name: MOUSE_AS_YOKE_RESUME
MOUSE_AS_YOKE_RESUME.multiplayer: Not currently used in the simulation.

MOUSE_AS_YOKE_SUSPEND.name: MOUSE_AS_YOKE_SUSPEND
MOUSE_AS_YOKE_SUSPEND.multiplayer: Not currently used in the simulation.

MOUSE_AS_YOKE_TOGGLE.name: MOUSE_AS_YOKE_TOGGLE
MOUSE_AS_YOKE_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Not currently used in the simulation.

AUTORUDDER_TOGGLE.name: AUTORUDDER_TOGGLE
AUTORUDDER_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turn the automatic rudder control feature on or off.

RUDDER_TRIM_DISABLED_SET.name: RUDDER_TRIM_DISABLED_SET
RUDDER_TRIM_DISABLED_SET.multiplayer: Enables (TRUE) or disables (FALSE) the rudder trim.

RUDDER_TRIM_DISABLED_TOGGLE.name: RUDDER_TRIM_DISABLED_TOGGLE
RUDDER_TRIM_DISABLED_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggles the rudder trim on (TRUE) or off (FALSE).

RUDDER_TRIM_SET.name: RUDDER_TRIM_SET
RUDDER_TRIM_SET.multiplayer: Sets the rudder trim value, between -100 and 100.

RUDDER_TRIM_SET_EX1.name: RUDDER_TRIM_SET_EX1
RUDDER_TRIM_SET_EX1.multiplayer: Sets the rudder trim value, between -16383 and 16383.

SLEW_HEADING_MINUS.name: SLEW_HEADING_MINUS
SLEW_HEADING_MINUS.multiplayer: Increase slew heading to the left

SLEW_HEADING_PLUS.name: SLEW_HEADING_PLUS
SLEW_HEADING_PLUS.multiplayer: Increase slew heading to the right

SLEW_RESET.name: SLEW_RESET
SLEW_RESET.multiplayer: Stop slew and reset pitch, bank, and heading all to zero.

SPOILERS_ARM_TOGGLE.name: SPOILERS_ARM_TOGGLE
SPOILERS_ARM_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggles arming of auto-spoilers between armed (1) and unarmed (0).

SPOILERS_DEC.name: SPOILERS_DEC
SPOILERS_DEC.multiplayer: Decremement the spoilers by  (down to a minimum of 0).

SPOILERS_INC.name: SPOILERS_INC
SPOILERS_INC.multiplayer: Increment the spoilers by  (down to a minimum of 0).

SPOILERS_OFF.name: SPOILERS_OFF
SPOILERS_OFF.multiplayer: Sets spoiler handle to full retract position.

SPOILERS_ON.name: SPOILERS_ON
