ATTITUDE_BARS_POSITION_DOWN.name: ATTITUDE_BARS_POSITION_DOWN
ATTITUDE_BARS_POSITION_DOWN.multiplayer: Decrements the attitude indicator pitch reference bars. If you hold down the key for more than 2 seconds it will decrement by 30, if you hold down the key for more than 1 second it will decrement by 10, otherwise it will decrement by 5.

ATTITUDE_BARS_POSITION_UP.name: ATTITUDE_BARS_POSITION_UP
ATTITUDE_BARS_POSITION_UP.multiplayer: Increments the attitude indicator pitch reference bars. If you hold down the key for more than 2 seconds it will increment by 30, if you hold down the key for more than 1 second it will increment by 10, otherwise it will increment by 5.

ATTITUDE_BARS_POSITION_SET.name: ATTITUDE_BARS_POSITION_SET
ATTITUDE_BARS_POSITION_SET.multiplayer: Sets attitude indicator pitch reference bars. Input value can be between -100 and 100.

BAROMETRIC.name: BAROMETRIC
BAROMETRIC.multiplayer: Syncs altimeter setting to sea level pressure, or 29.92 if above 18000 feet.

BAROMETRIC_STD_PRESSURE.name: BAROMETRIC_STD_PRESSURE
BAROMETRIC_STD_PRESSURE.multiplayer: Set the altimeter setting to the pressure at the standard atmospheric level (1013.25 hPa).

GAUGE_KEYSTROKE.name: GAUGE_KEYSTROKE
GAUGE_KEYSTROKE.multiplayer: Enables a keystroke to be sent to a gauge that is in focus. The keystrokes can only be in the range 0 to 9, A to Z, and the four keys: plus, minus, comma and period. This is typically used to allow some keyboard entry to a complex device such as a GPS to enter such things as ICAO codes using the keyboard, rather than turning dials.

HEADING_GYRO_SET.name: HEADING_GYRO_SET
HEADING_GYRO_SET.multiplayer: Sets heading indicator to 0 drift error.

RESET_G_FORCE_INDICATOR.name: RESET_G_FORCE_INDICATOR
RESET_G_FORCE_INDICATOR.multiplayer: Resets max/min indicated G force to 1.0.

RESET_MAX_RPM_INDICATOR.name: RESET_MAX_RPM_INDICATOR
RESET_MAX_RPM_INDICATOR.multiplayer: Reset max indicated engine rpm to 0.

ATTITUDE_CAGE_BUTTON.name: ATTITUDE_CAGE_BUTTON
ATTITUDE_CAGE_BUTTON.multiplayer: Cages attitude indicator at 0 pitch and bank.

TOGGLE_ICS.name: TOGGLE_ICS
TOGGLE_ICS.multiplayer: Toggle the InterCom system on the audio panel.

TOGGLE_TURN_INDICATOR_SWITCH.name: TOGGLE_TURN_INDICATOR_SWITCH
TOGGLE_TURN_INDICATOR_SWITCH.multiplayer: Turn the turn indicator on or off.

TOGGLE_VARIOMETER_SWITCH.name: TOGGLE_VARIOMETER_SWITCH
TOGGLE_VARIOMETER_SWITCH.multiplayer: Turn the variometer on or off.

TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_DEC.name: TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_DEC
TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements airspeed indicators true airspeed reference card.

TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_INC.name: TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_INC
TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_INC.multiplayer: Increments airspeed indicators true airspeed reference card.

TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_SET.name: TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_SET
TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_SET.multiplayer: Sets airspeed indicators true airspeed reference card (degrees, where 0 is standard sea level conditions).

VARIOMETER_SOUND_TOGGLE.name: VARIOMETER_SOUND_TOGGLE
VARIOMETER_SOUND_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggle the variometer sounds between on (1) and off (0).

ATC_MENU_0.name: ATC_MENU_0
ATC_MENU_0.description:
N/A  ATC_MENU_1
          ATC_MENU_2
          ATC_MENU_3
          ATC_MENU_4
          ATC_MENU_5
          ATC_MENU_6
          ATC_MENU_7
          ATC_MENU_8
          ATC_MENU_9

EGT.name: EGT
EGT.multiplayer: Selects EGT bug for +/-. Follow by SELECT_1, SELECT_2, SELECT_3, or SELECT_4 to target the appropriate bug.

EGT_SET.name: EGT_SET
EGT_SET.multiplayer: Sets all EGT bugs to the given value. Input will be normalised between 0 and 1.

EGT1_DEC.name: EGT1_DEC
EGT1_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the specific  EGT 1/2/3/4 bug value.

EGT1_INC.name: EGT1_INC
EGT1_INC.multiplayer: Increments the specific  EGT 1/2/3/4 bug value.

EGT1_SET.name: EGT1_SET
EGT1_SET.description:
[0]: Bug value (0 to 32768)  EGT2_SET
          EGT3_SET
          EGT4_SET
EGT1_SET.multiplayer: Sets the specific  EGT 1/2/3/4 bug value.

LOW_HEIGHT_WARNING_GAUGE_WILL_SET.name: LOW_HEIGHT_WARNING_GAUGE_WILL_SET
LOW_HEIGHT_WARNING_GAUGE_WILL_SET.multiplayer: Not currently used in the simulation.

LOW_HEIGHT_WARNING_SET.name: LOW_HEIGHT_WARNING_SET
LOW_HEIGHT_WARNING_SET.multiplayer: Not currently used in the simulation.

ANTISKID_BRAKES_TOGGLE.name: ANTISKID_BRAKES_TOGGLE
ANTISKID_BRAKES_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turn the anti-skid braking system on or off.

AXIS_IND_SET.name: AXIS_IND_SET
AXIS_IND_SET.multiplayer: Not currently used in the simulation.

AXIS_LEFT_BRAKE_LINEAR_SET.name: AXIS_LEFT_BRAKE_LINEAR_SET
AXIS_LEFT_BRAKE_LINEAR_SET.multiplayer:
Sets the left brake position from an axis controller (e.g. joystick) to the value given as the parameter [0], from -16383 (0 braking) to +16383 (maximum braking). Note that this is on a linear scale:
          
            -16383 = 0%
            0 = 50%
            +16383 = 100%
          
          Not currently used in the simulation.

AXIS_LEFT_BRAKE_SET.name: AXIS_LEFT_BRAKE_SET
AXIS_LEFT_BRAKE_SET.multiplayer:
Sets the left brake position from an axis controller (e.g. joystick) to the value given as the parameter [0], from -16383 (0 braking) to +16383 (maximum braking). Note that this is on a non-linear scale:
          
            -16383 = 0%
            -8191 = 8%
            0 = 27%
            +8191 = 53%
            +16383 = 100%

AXIS_RIGHT_BRAKE_LINEAR_SET.name: AXIS_RIGHT_BRAKE_LINEAR_SET
AXIS_RIGHT_BRAKE_LINEAR_SET.multiplayer:
Sets the right brake position from an axis controller (e.g. joystick) to the value given as the parameter [0], from -16383 (0 braking) to +16383 (maximum braking). Note that this is on a linear scale:
          
            -16383 = 0%
            0 = 50%
            +16383 = 100%
          
          Not currently used in the simulation.

AXIS_RIGHT_BRAKE_SET.name: AXIS_RIGHT_BRAKE_SET
AXIS_RIGHT_BRAKE_SET.multiplayer:
Sets the right brake position from an axis controller (e.g. joystick) to the value given as the parameter [0], from -16383 (0 braking) to +16383 (maximum braking). Note that this is on a non-linear scale:
          
            -16383 = 0%
            -8191 = 8%
            0 = 27%
            +8191 = 53%
            +16383 = 100%

GEAR_DOWN.name: GEAR_DOWN
GEAR_DOWN.multiplayer: Sets gear handle in DOWN position

GEAR_UP.name: GEAR_UP
GEAR_UP.multiplayer: Sets gear handle in UP position

RETRACT_FLOAT_SWITCH_DEC.name: RETRACT_FLOAT_SWITCH_DEC
RETRACT_FLOAT_SWITCH_DEC.multiplayer: If the plane has retractable floats, moves the retract position from Extend to Neutral, or Neutral to Retract.

RETRACT_FLOAT_SWITCH_INC.name: RETRACT_FLOAT_SWITCH_INC
RETRACT_FLOAT_SWITCH_INC.multiplayer: If the plane has retractable floats, moves the retract position from Retract to Neutral, or Neutral to Extend.

MAC_CREADY_SETTING_DEC.name: MAC_CREADY_SETTING_DEC
MAC_CREADY_SETTING_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the MacCready setting. Default decrement value is 0.1m/s, however holding down the key for more than 1 second will increase the amount to 0.5m/s, and holding it down for more than 2 seconds will further increase this to 1m/s. Note that the resulting value is clamped between 0 and 5 m/s.

MAC_CREADY_SETTING_INC.name: MAC_CREADY_SETTING_INC
MAC_CREADY_SETTING_INC.multiplayer: Increments the MacCready setting. Default increment value is 0.1m/s, however holding down the key for more than 1 second will increase the amount to 0.5m/s, and holding it down for more than 2 seconds will further increase this to 1m/s. Note that the resulting value is clamped between 0 and 5 m/s.

MAC_CREADY_SETTING_SET.name: MAC_CREADY_SETTING_SET
MAC_CREADY_SETTING_SET.multiplayer: Set the MacCready setting to a value between 0 and 5 m/s.

SET_TAIL_HOOK_HANDLE.name: SET_TAIL_HOOK_HANDLE
SET_TAIL_HOOK_HANDLE.description: [0]: TRUE/FALSE to set or retract the tailhook.
SET_TAIL_HOOK_HANDLE.multiplayer:
Sets the tail hook handle. Takes one of the following values:
          
            1 - set tail hook
            0 - retract tail hook

TOW_PLANE_RELEASE.name: TOW_PLANE_RELEASE
TOW_PLANE_RELEASE.multiplayer: Release a towed aircraft, usually a glider.

TOW_PLANE_REQUEST.name: TOW_PLANE_REQUEST
TOW_PLANE_REQUEST.multiplayer: Request a tow plane. The user aircraft must be tow-able, stationary, on the ground and not already attached for this to succeed.

ANNUNCIATOR_SWITCH_TOGGLE.name: ANNUNCIATOR_SWITCH_TOGGLE
ANNUNCIATOR_SWITCH_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggles the annunciator switch off (0) and on (1).

BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_INC.name: BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_INC
BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_INC.multiplayer: Increases the bleed air source control. Order of operation is Auto -> Off -> APU -> Engines.

BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_DEC.name: BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_DEC
BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_DEC.multiplayer: Decreases the bleed air source control. Order of operation is Engines -> APU -> Off -> Auto.

BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_SET.name: BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_SET
BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_SET.multiplayer:
Sets the bleed air system source. The input parameter [0] can be one of the following:
          
            0 - auto
            1 - off
            2 - apu
            3 - engines

CABIN_NO_SMOKING_ALERT_SWITCH_TOGGLE.name: CABIN_NO_SMOKING_ALERT_SWITCH_TOGGLE
CABIN_NO_SMOKING_ALERT_SWITCH_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turn the "No smoking" alert on or off.

CABIN_SEATBELTS_ALERT_SWITCH_TOGGLE.name: CABIN_SEATBELTS_ALERT_SWITCH_TOGGLE
CABIN_SEATBELTS_ALERT_SWITCH_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turn the "Fasten seatbelts" alert on or off.

DECREASE_DECISION_HEIGHT.name: DECREASE_DECISION_HEIGHT
DECREASE_DECISION_HEIGHT.multiplayer: Decrements the AGL decision height reference by 1m.

INCREASE_DECISION_HEIGHT.name: INCREASE_DECISION_HEIGHT
INCREASE_DECISION_HEIGHT.multiplayer: Increments the AGL decision height reference by 1m.

DECISION_HEIGHT_SET.name: DECISION_HEIGHT_SET
DECISION_HEIGHT_SET.multiplayer: Set the AGL decision height reference, in meters.

DECREASE_DECISION_ALTITUDE_MSL.name: DECREASE_DECISION_ALTITUDE_MSL
DECREASE_DECISION_ALTITUDE_MSL.multiplayer: Decrements the MSL decision height reference by the amount given, or by 10m if no amount is given.

INCREASE_DECISION_ALTITUDE_MSL.name: INCREASE_DECISION_ALTITUDE_MSL
INCREASE_DECISION_ALTITUDE_MSL.multiplayer: Increments the MSL decision height reference by the amount given, or by 10m if no amount is given.

SET_DECISION_ALTITUDE_MSL.name: SET_DECISION_ALTITUDE_MSL
SET_DECISION_ALTITUDE_MSL.multiplayer: Set the MSL decision height reference, in meters.

EXTINGUISH_ENGINE_FIRE.name: EXTINGUISH_ENGINE_FIRE
EXTINGUISH_ENGINE_FIRE.multiplayer: This key event requires a two digit number for parameter [0]. The first digit represents the fire extinguisher index to use, and the second represents the engine index. For example, a value of 11 would represent using bottle 1 on engine 1. 21 would represent using bottle 2 on engine 1. Typical entries for a twin engine aircraft would be 11 and 22.

HYDRAULIC_SWITCH_TOGGLE.name: HYDRAULIC_SWITCH_TOGGLE
HYDRAULIC_SWITCH_TOGGLE.description: [0]: TRUE/FALSE to set or the hydraulic switch on/off
HYDRAULIC_SWITCH_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turn the hydraulic switch on or off.

PITOT_HEAT_OFF.name: PITOT_HEAT_OFF
PITOT_HEAT_OFF.multiplayer: Turns the pitot heat switch off.

PITOT_HEAT_ON.name: PITOT_HEAT_ON
PITOT_HEAT_ON.multiplayer: Turns the pitot heat switch on.

PITOT_HEAT_SET.name: PITOT_HEAT_SET
PITOT_HEAT_SET.description:
[0]: TRUE/FALSE to set or the pitot heat switch on/off
          [1]: Pitot index
PITOT_HEAT_SET.multiplayer: Sets the pitot heat switch on/off.

RELEASE_DROPPABLE_OBJECTS.name: RELEASE_DROPPABLE_OBJECTS
RELEASE_DROPPABLE_OBJECTS.multiplayer: Release one dropable object. Multiple key events will release multiple objects.

SET_WING_FOLD.name: SET_WING_FOLD
SET_WING_FOLD.description: [0]: TRUE/FALSE to fold or unfold wings.
SET_WING_FOLD.multiplayer:
Sets the wings into the folded position suitable for storage, typically on a carrier. Takes one of the following values:
          
            1 -fold wings
            0 - unfold wings

SMOKE_SET.name: SMOKE_SET
SMOKE_SET.description: [0]: TRUE/FALSE to enable/disable the smoke system

TOGGLE_AIRCRAFT_EXIT.name: TOGGLE_AIRCRAFT_EXIT
TOGGLE_AIRCRAFT_EXIT.multiplayer: Toggles primary door open/close. Usually followed by (for example) KEY_SELECT_2, etc... for subsequent doors.

TOGGLE_WATER_BALLAST_VALVE.name: TOGGLE_WATER_BALLAST_VALVE
TOGGLE_WATER_BALLAST_VALVE.description: [0]: valve index from 1 to n where n is the NumberOfReleaseValves defined in the systems.cfg file.
TOGGLE_WATER_BALLAST_VALVE.multiplayer: Turn the indexed water ballast valve on or off.

TUG_HEADING.name: TUG_HEADING
TUG_HEADING.multiplayer: Triggers the tug and sets the desired heading. The units are a 32 bit integer (0 to 4294967295) which represent 0 to 360 degrees. To set a 45 degree angle, for example, set the value to 4294967295 / 8.

TUG_SPEED.name: TUG_SPEED
TUG_SPEED.multiplayer: Triggers tug, and sets desired speed, in feet per second. The speed can be either positive (forward movement) or negative (backward movement).

BACK_TO_FLY.name: BACK_TO_FLY
BACK_TO_FLY.multiplayer: This will raise the aircraft off the ground and into flight, or - if already in flight - it will force the aircraft to gain height.

PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_ALT_INC.name: PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_ALT_INC
PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_ALT_INC.multiplayer: Increases the altitude that the cabin is pressurized to by approximately 50ft.

PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_ALT_DEC.name: PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_ALT_DEC
PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_ALT_DEC.multiplayer: Decreases the altitude that the cabin is pressurized to by approximately 50ft.

PRESSURIZATION_CLIMB_RATE_INC.name: PRESSURIZATION_CLIMB_RATE_INC
PRESSURIZATION_CLIMB_RATE_INC.multiplayer: Increment the cabin pressurization by approximately 50ft/min step, based on the initialisation value of 500ft/min.

PRESSURIZATION_CLIMB_RATE_DEC.name: PRESSURIZATION_CLIMB_RATE_DEC
PRESSURIZATION_CLIMB_RATE_DEC.multiplayer: Decrement the cabin pressurization by approximately 50ft/min steps based on the initialisation value of 500ft/min.

PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_DUMP_SWITCH.name: PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_DUMP_SWITCH
PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_DUMP_SWITCH.multiplayer: Toggles the pressure dump switch between on (sets the cabin pressure to the outside air pressure) and off.

AXIS_STEERING_SET.name: AXIS_STEERING_SET
AXIS_STEERING_SET.multiplayer: Sets the value of the nose wheel steering position. Zero is straight ahead (-16384, far left +16384, far right).

NOSE_WHEEL_STEERING_LIMIT_SET.name: NOSE_WHEEL_STEERING_LIMIT_SET
NOSE_WHEEL_STEERING_LIMIT_SET.multiplayer: Set the steering angle limit for the nose wheel. -180° maps to -16383 and 180° maps to 16383.

STEERING_INC.name: STEERING_INC
STEERING_INC.multiplayer: Increments the nose wheel steering position by 5 percent.

STEERING_DEC.name: STEERING_DEC
STEERING_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the nose wheel steering position by 5 percent.

STEERING_SET.name: STEERING_SET
STEERING_SET.multiplayer: Sets the value of the nose wheel steering position. Zero is straight ahead (-16383, far left +16383, far right).

WINDSHIELD_DEICE_OFF.name: WINDSHIELD_DEICE_OFF
WINDSHIELD_DEICE_OFF.multiplayer: Switches on the windshield deicing system.

WINDSHIELD_DEICE_ON.name: WINDSHIELD_DEICE_ON
WINDSHIELD_DEICE_ON.multiplayer: Switches off the windshield deicing system.

WINDSHIELD_DEICE_SET.name: WINDSHIELD_DEICE_SET
WINDSHIELD_DEICE_SET.multiplayer: Sets the windshield deicing system on or off based on the input parameter [0].

WINDSHIELD_DEICE_TOGGLE.name: WINDSHIELD_DEICE_TOGGLE
WINDSHIELD_DEICE_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggles the windshield deicing system on and off.

TAKEOFF_ASSIST_ARM_TOGGLE.name: TAKEOFF_ASSIST_ARM_TOGGLE
TAKEOFF_ASSIST_ARM_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Deploy or remove the launch assist arm.

TAKEOFF_ASSIST_ARM_SET.name: TAKEOFF_ASSIST_ARM_SET
TAKEOFF_ASSIST_ARM_SET.multiplayer: Used to set or unset the launch assist arm.

TAKEOFF_ASSIST_FIRE.name: TAKEOFF_ASSIST_FIRE
TAKEOFF_ASSIST_FIRE.multiplayer: If everything is set up correctly. Launch from the catapult.

TOGGLE_LAUNCH_BAR_SWITCH.name: TOGGLE_LAUNCH_BAR_SWITCH
TOGGLE_LAUNCH_BAR_SWITCH.multiplayer: Toggle the request for the launch bar to be installed or removed.

SET_LAUNCH_BAR_SWITCH.name: SET_LAUNCH_BAR_SWITCH
SET_LAUNCH_BAR_SWITCH.multiplayer: Set the switch of the launch bar extension system to be on or off.

SLING_PICKUP_RELEASE.name: SLING_PICKUP_RELEASE
SLING_PICKUP_RELEASE.multiplayer: Toggle between pickup and release mode. Hold mode is automatic and cannot be selected.

HOIST_SWITCH_EXTEND.name: HOIST_SWITCH_EXTEND
HOIST_SWITCH_EXTEND.multiplayer: The rate at which a hoist cable extends (set in the Aircraft Configuration File)

HOIST_SWITCH_RETRACT.name: HOIST_SWITCH_RETRACT
HOIST_SWITCH_RETRACT.multiplayer: The rate at which a hoist cable retracts (set in the Aircraft Configuration File).

HOIST_SWITCH_SET.name: HOIST_SWITCH_SET
HOIST_SWITCH_SET.multiplayer:
The hoist control switch setting. Should be set to one of the following values:
          
            <0 up
            0 off
            >0 down

HOIST_DEPLOY_TOGGLE.name: HOIST_DEPLOY_TOGGLE
HOIST_DEPLOY_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggles the hoist arm switch, extend or retract.

HOIST_DEPLOY_SET.name: HOIST_DEPLOY_SET
HOIST_DEPLOY_SET.multiplayer:
The hoist deployment setting. The value should be set to one of the following:
          
            0 - set hoist switch to retract the arm
            1 - set hoist switch to extend the arm

ADF.name: ADF
ADF.multiplayer: Sequentially selects the ADF tuner digits for use with +/-. Follow by SELECT_1 for ADF 1, or SELECT_2 for ADF 2.

ADF_CARD_DEC.name: ADF_CARD_DEC
ADF_CARD_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the ADF card by 10° if the key is pressed more than 2 seconds, 4° if the key is pressed more than 1 second, or by 1° otherwise. The resulting value is clamped between 0° and 360°.

ADF_CARD_INC.name: ADF_CARD_INC
ADF_CARD_INC.multiplayer: Increments the ADF card by 10° if the key is pressed more than 2 seconds, 4° if the key is pressed more than 1 second, or by 1° otherwise. The resulting value is clamped between 0° and 360°.

ADF_CARD_SET.name: ADF_CARD_SET
ADF_CARD_SET.multiplayer: Sets the ADF card. The resulting value is clamped between 0° and 360°.

ADF_1_DEC.name: ADF_1_DEC
ADF_1_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the ADF 1 / 2 frequency by 1 KHz, with wrapping.

ADF_10_DEC.name: ADF_10_DEC
ADF_10_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the ADF 1 / 2 frequency by 10 KHz, with wrapping.

ADF_100_DEC.name: ADF_100_DEC
ADF_100_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the ADF 1 / 2 frequency by 100 KHz, with wrapping.

ADF_1_INC.name: ADF_1_INC
ADF_1_INC.multiplayer: Increments the ADF 1 / 2 frequency by 1 KHz, with wrapping.

ADF_10_INC.name: ADF_10_INC
ADF_10_INC.multiplayer: Increments the ADF 1 / 2 frequency by 10 KHz, with wrapping.

ADF_100_INC.name: ADF_100_INC
ADF_100_INC.multiplayer: Increments the ADF 1 / 2 frequency by 100 KHz, with wrapping.

ADF_ACTIVE_SET.name: ADF_ACTIVE_SET
ADF_ACTIVE_SET.multiplayer: Sets the ADF 1 / 2 active frequency (BCD32 encoded Hz).

ADF_COMPLETE_SET.name: ADF_COMPLETE_SET
ADF_COMPLETE_SET.multiplayer: Sets the ADF 1 / 2 frequency (BCD32 encoded Hz).

ADF_EXTENDED_SET.name: ADF_EXTENDED_SET
ADF_EXTENDED_SET.multiplayer: Sets the ADF 1 / 2 frequency (thousands and tenths, BCD32 encoded HZ).

ADF_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.name: ADF_FRACT_DEC_CARRY
ADF_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.multiplayer: Decrements the ADF 1 / 2 frequency by 0.1 KHz, with carry.

ADF_FRACT_INC_CARRY.name: ADF_FRACT_INC_CARRY
ADF_FRACT_INC_CARRY.multiplayer: Increments the ADF 1 / 2 frequency by 0.1 KHz, with carry.

ADF_HIGHRANGE_SET.name: ADF_HIGHRANGE_SET
ADF_HIGHRANGE_SET.multiplayer: Sets the ADF 1 / 2 highrange frequency (BCD32 encoded Hz).

ADF_LOWRANGE_SET.name: ADF_LOWRANGE_SET
ADF_LOWRANGE_SET.multiplayer: Sets the ADF 1 / 2 lowrange frequency (BCD32 encoded Hz).

ADF_NEEDLE_SET.name: ADF_NEEDLE_SET
ADF_NEEDLE_SET.multiplayer:
Sets the ADF 1 / 2 needle value, in radians.
          Note that ADF_OUTSIDE_SOURCE / ADF2_OUTSIDE_SOURCE must be enabled.

ADF_OUTSIDE_SOURCE.name: ADF_OUTSIDE_SOURCE
ADF_OUTSIDE_SOURCE.multiplayer: When TRUE sets ADF 1 / 2 source to be outside, when FALSE it's not. This enables you to use the ADF_NEEDLE_SET / ADF2_NEEDLE_SET events to set the ADF needle instead of relying on the simulation source.

ADF1_RADIO_SWAP.name: ADF1_RADIO_SWAP
ADF1_RADIO_SWAP.multiplayer: Swaps between the ADF 1 / 2 frequency and the standby frequency.

ADF1_RADIO_TENTHS_DEC.name: ADF1_RADIO_TENTHS_DEC
ADF1_RADIO_TENTHS_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the ADF 1 / 2 frequency by 0.1 KHz.

ADF1_RADIO_TENTHS_INC.name: ADF1_RADIO_TENTHS_INC
ADF1_RADIO_TENTHS_INC.multiplayer: Increments the ADF 1 / 2 frequency by 0.1 KHz.

ADF_STBY_SET.name: ADF_STBY_SET
ADF_STBY_SET.multiplayer: Sets ADF 1 / 2 standby frequency (BCD32 encoded Hz).

ADF_VOLUME_INC.name: ADF_VOLUME_INC
ADF_VOLUME_INC.multiplayer: Increase ADF 1 / 2 volume by 0.02. The resulting value will be clamped between 0 and 1.

ADF_VOLUME_DEC.name: ADF_VOLUME_DEC
ADF_VOLUME_DEC.multiplayer: Decrease ADF 1 / 2 volume by 0.02. The resulting value will be clamped between 0 and 1.

ADF1_WHOLE_DEC.name: ADF1_WHOLE_DEC
ADF1_WHOLE_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the ADF 1 / 2 frequency by 1 KHz, with carry as digits wrap.

ADF1_WHOLE_INC.name: ADF1_WHOLE_INC
ADF1_WHOLE_INC.multiplayer: Increments the ADF 1 / 2 frequency by 1 KHz, with carry as digits wrap.

RADIO_ADF_IDENT_SET.name: RADIO_ADF_IDENT_SET
RADIO_ADF_IDENT_SET.multiplayer: Sets the ADF 1 / 2 ID on (1) or off (2).

RADIO_ADF_IDENT_TOGGLE.name: RADIO_ADF_IDENT_TOGGLE
RADIO_ADF_IDENT_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggles the ADF 1 / 2 ID between on (1) and off (0).

AVIONICS_MASTER_SET.name: AVIONICS_MASTER_SET
AVIONICS_MASTER_SET.multiplayer: Sets the avionics master switch to on or off.

AVIONICS_MASTER_1_ON.name: AVIONICS_MASTER_1_ON
AVIONICS_MASTER_1_ON.multiplayer: Sets avionics master 1 / 2 switch to on (1).

AVIONICS_MASTER_1_OFF.name: AVIONICS_MASTER_1_OFF
AVIONICS_MASTER_1_OFF.multiplayer: Sets avionics master 1 / 2 switch to off (0).

AVIONICS_MASTER_1_SET.name: AVIONICS_MASTER_1_SET
AVIONICS_MASTER_1_SET.multiplayer: Sets avionics master 1 / 2 switch to on (1) or off (0).

COM_RADIO.name: COM_RADIO
COM_RADIO.multiplayer: Sequentially selects the COM tuner digits for use with +/-. Follow by SELECT_2 for COM 2 or SELECT_3 for COM 3.

COM_RADIO_FRACT_DEC.name: COM_RADIO_FRACT_DEC
COM_RADIO_FRACT_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements COM 1/2/3 frequency by 25 KHz, with no carry when digit wraps

COM_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.name: COM_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY
COM_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.multiplayer: Decrement COM 1/2/3 frequency by 25 KHz, and carry when digit wraps

COM_RADIO_FRACT_INC.name: COM_RADIO_FRACT_INC
COM_RADIO_FRACT_INC.multiplayer: Increment COM 1/2/3 frequency by 25 KHz, with no carry when digit wraps

COM_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY.name: COM_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY
COM_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY.multiplayer: Increment COM 1/2/3 frequency by 25 KHz, and carry when digit wraps

COM_RADIO_SET.name: COM_RADIO_SET
COM_RADIO_SET.description:
[0]: Frequency value (BCD16 encoded Hz)  COM2_RADIO_SET
          COM3_RADIO_SET
COM_RADIO_SET.multiplayer: Sets COM 1/2/3 frequency as a BCD16 encoded value.

COM_STBY_RADIO_SET.name: COM_STBY_RADIO_SET
COM_STBY_RADIO_SET.description:
[0]: Frequency value (BCD16 encoded Hz)  COM2_STBY_RADIO_SET
          COM3_STBY_RADIO_SET
COM_STBY_RADIO_SET.multiplayer: Sets COM 1/2/3 standby frequency as a BCD16 encoded value.

COM_STBY_RADIO_SET_HZ.name: COM_STBY_RADIO_SET_HZ
COM_STBY_RADIO_SET_HZ.multiplayer: Sets COM 1/2/3 standby frequency in Hz.

COM_RADIO_WHOLE_DEC.name: COM_RADIO_WHOLE_DEC
COM_RADIO_WHOLE_DEC.multiplayer: Decrement COM 1/2/3 frequency by 1 MHz. Values from 118 to 137, and this will wrap if the values go over 137.

COM_RADIO_WHOLE_INC.name: COM_RADIO_WHOLE_INC
COM_RADIO_WHOLE_INC.multiplayer: Increment COM 1/2/3 frequency by 1 MHz. Values are from 118 to 137, and this will wrap if the values go under 118.

COM_RADIO_SWAP.name: COM_RADIO_SWAP
COM_RADIO_SWAP.multiplayer:
Swaps COM 1/2/3 frequency with the standby frequency.
          NOTE: COM_RADIO_SWAP is simply an alias for COM1_RADIO_SWAP

COM1_RECEIVE_SELECT.name: COM1_RECEIVE_SELECT
COM1_RECEIVE_SELECT.multiplayer: Sets receive on (1) or off (0) for COM 1/2/3.

COM_1_SPACING_MODE_SWITCH.name: COM_1_SPACING_MODE_SWITCH
COM_1_SPACING_MODE_SWITCH.multiplayer: Toggle between the different modes for COM 1/2/3.

COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET.name: COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET
COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET.description:
[0]: Frequency value (BCD16 or BCD32 encoded Hz)  COM2_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET
          COM3_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET
COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET.multiplayer: Sets the COM 1/2/3 stored frequency as a BCD encoded value.

COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET_HZ.name: COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET_HZ
COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET_HZ.multiplayer: Sets COM 1/2/3 stored frequency as Hz.

COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_INDEX_SET.name: COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_INDEX_SET
COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_INDEX_SET.multiplayer:
This is used to select the index for when you want to store frequencies. This can be done by including this event when you store a frequency using one of the 2 available types: COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET, COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET_HZ.
          For example if you want to store a Com1 frequency HZ to an index of 2 then you would do this:
          2 (>K:COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_INDEX_SET) 112 (>K:COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET_HZ)
          After you save it you can retrieve this value from the 3 types of variables as seen here:
          (A:COM1 STORED FREQUENCY:2, Hz)
            (A:COM1 STORED FREQUENCY:2, FrequencyBCD16)
            (A:COM1 STORED FREQUENCY:2, FrequencyBCD32)

COM1_TRANSMIT_SELECT.name: COM1_TRANSMIT_SELECT
COM1_TRANSMIT_SELECT.multiplayer:
Selects COM 1/2 to transmit
           See PILOT_TRANSMITTER_SET instead.

COM1_VOLUME_INC.name: COM1_VOLUME_INC
COM1_VOLUME_INC.multiplayer: Increases the COM 1/2/3 volume by 0.02, and the resulting value will be clamped between 0 and 1.

COM1_VOLUME_DEC.name: COM1_VOLUME_DEC
COM1_VOLUME_DEC.multiplayer: Decreases the COM 1/2/3 volume by 0.02, and the resulting value will be clamped between 0 and 1.

COM_RECEIVE_ALL_SET.name: COM_RECEIVE_ALL_SET
COM_RECEIVE_ALL_SET.multiplayer: Sets whether to receive on all COM radios (1, 0)

COM_RECEIVE_ALL_TOGGLE.name: COM_RECEIVE_ALL_TOGGLE
COM_RECEIVE_ALL_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggles receive on (1) or off (0) for all COM radios.

RADIO_COMMNAV1_TEST_TOGGLE.name: RADIO_COMMNAV1_TEST_TOGGLE
RADIO_COMMNAV1_TEST_TOGGLE.multiplayer:
Places COM 1/2/3 in "test mode".
          NOTE: Currently, placing COMs in test mode will have no effect other than to set the SimVar COM TEST.

RADIO_COMM1_AUTOSWITCH_TOGGLE.name: RADIO_COMM1_AUTOSWITCH_TOGGLE
RADIO_COMM1_AUTOSWITCH_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggles the COM 1/2 autoswitch on (1) or off (0).

DME.name: DME
DME.multiplayer: Selects the DME for use with +/-

DME_SELECT.name: DME_SELECT
DME_SELECT.multiplayer: Selects one of the two DME systems (1, 2).

TOGGLE_DME.name: TOGGLE_DME
TOGGLE_DME.multiplayer: Toggles DME between NAV 1 and NAV 2.

DME1_TOGGLE.name: DME1_TOGGLE
DME1_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Sets the DME 1 / 2 display to NAV 1 / 2.

RADIO_DME1_IDENT_SET.name: RADIO_DME1_IDENT_SET
RADIO_DME1_IDENT_SET.multiplayer: Sets the DME 1 /2 ID to on (1) or off (0).

RADIO_DME1_IDENT_TOGGLE.name: RADIO_DME1_IDENT_TOGGLE
RADIO_DME1_IDENT_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggles the DME 1 / 2 ID between on (1) and off (0).

RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_ENABLE.name: RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_ENABLE
RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_ENABLE.multiplayer: Turns on the identification sound for the selected DME.

RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_DISABLE.name: RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_DISABLE
RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_DISABLE.multiplayer: Turns off the identification sound for the selected DME.

RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_SET.name: RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_SET
RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_SET.multiplayer: Sets the DME identification sound to the given filename.

RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_TOGGLE.name: RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_TOGGLE
RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turns on or off the identification sound for the selected DME.

ELT_SET.name: ELT_SET
ELT_SET.multiplayer: Sets the ELT on (1) or off (0).

ELT_TOGGLE.name: ELT_TOGGLE
ELT_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggles the ELT between on (1) and off (0).

GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON.name: GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON
GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON.multiplayer: Clears entered data on a page

GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON_DOWN.name: GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON_DOWN
GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON_DOWN.multiplayer: Triggers the pressing of the Clear button

GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON_UP.name: GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON_UP
GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON_UP.multiplayer: Triggers the release of the Clear button.

GPS_MENU_BUTTON.name: GPS_MENU_BUTTON
GPS_MENU_BUTTON.multiplayer: Brings up page to select active legs in a flightplan.

GPS_MSG_BUTTON_DOWN.name: GPS_MSG_BUTTON_DOWN
GPS_MSG_BUTTON_DOWN.multiplayer: Triggers the pressing of the message button.

GPS_MSG_BUTTON_UP.name: GPS_MSG_BUTTON_UP
GPS_MSG_BUTTON_UP.multiplayer: Triggers the release of the message button.

GPS_OBS.name: GPS_OBS
GPS_OBS.multiplayer: Toggle GPS OBS mode active status on/off.

GPS_OBS_DEC.name: GPS_OBS_DEC
GPS_OBS_DEC.multiplayer: Decreases GPS OBS value by 1 degree (if the value goes below 1 it will wrap to 360).

GPS_OBS_INC.name: GPS_OBS_INC
GPS_OBS_INC.multiplayer: Increases GPS OBS value by 1 degree (if the value goes above 360 it will wrap to 1).

GPS_OBS_OFF.name: GPS_OBS_OFF
GPS_OBS_OFF.multiplayer: Turn the GPS OBS mode to be inactive.

GPS_OBS_ON.name: GPS_OBS_ON
GPS_OBS_ON.multiplayer: Turn on the GPS OBS mode to be active

GPS_OBS_SET.name: GPS_OBS_SET
GPS_OBS_SET.multiplayer: Set the GPS OBS value to a new value, in degrees.

GPS_TERRAIN_BUTTON.name: GPS_TERRAIN_BUTTON
GPS_TERRAIN_BUTTON.multiplayer: Displays terrain information on default display

TOGGLE_GPS_DRIVES_NAV1.name: TOGGLE_GPS_DRIVES_NAV1
TOGGLE_GPS_DRIVES_NAV1.multiplayer: Toggles between GPS and NAV 1 driving NAV 1 OBS display (and AP)

FREQUENCY_SWAP.name: FREQUENCY_SWAP
FREQUENCY_SWAP.multiplayer: Swaps frequency with standby on whichever NAV or COM radio is selected.

MARKER_SOUND_SET.name: MARKER_SOUND_SET
MARKER_SOUND_SET.multiplayer:
Sets marker beacon sound (1, 0).
          Not currently used in the simulation.

PILOT_TRANSMITTER_SET.name: PILOT_TRANSMITTER_SET
PILOT_TRANSMITTER_SET.multiplayer:
This event can be used to select the COM channel to use. The input is one of the following values:
          
            0: Com1
            1: Com2
            2: Com3
            4: None

TOGGLE_RADAR.name: TOGGLE_RADAR
TOGGLE_RADAR.multiplayer: Not currently used in the simulation.

NAV_RADIO.name: NAV_RADIO
NAV_RADIO.multiplayer: Sequentially selects the NAV tuner digits for use with +/-. Follow by SELECT_1, SELECT_2, SELECT_3, or SELECT_4 for NAV 1, 2, 3 or 4.

NAV1_CLOSE_FREQ_SET.name: NAV1_CLOSE_FREQ_SET
NAV1_CLOSE_FREQ_SET.multiplayer:
This event is used to enable (set to 1, TRUE) or disable (set to 0, FALSE) the following SimVars:
          
            NAV_CLOSE_DME
            NAV_CLOSE_FREQUENCY
            NAV_CLOSE_IDENT
            NAV_CLOSE_LOCALIZER
            NAV_CLOSE_NAME
          
          Also note that all the NAV key events are simply aliases for each other, and using any of them will have the same effect.

NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_DEC.name: NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_DEC
NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the chosen NAV frequency by 25 KHz.

NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.name: NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY
NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.multiplayer: Decrement the chosen NAV frequency by 50 KHz, and will carry when the value wraps.

NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_INC.name: NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_INC
NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_INC.multiplayer: Increments the chosen NAV frequency by 25 KHz.

NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY.name: NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY
NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY.multiplayer: Increment the chosen NAV frequency by 50 KHz, and will carry when the value wraps.

NAV1_RADIO_SET.name: NAV1_RADIO_SET
NAV1_RADIO_SET.multiplayer: Sets the chosen NAV frequency (BCD16 encoded Hz).

NAV1_RADIO_SWAP.name: NAV1_RADIO_SWAP
NAV1_RADIO_SWAP.multiplayer: Swap between the chosen NAV frequency and the corresponding standby frequency.

NAV1_RADIO_WHOLE_DEC.name: NAV1_RADIO_WHOLE_DEC
NAV1_RADIO_WHOLE_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the chosen NAV frequency by one MHz.

NAV1_RADIO_WHOLE_INC.name: NAV1_RADIO_WHOLE_INC
NAV1_RADIO_WHOLE_INC.multiplayer: Increments the chosen NAV frequency by one MHz.

NAV1_STBY_SET.name: NAV1_STBY_SET
NAV1_STBY_SET.multiplayer: Sets the chosen NAV standby frequency (BCD16 encoded Hz).

NAV1_STBY_SET_HZ.name: NAV1_STBY_SET_HZ
NAV1_STBY_SET_HZ.multiplayer: Sets the chosen NAV standby frequency (Hz).

NAV1_VOLUME_DEC.name: NAV1_VOLUME_DEC
NAV1_VOLUME_DEC.multiplayer: Decrement the volume by 0.02, down to a minimum of 0.

NAV1_VOLUME_INC.name: NAV1_VOLUME_INC
NAV1_VOLUME_INC.multiplayer: Increment the volume by 0.02, up to a maximum of 1.

NAV1_VOLUME_SET.name: NAV1_VOLUME_SET
NAV1_VOLUME_SET.multiplayer:
Sets the volume for the chosen NAV.
          NOTE: These events are deprecated as they no longer work correctly. Instead use the _EX1 versions, listed below.

NAV1_VOLUME_SET_EX1.name: NAV1_VOLUME_SET_EX1
NAV1_VOLUME_SET_EX1.multiplayer: Sets the volume for the chosen NAV, from 0 to 100 (interpolated in the simulation to a value from 0 to 1).

TACAN1_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_SET.name: TACAN1_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_SET
TACAN1_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_SET.multiplayer: Set TACAN 1/2 active channel, from 1 to 127.

TACAN1_STANDBY_CHANNEL_SET.name: TACAN1_STANDBY_CHANNEL_SET
TACAN1_STANDBY_CHANNEL_SET.multiplayer: Set TACAN 1/2 standby channel, from 1 to 127

TACAN1_ACTIVE_MODE_SET.name: TACAN1_ACTIVE_MODE_SET
TACAN1_ACTIVE_MODE_SET.multiplayer: Set the TACAN 1/2 active mode, either 0 (X) or 1 (Y).

TACAN1_STANDBY_MODE_SET.name: TACAN1_STANDBY_MODE_SET
TACAN1_STANDBY_MODE_SET.multiplayer: Set the TACAN 1/2 standby mode, either 0 (X) or 1 (Y).

TACAN1_SWAP.name: TACAN1_SWAP
TACAN1_SWAP.multiplayer: Swap between active and standby TACAN 1/2 frequencies.

TACAN1_VOLUME_INC.name: TACAN1_VOLUME_INC
TACAN1_VOLUME_INC.multiplayer: Increase TACAN 1/2 volume by 1, up to a maximum volume of 100.

TACAN1_VOLUME_DEC.name: TACAN1_VOLUME_DEC
TACAN1_VOLUME_DEC.multiplayer: Decrease TACAN 1/2 volume by 1, down to a minimum volume of 0.

TACAN1_VOLUME_SET.name: TACAN1_VOLUME_SET
TACAN1_VOLUME_SET.multiplayer: Set TACAN 1/2 volume to a value from 0 (no volume) to 100 (full volume).

TACAN1_SET.name: TACAN1_SET
TACAN1_SET.multiplayer: Set TACAN 1/2 Omni bearing indicator. The behavior is similar to the OBS knob on a traditional VOR.

TACAN1_OBI_DEC.name: TACAN1_OBI_DEC
TACAN1_OBI_DEC.multiplayer: Decrease TACAN 1/2 OBI by 1 degree. OBI bearing is between 0° and 359°, and and will loop back to 359o if you go below 0o.

TACAN1_OBI_INC.name: TACAN1_OBI_INC
TACAN1_OBI_INC.multiplayer: Increase TACAN 1/2 OBI by 1 degree. OBI bearing is between 0° and 359°, and and will loop back to 0o if you go above 359o.

TACAN1_OBI_FAST_DEC.name: TACAN1_OBI_FAST_DEC
TACAN1_OBI_FAST_DEC.multiplayer: Decrease TACAN 1/2 OBI by 10 degrees. OBI bearing is between 0° and 359°, and and will loop back to 359o if you go below 0o.

TACAN1_OBI_FAST_INC.name: TACAN1_OBI_FAST_INC
TACAN1_OBI_FAST_INC.multiplayer: Increase TACAN 1/2 OBI by 10 degrees. OBI bearing is between 0° and 359°, and and will loop back to 0o if you go above 359o.

TOGGLE_TACAN_DRIVES_NAV1.name: TOGGLE_TACAN_DRIVES_NAV1
TOGGLE_TACAN_DRIVES_NAV1.multiplayer: Toggles the TACAN DRIVES NAV SimVar to indicate that the NAV1 autopilot feature is driven by Tacan instead of classic Nav systems (VOR/ILS).

RADIO_VOR1_IDENT_TOGGLE.name: RADIO_VOR1_IDENT_TOGGLE
RADIO_VOR1_IDENT_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggles VOR 1/2/3/4 ID between on and off.

VOR_OBS.name: VOR_OBS
VOR_OBS.multiplayer: Sequentially selects the VOR OBS for use with +/-. Follow by SELECT_1 for VOR 1 and SELECT_2 for VOR 2.

VOR1_OBI_FAST_DEC.name: VOR1_OBI_FAST_DEC
VOR1_OBI_FAST_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the VOR 1/2/3/4 OBS setting by 10 degrees. The value will stop on 0 and not arap.

VOR1_OBI_FAST_INC.name: VOR1_OBI_FAST_INC
VOR1_OBI_FAST_INC.multiplayer: Increments the VOR 1/2/3/4 OBS setting by 10 degrees. The value will stop on 360 and not arap.

XPNDR.name: XPNDR
XPNDR.multiplayer: Sequentially selects the transponder digits for use with +/-.

XPNDR_1000_DEC.name: XPNDR_1000_DEC
XPNDR_1000_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the first digit of the transponder.

XPNDR_100_DEC.name: XPNDR_100_DEC
XPNDR_100_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the second digit of the transponder.

XPNDR_10_DEC.name: XPNDR_10_DEC
XPNDR_10_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the third digit of the transponder.

XPNDR_1_DEC.name: XPNDR_1_DEC
XPNDR_1_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the fourth digit of the transponder.

XPNDR_1000_INC.name: XPNDR_1000_INC
XPNDR_1000_INC.multiplayer: Increments the first digit of the transponder.

XPNDR_100_INC.name: XPNDR_100_INC
XPNDR_100_INC.multiplayer: Increments the second digit of the transponder.

XPNDR_10_INC.name: XPNDR_10_INC
XPNDR_10_INC.multiplayer: Increments the third digit of the transponder.

XPNDR_1_INC.name: XPNDR_1_INC
XPNDR_1_INC.multiplayer: Increments the fourth digit of the transponder.

XPNDR_DEC_CARRY.name: XPNDR_DEC_CARRY
XPNDR_DEC_CARRY.multiplayer: Decrements the fourth digit of the transponder, with carry.

XPNDR_INC_CARRY.name: XPNDR_INC_CARRY
XPNDR_INC_CARRY.multiplayer: Increments the fourth digit of the transponder, with carry.

XPNDR_IDENT_OFF.name: XPNDR_IDENT_OFF
XPNDR_IDENT_OFF.multiplayer: Disable the transponder Ident (can be used along with the simvar TRANSPONDER_IDENT).

XPNDR_IDENT_ON.name: XPNDR_IDENT_ON
XPNDR_IDENT_ON.multiplayer: Enable the transponder Ident (can be used along with the simvar TRANSPONDER_IDENT). After 18 seconds it will disable automatically.

XPNDR_IDENT_SET.name: XPNDR_IDENT_SET
XPNDR_IDENT_SET.multiplayer: Set the transponder Ident on or off (can be used along with the simvar TRANSPONDER_IDENT). If set to on, it will switch off automatically after 18 seconds.

XPNDR_IDENT_TOGGLE.name: XPNDR_IDENT_TOGGLE
XPNDR_IDENT_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggle the transponder Ident from on to off or off to on (can be used along with the simvar TRANSPONDER_IDENT).

CROSS_FEED_OPEN.name: CROSS_FEED_OPEN
CROSS_FEED_OPEN.multiplayer: Opens cross feed valve (when used in conjunction with "isolate" tank)

CROSS_FEED_TOGGLE.name: CROSS_FEED_TOGGLE
CROSS_FEED_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggles crossfeed valve (when used in conjunction with "isolate" tank)

CROSS_FEED_OFF.name: CROSS_FEED_OFF
CROSS_FEED_OFF.multiplayer: Closes crossfeed valve (when used in conjunction with "isolate" tank)

CROSS_FEED_LEFT_TO_RIGHT.name: CROSS_FEED_LEFT_TO_RIGHT
CROSS_FEED_LEFT_TO_RIGHT.multiplayer: Sets the fuel crossfeed to be from left to right.

CROSS_FEED_RIGHT_TO_LEFT.name: CROSS_FEED_RIGHT_TO_LEFT
CROSS_FEED_RIGHT_TO_LEFT.multiplayer: Sets the fuel crossfeed to be from right to left.

FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT
FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT.multiplayer: Turns selector 2 to LEFT position (fuel will be retrieved from Left Tip then Left Aux then Left Main).

FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT_AUX.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT_AUX
FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT_AUX.multiplayer: Turns selector 2 to LEFT AUX position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT_MAIN.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT_MAIN
FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT_MAIN.multiplayer: Sets the fuel selector for engine 2 to the left Main tank.

FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT
FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT.multiplayer: Turns selector 2 to RIGHT position (fuel will be retrieved from Right Tip then Right Aux then Right Main)

FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT_AUX.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT_AUX
FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT_AUX.multiplayer: Turns selector 2 to RIGHT AUX position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT_MAIN.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT_MAIN
FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT_MAIN.multiplayer: Sets the fuel selector for engine 2 to the right Main tank.

FUEL_SELECTOR_2_SET.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_2_SET
FUEL_SELECTOR_2_SET.multiplayer: Sets selector 2 position (see the Fuel Selector Codes list for the correct code to use).

FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT
FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT.multiplayer: Turns selector 3 to LEFT position (fuel will be retrieved from Left Tip then Left Aux then Left Main).

FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT_AUX.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT_AUX
FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT_AUX.multiplayer: Turns selector 3 to LEFT AUX position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT_MAIN.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT_MAIN
FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT_MAIN.multiplayer: Sets the fuel selector for engine 3 to the left Main tank.

FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT
FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT.multiplayer: Turns selector 3 to RIGHT position (fuel will be retrieved from Right Tip then Right Aux then Right Main).

FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT_AUX.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT_AUX
FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT_AUX.multiplayer: Turns selector 3 to RIGHT AUX position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT_MAIN.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT_MAIN
FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT_MAIN.multiplayer: Sets the fuel selector for engine 3 to the right Main tank.

FUEL_SELECTOR_3_SET.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_3_SET
FUEL_SELECTOR_3_SET.multiplayer: Sets selector 3 position (see the Fuel Selector Codes list for the correct code to use).

FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT
FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT.multiplayer: Turns selector 4 to LEFT position (fuel will be retrieved from Left Tip then Left Aux then Left Main).

FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT_AUX.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT_AUX
FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT_AUX.multiplayer: Turns selector 4 to LEFT AUX position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT_MAIN.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT_MAIN
FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT_MAIN.multiplayer: Sets the fuel selector for engine 4 to the left Main tank.

FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT
FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT.multiplayer: Turns selector 4 to RIGHT position (fuel will be retrieved from Right Tip then Right Aux then Right Main).

FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT_AUX.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT_AUX
FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT_AUX.multiplayer: Turns selector 4 to RIGHT AUX position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT_MAIN.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT_MAIN
FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT_MAIN.multiplayer: Sets the fuel selector for engine 4 to the right Main tank.

FUEL_SELECTOR_4_SET.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_4_SET
FUEL_SELECTOR_4_SET.multiplayer: Sets selector 4 position (see the Fuel Selector Codes list for the correct code to use).

FUEL_SELECTOR_ALL.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_ALL
FUEL_SELECTOR_ALL.multiplayer: Turn fuel selector 1 to the ALL position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT
FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT.multiplayer: Turns selector 1 to LEFT position (fuel will be retrieved from Left Tip then Left Aux then Left Main).

FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT_AUX.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT_AUX
FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT_AUX.multiplayer: Turns selector 1 to LEFT AUX position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT_MAIN.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT_MAIN
FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT_MAIN.multiplayer: Sets the fuel selector for engine 1 to the left Main tank.

FUEL_SELECTOR_OFF.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_OFF
FUEL_SELECTOR_OFF.multiplayer: Turn fuel selector 1 to the OFF position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT
FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT.multiplayer: Turns selector 1 to RIGHT position (fuel will be retrieved from Right Tip then Right Aux then Right Main).

FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT_AUX.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT_AUX
FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT_AUX.multiplayer: Turns selector 1 to RIGHT AUX position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT_MAIN.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT_MAIN
FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT_MAIN.multiplayer: Sets the fuel selector for engine 1 to the right Main tank.

FUEL_SELECTOR_SET.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_SET
FUEL_SELECTOR_SET.multiplayer: Sets selector 1 position (see the Fuel Selector Codes list for the correct code to use).

FUELSYSTEM_JUNCTION_SET.name: FUELSYSTEM_JUNCTION_SET
FUELSYSTEM_JUNCTION_SET.multiplayer: Set the current junction options for which lines are open or closed at any given time. This event requires two parameters: the first is the index of the junction (as defined by the N index of the Junction.N parameter), and the second is the Option index, which is what sets the lines to open/close.

FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_OFF.name: FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_OFF
FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_OFF.multiplayer: Turn a fuel pump off. The event requires the N index of the Pump.N parameter to define the pump to use.

FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_ON.name: FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_ON
FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_ON.multiplayer: Turn a fuel pump on. The event requires the N index of the Pump.N parameter to define the pump to use.

FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_SET.name: FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_SET
FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_SET.description:
[0]: Pump Index
          [1]: Status
                  0 = Off
                  1 = On
                  2 = Auto
FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_SET.multiplayer: Set a fuel pump to be either on or off or auto. The event requires the N index of the Pump.N parameter to define the pump to use.

FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_TOGGLE.name: FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_TOGGLE
FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggle a fuel pump on/off. The event requires the N index of the Pump.N parameter to define the pump to use.

FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_OFF.name: FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_OFF
FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_OFF.multiplayer: Turn a trigger event off. The event requires the N index of the Trigger.N parameter to define the trigger to switch off.

FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_ON.name: FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_ON
FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_ON.multiplayer: Turn a trigger event on. The event requires the N index of the Trigger.N parameter to define the trigger to switch off.

FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_SET.name: FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_SET
FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_SET.description:
[0]: Trigger Index
          [1]: Status, either on (1) or off (0)
FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_SET.multiplayer: Set a trigger event to be either on or off. The event requires the N index of the Trigger.N parameter to define the trigger to switch off.

FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_TOGGLE.name: FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_TOGGLE
FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggle a trigger event on/off. The event requires the N index of the Trigger.N parameter to define the trigger to switch off.

FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_CLOSE.name: FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_CLOSE
FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_CLOSE.multiplayer: Close a specific valve in the fuel system. The event requires the N index of the Valve.N parameter to define the valve to target.

FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_OPEN.name: FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_OPEN
FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_OPEN.multiplayer: Open a specific valve in the fuel system. The event requires the N index of the Valve.N parameter to define the valve to target.

FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_SET.name: FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_SET
FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_SET.description:
[0]: Valve Index
          [1]: Status, either open (1) or closed (0)
FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_SET.multiplayer: Set a valve to be either open or closed. The event requires the N index of the Valve.N parameter to define the valve to target.

FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_TOGGLE.name: FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_TOGGLE
FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggle a valve open/closed. The event requires the N index of the Valve.N parameter to define the valve to target.

SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_CUSTOM.name: SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_CUSTOM
SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_CUSTOM.multiplayer: Set the fuel transfer mode to the "custom" setting. Requires that at least 1 transfer pump has been defined in the flight_model.cfg file using the fuel_transfer_pump.N parameter.

FUEL_TRANSFER_CUSTOM_INDEX_TOGGLE.name: FUEL_TRANSFER_CUSTOM_INDEX_TOGGLE
FUEL_TRANSFER_CUSTOM_INDEX_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggle a custom fuel transfer pump on/off. The index is the Pump ID value supplied as part of the fuel pump definition for the fuel_transfer_pump.N parameter in the flight_model.cfg file.

SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_FORWARD.name: SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_FORWARD
SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_FORWARD.multiplayer: Set the fuel transfer system to use the "forward" setting, which pumps from tank 1 to tank 2.

SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_AFT.name: SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_AFT
SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_AFT.multiplayer: Set the fuel transfer system to use the "aft" setting, which pumps from tank 2 to tank 1.

SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_AUTO.name: SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_AUTO
SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_AUTO.multiplayer: Set the fuel transfer pump to automatically balance the fuel in tanks 1 and 2 to maintain the CG.

SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_OFF.name: SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_OFF
SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_OFF.multiplayer: Set the fuel transfer pump to off.

ADD_FUEL_QUANTITY.name: ADD_FUEL_QUANTITY
ADD_FUEL_QUANTITY.multiplayer: Adds fuel to the aircraft, 25% of capacity by default. 0 to 65535 (max fuel) can be passed.

ELECT_FUEL_PUMP1_SET.name: ELECT_FUEL_PUMP1_SET
ELECT_FUEL_PUMP1_SET.multiplayer:
Set the electrical pump status for engines 1-4. Values are as follows:
          
            0 = Off
            1 = On
            2 = Auto
          
          These keys are only useful when using the legacy [FUEL] system.

ENGINE_FUELFLOW_BUG_POSITION1.name: ENGINE_FUELFLOW_BUG_POSITION1
ENGINE_FUELFLOW_BUG_POSITION1.multiplayer: Not currently used in the simulation.

FUEL_DUMP_SWITCH_SET.name: FUEL_DUMP_SWITCH_SET
FUEL_DUMP_SWITCH_SET.multiplayer:
Set to 1 (TRUE) or 0 (FALSE). The switch can only be set to TRUE if fuel_dump_rate is specified in the aircraft configuration file, indicating that a fuel dump system exists.
          This key is only useful when using the legacy [FUEL] system.

FUEL_DUMP_TOGGLE.name: FUEL_DUMP_TOGGLE
FUEL_DUMP_TOGGLE.multiplayer:
Used to turn on (1, TRUE) or off (0, FALSE) the fuel dump switch.
          This key is only useful when using the legacy [FUEL] system.

MANUAL_FUEL_PRESSURE_PUMP.name: MANUAL_FUEL_PRESSURE_PUMP
MANUAL_FUEL_PRESSURE_PUMP.multiplayer: Activate the manual fuel pressure pump. Used for both modern [FUEL_SYSTEM] and legacy [FUEL] systems.

MANUAL_FUEL_PRESSURE_PUMP_SET.name: MANUAL_FUEL_PRESSURE_PUMP_SET
MANUAL_FUEL_PRESSURE_PUMP_SET.description:
[0]: The pump index
            [1]: A value between 0 and 16384
MANUAL_FUEL_PRESSURE_PUMP_SET.multiplayer: Set the position of the fuel manual pump handle, as a percentage. This key is only useful when using the modern [FUEL_SYSTEM].

MANUAL_FUEL_TRANSFER.name: MANUAL_FUEL_TRANSFER
MANUAL_FUEL_TRANSFER.multiplayer: When set to 1 (TRUE) it sets the fuel transfer mode to manual.

RELEASE_DROP_TANK_ALL.name: RELEASE_DROP_TANK_ALL
RELEASE_DROP_TANK_ALL.multiplayer: Release all external tanks that can be jettisoned.

RELEASE_DROP_TANK_1.name: RELEASE_DROP_TANK_1
RELEASE_DROP_TANK_1.multiplayer: Release the first external tank that can be jettisoned.

RELEASE_DROP_TANK_2.name: RELEASE_DROP_TANK_2
RELEASE_DROP_TANK_2.multiplayer: Release the second external tank that can be jettisoned.

REPAIR_AND_REFUEL.name: REPAIR_AND_REFUEL
REPAIR_AND_REFUEL.multiplayer: Fully repair and refuel the user aircraft. Ignored if flight realism is enforced.

REQUEST_FUEL_KEY.name: REQUEST_FUEL_KEY
REQUEST_FUEL_KEY.multiplayer: Request a fuel truck. The aircraft must be in a parking spot for this to be successful.

ANTIDETONATION_TANK_VALVE_TOGGLE.name: ANTIDETONATION_TANK_VALVE_TOGGLE
ANTIDETONATION_TANK_VALVE_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggle the anti-detonation valve. Pass a value to determine which tank to use if there are multiple tanks. See the Fuel Selector Codes list for the correct tank code to use. Note that this key requires the [ANTIDETONATION_SYSTEM.N] system to have been set up in the engine configuration file.

NITROUS_TANK_VALVE_TOGGLE.name: NITROUS_TANK_VALVE_TOGGLE
NITROUS_TANK_VALVE_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggle the nitrous valve. Pass a value to determine which tank to use if there are multiple tanks. See the Fuel Selector Codes list for the correct tank code to use. Note that this key requires the [NITROUS_SYSTEM.N] system to have been set up in the engine configuration file.

AUTO_HOVER_OFF.name: AUTO_HOVER_OFF
AUTO_HOVER_OFF.multiplayer:
Disable the auto-hover function of the helicopter, if one is available.
          NOTE: This is currently not implemented in the Simulation

AUTO_HOVER_ON.name: AUTO_HOVER_ON
AUTO_HOVER_ON.multiplayer:
Enable the auto-hover function of the helicopter - if one is available.
          NOTE: This is currently not implemented in the Simulation

AUTO_HOVER_SET.name: AUTO_HOVER_SET
AUTO_HOVER_SET.multiplayer:
Set the auto-hover - if available - to either on (True, 1) or off (False, 0).
          NOTE: This is currently not implemented in the Simulation

AUTO_HOVER_TOGGLE.name: AUTO_HOVER_TOGGLE
AUTO_HOVER_TOGGLE.multiplayer:
Toggle the auto-hover - if available - between on (True, 1) and off (False, 0).
          NOTE: This is currently not implemented in the Simulation

AXIS_COLLECTIVE_SET.name: AXIS_COLLECTIVE_SET
AXIS_COLLECTIVE_SET.multiplayer: Set the collective pitch angle (a value from 0 to 1 interpolated from the 0 to 16384 input).

AXIS_STEERING_SET (HELICOPTERS).name: AXIS_STEERING_SET (helicopters)
AXIS_STEERING_SET (HELICOPTERS).multiplayer: Set the steering axis value from -1 to 1 (interpolated from the -16384 to 16384 input).

AXIS_TAIL_ROTOR_SET.name: AXIS_TAIL_ROTOR_SET
AXIS_TAIL_ROTOR_SET.multiplayer: Sets the tail rotor speed as a value from 0 to 1 (interpolated from the 0 to 16384 input).

COLLECTIVE_DECR.name: COLLECTIVE_DECR
COLLECTIVE_DECR.multiplayer: Decrease the engine collective by 0.05. Minimum value is clamped to 0.

COLLECTIVE_INCR.name: COLLECTIVE_INCR
COLLECTIVE_INCR.multiplayer: Increase the engine collective by 0.05. Minimum value is clamped to 0.

DECREASE_HELO_GOV_BEEP.name: DECREASE_HELO_GOV_BEEP
DECREASE_HELO_GOV_BEEP.multiplayer:
If the helicopter has an engine trimmer, this event can be used to decrease the nominal engine/rotor RPM that the governor is trying to maintain.
          The amount that the trim will be adjusted by is set using the engine_trim_rate CFG parameter, and the min and max achievable values are set using engine_trim_min and engine_trim_max. Alternatively, you may supply a value that will override that set in the engine_trim_rate CFG parameter (the min and max values will still be used).

INCREASE_HELO_GOV_BEEP.name: INCREASE_HELO_GOV_BEEP
INCREASE_HELO_GOV_BEEP.multiplayer:
If the helicopter has an engine trimmer, this event can be used to increase the nominal engine/rotor RPM that the governor is trying to maintain.
          The amount that the trim will be adjusted by is set using the engine_trim_rate CFG parameter, and the min and max achievable values are set using engine_trim_min and engine_trim_max. Alternatively, you may supply a value that will override that set in the engine_trim_rate CFG parameter (the min and max values will still be used).

SET_HELO_GOV_BEEP.name: SET_HELO_GOV_BEEP
SET_HELO_GOV_BEEP.multiplayer:
This is used to set the helicopter engine trimmer value directly as a negative or positive deviation from 1, where 1 is the rated nominal engine RPM.
          The final engine trimmer value will be limited according to the engine_trim_min and engine_trim_max settings.

AXIS_CYCLIC_LATERAL_SET.name: AXIS_CYCLIC_LATERAL_SET
AXIS_CYCLIC_LATERAL_SET.multiplayer: Set the lateral cyclic axis as a value between -16384 and 16384.

CYCLIC_LATERAL_LEFT.name: CYCLIC_LATERAL_LEFT
CYCLIC_LATERAL_LEFT.multiplayer: Change the lateral cyclic (left) by -0.098 when pressed. If held down, the change will happen more rapidly.

CYCLIC_LATERAL_RIGHT.name: CYCLIC_LATERAL_RIGHT
CYCLIC_LATERAL_RIGHT.multiplayer: Change the lateral cyclic (right) by 0.098 when pressed. If held down, the change will happen more rapidly.

CYCLIC_LONGITUDINAL_DOWN.name: CYCLIC_LONGITUDINAL_DOWN
CYCLIC_LONGITUDINAL_DOWN.multiplayer: Change the longitudinal cyclic (down) by -0.049 when pressed. If held down, the change will happen more rapidly.

CYCLIC_LONGITUDINAL_UP.name: CYCLIC_LONGITUDINAL_UP
CYCLIC_LONGITUDINAL_UP.multiplayer: Change the longitudinal cyclic (up) by 0.049 when pressed. If held down, the change will happen more rapidly.

AXIS_HELICOPTER_THROTTLE1_SET.name: AXIS_HELICOPTER_THROTTLE1_SET
AXIS_HELICOPTER_THROTTLE1_SET.multiplayer: Set the throttle 1 or 2 value from 0 to 1 (interpolated from the 0 to 16384 input).

AXIS_HELICOPTER_THROTTLE_SET.name: AXIS_HELICOPTER_THROTTLE_SET
AXIS_HELICOPTER_THROTTLE_SET.multiplayer: Set all throttles to a value from 0 to 1 (interpolated from the 0 to 16384 input).

HELICOPTER_THROTTLE1_DEC.name: HELICOPTER_THROTTLE1_DEC
HELICOPTER_THROTTLE1_DEC.multiplayer: By default this will decrement throttle 1 or 2 by 1/128, to a minimum of 0. If you provide an input parameter then this will be internally normalised to a value between 0 and 1 and used to decrement instead.

HELICOPTER_THROTTLE1_INC.name: HELICOPTER_THROTTLE1_INC
HELICOPTER_THROTTLE1_INC.multiplayer: By default this will increment throttle 1 or 2 by 1/128, to a maximum of 1. If you provide an input parameter then this will be internally normalised to a value between 0 and 1 and used to increment instead.

HELICOPTER_THROTTLE1_SET.name: HELICOPTER_THROTTLE1_SET
HELICOPTER_THROTTLE1_SET.multiplayer: Set throttle 1 or 2 based on the input value. The input is between 0 and 16384, which will be normalised to a value between 0 and 1.

HELICOPTER_THROTTLE_DEC.name: HELICOPTER_THROTTLE_DEC
HELICOPTER_THROTTLE_DEC.multiplayer: By default this will decrement all throttles by 1/128, to a minimum of 0. If you provide an input parameter then this will be internally normalised to a value between 0 and 1 and used to decrement instead.

HELICOPTER_THROTTLE_INC.name: HELICOPTER_THROTTLE_INC
HELICOPTER_THROTTLE_INC.multiplayer: By default this will increment all throttles by 1/128, to a maximum of 1. If you provide an input parameter then this will be internally normalised to a value between 0 and 1 and used to increment instead.

HELICOPTER_THROTTLE_SET.name: HELICOPTER_THROTTLE_SET
HELICOPTER_THROTTLE_SET.multiplayer: Set all throttles based on the input value. The input is between 0 and 16384, which will be normalised to a value between 0 and 1.

ROTOR_BRAKE_OFF.name: ROTOR_BRAKE_OFF
ROTOR_BRAKE_OFF.multiplayer: Switches off the rotor brake switch .

ROTOR_BRAKE_ON.name: ROTOR_BRAKE_ON
ROTOR_BRAKE_ON.multiplayer: Switches on the rotor brake switch .

ROTOR_BRAKE_SET.name: ROTOR_BRAKE_SET
ROTOR_BRAKE_SET.multiplayer: Set the rotor brake switch to be on (1) or off (0).

ROTOR_BRAKE_TOGGLE.name: ROTOR_BRAKE_TOGGLE
ROTOR_BRAKE_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggle the rotor brake switch between on (1) and off (0).

ROTOR_CLUTCH_SWITCH_SET.name: ROTOR_CLUTCH_SWITCH_SET
ROTOR_CLUTCH_SWITCH_SET.multiplayer: Sets the rotor clutch switch to on (1) or off (0).

ROTOR_CLUTCH_SWITCH_TOGGLE.name: ROTOR_CLUTCH_SWITCH_TOGGLE
ROTOR_CLUTCH_SWITCH_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggles the rotor clutch switch between on (1) and off (0).

ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_OFF.name: ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_OFF
ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_OFF.multiplayer: Sets the rotor governor switch to off (0).

ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_ON.name: ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_ON
ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_ON.multiplayer: Sets the rotor governor switch to on (1).

ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_SET.name: ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_SET
ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_SET.multiplayer: Sets the rotor governor switch to on/off (1,0).

ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_TOGGLE.name: ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_TOGGLE
ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Toggles the rotor governor switch between on (1) and off (0).

ROTOR_LATERAL_TRIM_DEC.name: ROTOR_LATERAL_TRIM_DEC
ROTOR_LATERAL_TRIM_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the roll (lateral) rotor trim by the amount specified by the parameter right_trim_step.

ROTOR_LATERAL_TRIM_INC.name: ROTOR_LATERAL_TRIM_INC
ROTOR_LATERAL_TRIM_INC.multiplayer: Increments the roll (lateral) rotor trim by the amount specified by the parameter right_trim_step.

ROTOR_LATERAL_TRIM_SET.name: ROTOR_LATERAL_TRIM_SET
ROTOR_LATERAL_TRIM_SET.multiplayer: Sets the roll (lateral) rotor trim to a value between -1 and 1 (interpolated from the +/-16384 input value).

ROTOR_LONGITUDINAL_TRIM_DEC.name: ROTOR_LONGITUDINAL_TRIM_DEC
ROTOR_LONGITUDINAL_TRIM_DEC.multiplayer: Decrements the pitch (longitudinal) rotor trim by the amount specified by the parameter front_trim_step.

ROTOR_LONGITUDINAL_TRIM_INC.name: ROTOR_LONGITUDINAL_TRIM_INC
ROTOR_LONGITUDINAL_TRIM_INC.multiplayer: Increments the pitch (longitudinal) rotor trim by the amount specified by the parameter front_trim_step.

ROTOR_LONGITUDINAL_TRIM_SET.name: ROTOR_LONGITUDINAL_TRIM_SET
ROTOR_LONGITUDINAL_TRIM_SET.multiplayer: Sets the pitch (longitudinal) rotor trim to a value between -1 and 1 (interpolated from the +/-16384 input value).

ROTOR_TRIM_RESET.name: ROTOR_TRIM_RESET
ROTOR_TRIM_RESET.multiplayer: Resets the rotor time values to their default.

ROTOR_BRAKE.name: ROTOR_BRAKE
ROTOR_BRAKE.multiplayer: Sets rotor brake switch on. Deprecated in favour of ROTOR_BRAKE_ON.

ABORT.name: ABORT
ABORT.multiplayer: Quit Microsoft Flight Simulator without a message.

AUDIO_PANEL_VOLUME_INC.name: AUDIO_PANEL_VOLUME_INC
AUDIO_PANEL_VOLUME_INC.multiplayer: Increases the audio panel sound volume by 0.01. The resulting value will be clamped between 0 and 1.

AUDIO_PANEL_VOLUME_DEC.name: AUDIO_PANEL_VOLUME_DEC
AUDIO_PANEL_VOLUME_DEC.multiplayer: Decreases the audio panel sound volume by 0.01. The resulting value will be clamped between 0 and 1.

AUDIO_PANEL_VOLUME_SET.name: AUDIO_PANEL_VOLUME_SET
AUDIO_PANEL_VOLUME_SET.multiplayer: Set the audio panel volume to the given value, clamped between 0 and 1.

AUTOCOORD_TOGGLE.name: AUTOCOORD_TOGGLE
AUTOCOORD_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Switch inversion of Y axis controls on or off.

CAPTURE_SCREENSHOT.name: CAPTURE_SCREENSHOT
CAPTURE_SCREENSHOT.multiplayer: Capture the current view as a screenshot. Which will be saved to a bmp file in: My Documents\Pictures\

RELOAD_USER_AIRCRAFT.name: RELOAD_USER_AIRCRAFT
RELOAD_USER_AIRCRAFT.multiplayer: Reloads the user aircraft data (from cache if same type loaded as an AI,otherwise from disk)

DEBUG_0.name: DEBUG_0
DEBUG_0.description:
DEBUG_1
          DEBUG_2
          DEBUG_3
          DEBUG_4
          DEBUG_5
          DEBUG_6
          DEBUG_7
          DEBUG_8
          DEBUG_9

EXIT.name: EXIT
EXIT.multiplayer: Quit Microsoft Flight Simulator with a message

EXTERNAL_SYSTEM_SET.name: EXTERNAL_SYSTEM_SET
EXTERNAL_SYSTEM_SET.multiplayer: Generic key event to set a number value.

EXTERNAL_SYSTEM_TOGGLE.name: EXTERNAL_SYSTEM_TOGGLE
EXTERNAL_SYSTEM_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Generic key event to toggle a value on/off (true/false).

FULL_WINDOW_TOGGLE.name: FULL_WINDOW_TOGGLE
FULL_WINDOW_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Not currently used in the simulation.

MINUS.name: MINUS
MINUS.multiplayer: Used in conjunction with "selected" parameters to decrease their value (e.g.,radio frequency)

MOUSE_LOOK_TOGGLE.name: MOUSE_LOOK_TOGGLE
MOUSE_LOOK_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Switch Mouse Look mode on or off. Mouse Look mode enables a user to control their view using the mouse, and holding down the space bar.

PANEL_1.name: PANEL_1
PANEL_1.description:
PANEL_2
          PANEL_3
          PANEL_4
          PANEL_5
          PANEL_6
          PANEL_7
          PANEL_8
          PANEL_9

PANEL_TOGGLE.name: PANEL_TOGGLE
PANEL_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Not currently used in the simulation.

PLUS.name: PLUS
PLUS.multiplayer: Used in conjunction with "selected" parameters to increase their value (e.g.,radio frequency)

READOUTS_SLEW.name: READOUTS_SLEW
READOUTS_SLEW.multiplayer: Cycle through information readouts while in slew

REFRESH_SCENERY.name: REFRESH_SCENERY
REFRESH_SCENERY.multiplayer:
Reloads scenery.
          Deprecated, do not use.

REQUEST_CATERING.name: REQUEST_CATERING
REQUEST_CATERING.multiplayer: Requests catering truck on the nearest airport.

REQUEST_LUGGAGE.name: REQUEST_LUGGAGE
REQUEST_LUGGAGE.multiplayer: Requests a baggage loader from the nearest airport.

REQUEST_POWER_SUPPLY.name: REQUEST_POWER_SUPPLY
REQUEST_POWER_SUPPLY.multiplayer: Requests ground power unit from the nearest airport.

TOGGLE_AIRPORT_NAME_DISPLAY.name: TOGGLE_AIRPORT_NAME_DISPLAY
TOGGLE_AIRPORT_NAME_DISPLAY.multiplayer: Turn on or off the airport name.

TOGGLE_ENEMY_INDICATOR.name: TOGGLE_ENEMY_INDICATOR
TOGGLE_ENEMY_INDICATOR.multiplayer: Not currently used in the simulation.

TOGGLE_JETWAY.name: TOGGLE_JETWAY
TOGGLE_JETWAY.multiplayer: Requests a jetway, which will only be answered if the aircraft is at a parking spot, or sends already requested jetway away.

TOGGLE_RAMPTRUCK.name: TOGGLE_RAMPTRUCK
TOGGLE_RAMPTRUCK.multiplayer: Requests a boarding ramp from the nearest airport, or sends an already requested boarding ramp away.

TOOLTIP_UNITS_SET.name: TOOLTIP_UNITS_SET
TOOLTIP_UNITS_SET.multiplayer: Not currently used in the simulation.

VIDEO_RECORD_TOGGLE.name: VIDEO_RECORD_TOGGLE
VIDEO_RECORD_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turn on or off the video recording feature. This records uncompressed AVI format files to: My Documents\Videos\

VIEW_WINDOW_TITLES_TOGGLE.name: VIEW_WINDOW_TITLES_TOGGLE
VIEW_WINDOW_TITLES_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turn window titles on or off.

YAXIS_INVERT_TOGGLE.name: YAXIS_INVERT_TOGGLE
YAXIS_INVERT_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Switch inversion of Y axis controls on or off.

VERTICAL_SPEED_DEC.name: VERTICAL_SPEED_DEC
VERTICAL_SPEED_DEC.description:
[0] Value between -16000 and 16000 to decrement by
            (maps to a value between -1 and 1)
VERTICAL_SPEED_DEC.multiplayer: By default this will decrement the vertical speed by 1/128, but you may supply a decrement amount as a parameter.

VERTICAL_SPEED_INC.name: VERTICAL_SPEED_INC
VERTICAL_SPEED_INC.description:
[0] Value between -16000 and 16000 to increment by
            (maps to a value between -1 and 1)
VERTICAL_SPEED_INC.multiplayer: By default this will increment the vertical speed by 1/128, but you may supply an increment amount as a parameter.

VERTICAL_SPEED_SET.name: VERTICAL_SPEED_SET
VERTICAL_SPEED_SET.description: [0] The axis value between -1 and 1 (maps to -16000 and 16000)
VERTICAL_SPEED_SET.multiplayer: Set the vertical speed to a value between -1 and 1.

FREEZE_LATITUDE_LONGITUDE_TOGGLE.name: FREEZE_LATITUDE_LONGITUDE_TOGGLE
FREEZE_LATITUDE_LONGITUDE_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turns the freezing of the lat/lon position of the aircraft (either user or AI controlled) on or off. If this key event is set, it means that the latitude and longitude of the aircraft are not being controlled by ESP, so enabling, for example, a SimConnect client to control the position of the aircraft. This can also apply to altitude and attitude. Refer to the simulation variables: IS_LATITUDE_LONGITUDE_FREEZE_ON, IS_ALTITUDE_FREEZE_ON, and IS_ATTITUDE_FREEZE_ON. Refer also to the SimConnect_AIReleaseControl function.

FREEZE_LATITUDE_LONGITUDE_SET.name: FREEZE_LATITUDE_LONGITUDE_SET
FREEZE_LATITUDE_LONGITUDE_SET.multiplayer: Freezes the lat/lon position of the aircraft.

FREEZE_ALTITUDE_TOGGLE.name: FREEZE_ALTITUDE_TOGGLE
FREEZE_ALTITUDE_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turns the freezing of the altitude of the aircraft on or off.

FREEZE_ALTITUDE_SET.name: FREEZE_ALTITUDE_SET
FREEZE_ALTITUDE_SET.multiplayer: Freezes the altitude of the aircraft.

FREEZE_ATTITUDE_TOGGLE.name: FREEZE_ATTITUDE_TOGGLE
FREEZE_ATTITUDE_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turns the freezing of the attitude (pitch, bank and heading) of the aircraft on or off.

FREEZE_ATTITUDE_SET.name: FREEZE_ATTITUDE_SET
FREEZE_ATTITUDE_SET.multiplayer: Freezes the attitude (pitch, bank and heading) of the aircraft.

POINT_OF_INTEREST_TOGGLE_POINTER.name: POINT_OF_INTEREST_TOGGLE_POINTER
POINT_OF_INTEREST_TOGGLE_POINTER.multiplayer: Turn the point-of-interest indicator (often a light beam) on or off. Refer to the Missions system documentation.

POINT_OF_INTEREST_CYCLE_PREVIOUS.name: POINT_OF_INTEREST_CYCLE_PREVIOUS
POINT_OF_INTEREST_CYCLE_PREVIOUS.multiplayer: Change the current point-of-interest to the previous point-of-interest.

POINT_OF_INTEREST_CYCLE_NEXT.name: POINT_OF_INTEREST_CYCLE_NEXT
POINT_OF_INTEREST_CYCLE_NEXT.multiplayer: Change the current point-of-interest to the next point-of-interest.

MP_BROADCAST_VOICE_CAPTURE_START.name: MP_BROADCAST_VOICE_CAPTURE_START
MP_BROADCAST_VOICE_CAPTURE_START.multiplayer: Start capturing audio from the users computer and transmitting it to all other players in the multiplayer session.

MP_PLAYER_CYCLE.name: MP_PLAYER_CYCLE
MP_PLAYER_CYCLE.multiplayer: Cycle through the current user aircraft.

MP_PLAYER_FOLLOW.name: MP_PLAYER_FOLLOW
MP_PLAYER_FOLLOW.multiplayer: Set the view to follow the selected user aircraft.

MP_TRANSFER_CONTROL.name: MP_TRANSFER_CONTROL
MP_TRANSFER_CONTROL.multiplayer: Toggle to the next player to track

MP_VOICE_CAPTURE_START.name: MP_VOICE_CAPTURE_START
MP_VOICE_CAPTURE_START.multiplayer: Start capturing audio from the users computer and transmitting it to all other players in the multiplayer session who are turned to the same radio frequency.

TOGGLE_RACERESULTS_WINDOW.name: TOGGLE_RACERESULTS_WINDOW
TOGGLE_RACERESULTS_WINDOW.multiplayer: Show or hide multi-player race results.

SIM_RATE.name: SIM_RATE
SIM_RATE.multiplayer: Selects the simulation rate. Use the PLUS and MINUS events to increment/decrement the value.

SIM_RATE_DECR.name: SIM_RATE_DECR
SIM_RATE_DECR.multiplayer: Decreases the simulation rate, which will slow down the in-simulation time.

SIM_RATE_INCR.name: SIM_RATE_INCR
SIM_RATE_INCR.multiplayer: Increase the simulation rate, which will speed up the in-simulation time.

AXIS_PAN_PITCH.name: AXIS_PAN_PITCH
AXIS_PAN_PITCH.multiplayer: Sets the pitch of the camera axis. Requires an angle.

AXIS_PAN_HEADING.name: AXIS_PAN_HEADING
AXIS_PAN_HEADING.multiplayer: Sets the heading of the axis. Requires an angle.

AXIS_PAN_TILT.name: AXIS_PAN_TILT
AXIS_PAN_TILT.multiplayer: Sets the tilt of the axis. Requires an angle.

VIEW_CHASE_DISTANCE_ADD.name: VIEW_CHASE_DISTANCE_ADD
VIEW_CHASE_DISTANCE_ADD.multiplayer: Increments the distance of the view camera from the chase object (such as in Spot Plane view, or viewing an AI controlled aircraft).

VIEW_CHASE_DISTANCE_SUB.name: VIEW_CHASE_DISTANCE_SUB
VIEW_CHASE_DISTANCE_SUB.multiplayer: Decrements the distance of the view camera from the chase object.

MAP_ZOOM_FINE_OUT.name: MAP_ZOOM_FINE_OUT
MAP_ZOOM_FINE_OUT.multiplayer: Fine zoom out in map view

MAP_ZOOM_SET.name: MAP_ZOOM_SET
MAP_ZOOM_SET.multiplayer: Not currently used in the simulation.

VIEW_FORWARD_LEFT.multiplayer: Sets view direction forward and left

VIEW_FORWARD_RIGHT.name: VIEW_FORWARD_RIGHT
VIEW_FORWARD_RIGHT.multiplayer: Sets view direction forward and right

VIEW_FORWARD_RIGHT_UP.name: VIEW_FORWARD_RIGHT_UP
VIEW_FORWARD_RIGHT_UP.multiplayer: Sets view forward, right, and up

VIEW_FORWARD_LEFT_UP.name: VIEW_FORWARD_LEFT_UP
VIEW_FORWARD_LEFT_UP.multiplayer: Sets view forward left and up

VIEW_LEFT.name: VIEW_LEFT
VIEW_LEFT.multiplayer: Sets view direction to the left

VIEW_LINKING_SET.name: VIEW_LINKING_SET
VIEW_LINKING_SET.multiplayer: Links all the views from one camera together, so that panning the view will change the view of all the linked cameras.

VIEW_LINKING_TOGGLE.name: VIEW_LINKING_TOGGLE
VIEW_LINKING_TOGGLE.multiplayer: Turns view linking on or off.

VIEW1_MODE_SET.name: VIEW1_MODE_SET
VIEW1_MODE_SET.multiplayer: Not currently used in the simulation.

VIEW_PANEL_ALPHA_SELECT.name: VIEW_PANEL_ALPHA_SELECT
VIEW_PANEL_ALPHA_SELECT.multiplayer: Sets the mode to change the alpha-blending, so the keys KEY_PLUS and KEY_MINUS increment and decrement the value.

VIEW_PANEL_ALPHA_SET.name: VIEW_PANEL_ALPHA_SET
VIEW_PANEL_ALPHA_SET.multiplayer: Sets the alpha-blending value for the panel. Takes a parameter in the range 0to 255. The alpha-blending can be changed from the keyboard using Ctrl-Shift-T,and the plus and minus keys.

VIEW_REAR.name: VIEW_REAR
VIEW_REAR.multiplayer: Sets view direction to the rear

VIEW_REAR_LEFT.name: VIEW_REAR_LEFT
VIEW_REAR_LEFT.multiplayer: Sets view direction to the rear and left

VIEW_REAR_LEFT_UP.name: VIEW_REAR_LEFT_UP
VIEW_REAR_LEFT_UP.multiplayer: Sets view rear left and up

VIEW_REAR_RIGHT.name: VIEW_REAR_RIGHT
VIEW_REAR_RIGHT.multiplayer: Sets view direction to the rear and right

VIEW_REAR_RIGHT_UP.name: VIEW_REAR_RIGHT_UP
VIEW_REAR_RIGHT_UP.multiplayer: Sets view rear, right, and up

VIEW_RESET.name: VIEW_RESET
VIEW_RESET.multiplayer: Resets the view to the default

VIEW_RIGHT.name: VIEW_RIGHT
VIEW_RIGHT.multiplayer: Sets view direction to the right

VIEW_SNAP_PANEL_RESET.name: VIEW_SNAP_PANEL_RESET
VIEW_SNAP_PANEL_RESET.multiplayer: Not currently used in the simulation.

VIEW_VIRTUAL_COCKPIT_FORWARD.name: VIEW_VIRTUAL_COCKPIT_FORWARD
VIEW_VIRTUAL_COCKPIT_FORWARD.multiplayer: Switch immediately to the forward view, in virtual cockpit mode.

PAN_RESET_COCKPIT.name: PAN_RESET_COCKPIT
PAN_RESET_COCKPIT.multiplayer: Reset panning to forward, if in cockpit view
